INSERT INTO `events` VALUES (10,'Partner Acrobatics & Flying Therapeutics Intensive Teacher Training','2013-11-15 00:00:00','2013-12-13 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','4 weeks of intensive practice and deep learning about how to teach Partner Acrobatics.<div>Space to become a Flying Therapeutics practitioner too.</div><div>Teachers: Niko Douwes, Emily Baxter, Lorenzo Becchi.</div>','<p style=\"font-size: medium;\">Check the official website for more details:&nbsp;</p><div style=\"font-size: medium;\"><a href=\"http://www.partner-acrobatics.com/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">www.partner-acrobatics.com</a><div><div><br></div><div><b>Lorenzo Becchi</b>,&nbsp;<b>Niko Douwes</b>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>Emily Baxter</b>, collaborating to share their love of Acrobatics, Flying Therapeutics and Teaching.</div><div><br></div><div><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times;\">This is an intensive, we will work hard and play hard. There will be long hours, challenges and triumphs. You will increase strength and flexibility in all areas of your life. As you are presented with challenges and you work through them in a group, supported by friends who will become like family, you will learn a lot about yourself, not just acrobatics.</p><p style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times;\">We will spend the four weeks enhancing our practice and deepening our exploration into the role of a teacher, practicing teaching and trainees will also be trained as \"&nbsp;<a href=\"http://flyingtherapeutics.org/certification.php\" target=\"_blank\">Flying Therapeutics Practitioners</a>&nbsp;\".</p></div></div></div>','http://www.partner-acrobatics.com'),(11,'Summer Convergence 2013','2013-08-03 00:00:00','2013-08-11 00:00:00',1,'Polland','The Summer Convergence - bringing together acrobatics, healing arts and yoga into a week long gathering.&nbsp;<div>With Jaqui Wan,&nbsp;Yohann Guichard, Thorsten Bohle, Jasper Herrman, Lorenzo Becchi.</div>','<div>Check the official website:</div><a href=\"http://summerconvergence.eu/\" title=\"Summer Convergence website\" target=\"\">http://summerconvergence.eu/</a><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><div>With the success of last year retreat we are running it again. Five European, phenomenally experienced and renowned teachers are collaborating to bring you a unique offering to explore the infinite possibilities of the human form. A chance to grow, to play, to heal and be. We are offering a chance to delve deeper into the practices of yoga, acrobatics and the healing arts of Thai massage and flying therapeutics. This gathering will fantastic country house situated in the heart of Polish countryside. This retreat will be the perfect exploratory lab for passionate acro-bodywork squirrels.</div><div><br></div><div>The great convergence of 2013!</div></div>',''),(12,'IAC-International Acrobatics Convention','2013-06-10 00:00:00','2013-06-17 00:00:00',1,'Cesenatico, Italy','<div>The purpose of the festival is to help the sport of acrobatics to spread throughout the world</div>','<div><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); \"><br></span></div><div><div><a href=\"http://acrobatics.nl/\" title=\"\" target=\"\">http://acrobatics.nl/</a></div><div><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/177552749048449/?ref=ts&amp;fref=ts\" title=\"\" target=\"\">https://www.facebook.com/events/177552749048449/?ref=ts&amp;fref=ts</a></div></div><div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;The way we do this by holding a convention of somewhere between 100 and 200 people. We started in Croatia, and went via France and Sweden to Denmark this year. We are moving the festival from country to country every year. This is to make sure every acrobat gets to have a change to participate without having to travel half the world. Of course it\'s also nice to go to unknown places that are touristic or otherwise interesting to make a longer stay possible. Meanwhile we hope our influence on the local acrobatic-scene is big enough to make a prolongation possible for a local festival.&nbsp;</div></div>',''),(15,'Extreme Convention','2013-04-13 00:00:00','2013-04-14 00:00:00',1,'Antwerp, Belgium','At Extreme Convention, we practice contemporary and extreme circus and acrobatics techniques in a rather interactive way.','For three days, circus devotees of all levels can participate in different workshops, initiated by many skillful artists. The bascule, Chinese pole, the rhönrad, the roue cyr, the trampoline, … are only a few of many techniques we offer to the visitors of our festival!','http://www.extremeconvention.be/extreme/en/index.html'),(13,'Dutch Acro','2013-05-17 00:00:00','2013-05-20 00:00:00',1,'Bemmel, Netherlands','<div>The Netherlands Acrobatics Festival is well-known for its large variety of workshops in acrobatics and related activities.</div><div><div>The festival is by acrobats for acrobats and it is tradition that anyone with something exciting to offer shares this by running one or more workshops.</div></div><br>','<div><div>There will be:</div><div>- 10 rounds of workshops at all levels;</div><div>- two excellent evening shows;</div><div>- all the good teachers are coming;</div><div>- camping on short grass (at the soccer field), therefore no pollen and not so humid :-)</div><div>- great vegetarian food</div></div><div><br><br></div>',' http://festival.akrobatiek.nl/'),(14,'Pre Convention to Dutch Acro','2014-06-02 00:00:00','2014-06-06 00:00:00',1,'near the border of the Netherlands','Precon for those wanting to get their level up at a 4 day training just before the Dutch Acrofestival.','		\r\n	\r\n	\r\n		<div class=\"column\">\r\n			<p></p><p></p><div><div>Here we go again one more Preconvention. &nbsp;Can\'t wait to see everyone together again. &nbsp;Four days of hard training and good times,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">food and accommodation included.</span></div><div><br></div><div>Location de Vlierhof is set:</div><div>http://vlierhof.org/</div><div><br></div><div>Starting on the 2nd at 9 in the Morning until lunch on friday the 6th. &nbsp;We then go straight to Dutch acro.</div><div>http://www.akrobatiek.nl/home.php</div><div><br></div><div>After registration and payment your place is secure. &nbsp;Remember there are only 10 dorm spaces&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">but lots of camping.</span></div><div>Register through this link:</div><div>https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1l4gFoWflVjljiqudRNH_CN9l5bNeMV4aQoDu81je_mE/viewform</div><div><br></div><div>The program will be very much the same as last year:</div><div>Fons</div><div>Wybren</div><div>Niko</div><div>Emily Baxter</div><div><br></div><div>Not 100% certain yet but possible guest teachers:</div><div>Jade</div><div>Ben</div><div>Suze</div><div>Emily Nichols</div><div>Noel</div><div>Hugo</div><div>Bart and Kirsty</div><div>Maartje and Harm</div></div><p></p><p></p>\r\n		</div>','https://www.facebook.com/preconvention'),(43,'Dutch Acrobatics Convention','2014-06-06 00:00:00','2014-06-09 00:00:00',1,'Hilversum, Netherlands','<div>The Netherlands Acrobatics Festival is well-known for its large variety of workshops in acrobatics and related activities.</div><div>The festival is by acrobats for acrobats and it is tradition that anyone with something exciting to offer shares this by running one or more workshops</div>','<div><div>There will be:</div><div>- 10 rounds of workshops at all levels;</div><div>- two excellent evening shows;</div><div>- all the good teachers are coming;</div><div>- camping on short grass (at the soccer field), therefore no pollen and not so humid :-)</div><div>- great vegetarian food</div></div><div><br></div>https://www.facebook.com/events/544275032307905/?ref=notif¬if_t=plan_edited<div><br></div><div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">.&nbsp;</span></div></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>','http://www.akrobatiek.nl/'),(41,'British Acrobatics And Circus Festival ','2014-05-23 00:00:00','2014-05-25 00:00:00',1,'Uckfield, England','The first three day greenfield acrobatics and circus festival in the south of England. The main focus will be partner acrobatics but also other circus skills depending on interest','<div>So far Fons has confirmed he will be there, other instructors TBC. All levels will be catered for. Please spread the word!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>This is 2 weeks before Bemmel, Dutch acro festival. It will be a community based camping event similar to Bemmel, in the beautiful Sussex countryside. Please register your interest on the facebook page and webpage to follow soon.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/1420791421469985/1436839009865226/?notif_t=plan_mall_activity'),(42,'NW AcroYoga Summer Camp-Out','2014-07-24 00:00:00','2014-07-27 00:00:00',1,'Buxton, USA','3 Days of AcroYoga, Slacklining, Dancing, Camping, and More....','<div>Located on 80 acres of farmland just 45 minutes outside of Portland.</div><div><br></div><div>Multiple workshops at all levels each day.....</div><div><br></div><div>Last year was a huge success and this year space is definitely limited so sign up early.</div><div><br></div><div>Teachers: Jacob Handwerker, Amy Impellizzeri, and more....</div><div><br></div><div>You are responsible for all camping gear. Organic vegetarian delicious meals from Thursday dinner to Sunday lunch included.</div><div><br></div><div>Kids and families welcome!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Smoke, Alcohol, and Drug free. Please leave pets at home too.</div><div><br></div><div>Prices:</div><div>$225 before March 15th</div><div>$260 before June 1st</div><div>$295 after June 1st.</div><div><br></div><div>This event will definitely sell out so register early.</div><div><br></div><div>Arrive Thursday after 2:00PM and leave Sunday by 5:00PM.</div><div><br></div><div>To register email: acroyogacampout@gmail.com</div><div><br></div><div>Prices and more details soon.....</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/663609906994149/'),(16,'Bremen Convention','2013-10-10 00:00:00','2013-10-13 00:00:00',1,'Bremen, Germany','<div>4 days of Acro.</div>','<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">University of Bremen, \"Sportturm\".</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">There you can do acrobatics, sleep and swim.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">We will organize&nbsp;<b>vegetarian</b>&nbsp;food!</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">Please bring isomat, sleepingbag and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">swimming gear.</p>','http://www.akrobatik-bremen.de/en_con_aktuell.htm'),(19,'Frankfurt Akrobatik Festival','2013-04-26 00:00:00','2013-04-28 00:00:00',1,'Frankfurt, Germany','<br>','All facts and enrollment will be online in february 2013 on: <a href=\"http://www.akrobatik.info\" title=\"\" target=\"\">www.akrobatik.info</a>','https://www.facebook.com/events/535517199809530/'),(20,'Karlsruher Akrobatikfestival','2013-04-04 00:00:00','2013-04-07 00:00:00',1,'Karlsruhe, Germany','<br>','<br>','http://www.akrobatik.kleinkunst-ka.de/'),(32,'Acrobatics Holidays in Andalucia','2013-09-01 00:00:00','2013-09-08 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','Frank and Fons leading a spectacular retreat in the south of Spain.','<div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\">Back again in the beautiful and warm September, we want to do acrobatics with a lot fun in our extraordinary location in the mediterranean mountains of southern Spain.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\">While practicing on the open stage, we can enjoy the dreamy surroundings, spectacular views, sun and amazing peace and quiet.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\">We can soak up the sun, enjoy the pool, hike to various waterfalls or explore the area on a walk through the lush green valley.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\">Fons, our famous teacher from Holland will integrate all levels in the small group.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#003366\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 11px; line-height: 20px;\">Check the official website for more info. In English and German.</span></font></div>','http://www.akro.rapidrepeat.de/index_en.html'),(17,'French Acrobatics Convention 2013','2013-07-06 00:00:00','2013-07-15 00:00:00',1,'near Bordeaux, France','<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; color: rgb(49, 50, 60); \">The France Acrobatics Convention is a great acrobatic happening with an incredible atmosphere.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; color: rgb(49, 50, 60); \">The festival is by acrobats for acrobats and blessed with a great location and famous teachers: Det&nbsp;Rijven, Wybren Wouda, Paul Griffioen, Jim Klinkhamer, An Raeymakers, Tyll and Ann, and some&nbsp;others.</p>','<div><a href=\"http://acrocalendar.com/download/French_Acrobatics_Convention_2013.pdf\" title=\"The French Convention flyer\" target=\"\">Pdf of the flyer</a>&nbsp;(german and french)</div><div><br></div>Échange international et entraînement libre, avec des ateliers d\'acrobatie à deux et&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">d\'autres disciplines de cirque, dirigés par des moniteurs professionnelles.</span><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><div>Le maximum de participants est fixé à 140 (répartis approximativement en</div><div>25 profs/cuisiniers/organisateurs, 20 aides, 80 adultes, 15 adolescents et enfants)</div></span></div>','http://www.facebook.com/events/302244019891629/?ref=ts&fref=ts'),(18,'Israel Acro Convention','2013-05-15 00:00:00','2013-05-18 00:00:00',1,'Mitzpe Ramon, Israel','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 24px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(51, 50, 51); \"></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 24px; \"></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 24px; font-family: Georgia; \">This is the 3rd year we are having this event and it will be EPIC! Our wonderful teachers<span style=\"color: #0066cc\">&nbsp;</span>from last year couldn\'t stay away and have all signed up to come again. In addition, we have some of the top teachers from around the world and from Israel.</p><p></p><p></p>','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 24px; font-size: 16px; font-family: Georgia; \">We will have a wide variety of workshops (for absolute beginners as well), music and dancing, performances, excellent food and wonderful people to play with! The beautiful landscape of the desert will be all around us as inspiration.<br>\r\nIf you are planning to attend, you should register early as places are limited and we do expect to be sold out.</p>','http://www.acrobalance.co.il'),(21,'Akrotreff am Santis','2013-03-29 00:00:00','2013-03-31 00:00:00',1,'Waldstatt, Switzerland','Acro in the beautifull town of Waldstatt north eastern Swtizerland. Only 60 places available.<br>','<div class=\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=\"field-items\"><div class=\"field-item even\"><p><strong>3. Akrobatentreffen in Waldstatt</strong><br>\r\nim Mehrzweckgebäude</p>\r\n<p>Von Karfreitag 29. März bis Ostersonntag 31. März 2013<br>\r\ntrainieren wir in der schönen Anlage mit Blick auf den Säntis.</p>\r\n<p>Workshops<br>\r\nfreies Training<br><strong>Showabend Samstag 30. März 20:15 Uhr</strong><br>\r\nFeines Essen</p>\r\n<p>Max. 60 Teilnehmer</p>\r\n</div></div></div>','www.akroamsaentis.ch'),(22,'USA - AcroYoga Level 1 Teacher Training','2013-04-19 00:00:00','2013-05-05 00:00:00',1,'Western Massachusetts','<div>with Jason Nemer, Chris Loebsack &amp; Bonnie Argo</div><div><br></div>','<br class=\"Apple-interchange-newline\">The AcroYoga Teacher Training can be one of the most exciting journeys of your life. We are honored to support you as you step into a realm of leading from your heart and true power. We feel the teacher training is truly the highest offering we can give and it requires the highest level of dedication, devotion and passion from prospective applicants.<div><br></div><div>check the home page for more details about application.</div>','http://www.acroyoga.org/teacher-training'),(23,'Spain - AcroYoga Level 1 Teacher Training','2013-07-15 00:00:00','2013-07-31 00:00:00',1,'Barcelona, Spain','Jason Nemer, Pau Castellsague &amp; Bonnie Argo','<div>The AcroYoga Teacher Training can be one of the most exciting journeys of your life. We are honored to support you as you step into a realm of leading from your heart and true power. We feel the teacher training is truly the highest offering we can give and it requires the highest level of dedication, devotion and passion from prospective applicants.</div><div><br></div><div>check the home page for more details about application.</div>','http://www.acroyoga.org/teacher-training'),(24,'Mexico - AcroYoga Level 1 Teacher Training','2013-08-30 00:00:00','2013-09-15 00:00:00',1,'Guadalajara, Mexico','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Jason Nemer, Bonnie Argo &amp; Alexandra Ruiz</span></div>','<div>The AcroYoga Teacher Training can be one of the most exciting journeys of your life. We are honored to support you as you step into a realm of leading from your heart and true power. We feel the teacher training is truly the highest offering we can give and it requires the highest level of dedication, devotion and passion from prospective applicants.</div><div><br></div><div>check the home page for more details about application.</div>','http://www.acroyoga.org/teacher-training'),(25,'Acro Yoga Montreal Teacher Training','2013-07-02 00:00:00','2013-07-28 00:00:00',1,'Montreal, Canada','<div>with Jessie Goldberg , Eugene Poku and guest teachers</div>','<div>This is a short Teacher Training Intensive, we are looking for participants that have experience in Acro Yoga so we can focus our time on sharing the art of teaching acrobatics with a yogic consciousness, moving well beyond the fundamentals. Acro Yoga is a fun filled yet serious practice with the potential to reconnect us to our inner child. The participatory, interactive and self affirming energy of the practice unites like minded people from different walks of life. It has many practical and therapeutic applications both in the Acro Yoga community and the world at large.</div><div><br></div><div>check the home page for more details about application.</div>','http://www.acroyoga.com/teacher-training-2/'),(26,'Acrotastic!','2013-04-14 00:00:00','2013-04-18 00:00:00',1,'Oakland, California ','<div><div>Acrotastic Extravaganza! Advanced Acrobatics Immersion with:</div><div>Jason &amp; Chelsey (Team YogaSlackers)</div><div>Jenny &amp; Jason (AcroYoga co-founders, San Francisco)</div><div>Lux (Seattle Acro)</div></div>','<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Come join the 3 ring circus in Oakland with some of the most active and passionate Acrobatics teachers within the realm of AcroYoga. Drawing upon the unique strengths and signature style of each team, we will share a wide variety of complimentary skills and flows, designed for the seasoned acrobat. To maximize safety and optimal learning curve, we are giving preference to participants who come in a committed acrobatic partnership in the established roles of base and flyer, which will be maintained during our time training together. It is also possible to come as a solo practitioner, and we will assign acrobatic partnerships on the first day. Get ready for a ridiculously fun and adventurous 5 days.</span><div><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></div><div><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">check the home page for more details about application.</span></font></div>','http://www.yogaslackers.com/events/acrotastic'),(27,'Acroyoga summer Camp-Out','2013-07-25 00:00:00','2013-07-28 00:00:00',1,'Portland, Oregon','3 Days of Flying, Fun, Camping, and Friends.....','<div class=\"fbInfoIcon\"><img class=\"img\" src=\"https://fbstatic-a.akamaihd.net/rsrc.php/v2/yX/r/acBKJPTD7H-.png\" title=\"Beschrijving\" height=\"16\" width=\"16\"></div><span itemprop=\"description\"><span class=\"fsl\">3 Days of Flying, Fun, Camping, and Friends.....<br> <br> Located on 80 acres of farmland just 45 minutes outside of Portland.<br> <br> This gathering will be a TON of fun and spaces are limited.<br> <br> Arrive Thursday anytime after Noon and leave Sunday by 5PM.<br> <br> You are responsible for all camping gear.<br> <br> We will provide meals from Thursday dinner to Sunday lunch.   All vegetarian.<br> <br> Kids and families welcome!  <br> <br> ONLY.......<br> <br> $175 first 10 to register<br> $195 next 15 to register<br> $220 next 25 to register<br> <br> Full Price:   $245<br> <br> Alcohol and Drug free.<br> <br> To register email:  acroyogacampout@gmail.com</span></span>','https://www.facebook.com/events/500966629935961/?ref=3'),(29,'Bosnia Convention','2013-08-19 00:00:00','2013-08-25 00:00:00',1,'Krupa, Bosnia-Herzegovina ','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; min-height: 19px;\"><font color=\"#705e4e\" face=\"Georgia\" size=\"3\">An intimate festival in an undiscovered and unspoiled corner of Europe</font></p>','<p style=\"margin: 0px; background-color: rgb(245, 244, 244);\"><font color=\"#705e4e\" face=\"Georgia\" size=\"3\">5 days of acrobatics and related disciplines under the Bosnian sun. Next to the Vrbas, our icecold and crystal clear river, hosted by the local towns people with vegetarian and locally grown- and prepared food. &nbsp;Niko Douwes, Paul Griffioen and Emilien Medial.</font></p>','http://cirkusbanjaluka.wordpress.com'),(31,'Berlin acro convention','2013-09-20 00:00:00','2013-09-22 00:00:00',1,'Berlin, Germany','13 th Berlin acro convention. Everyone can come and play in a gym in Berlin.<br><br>','<a href=\"http://www.akro-berlin.de/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">http://www.akro-berlin.de/</a><div><br></div><div>All in Berlin to do some Acro, vamos!!!</div>','http://www.akro-berlin.de/'),(30,'London Acrobatics Convention 2013','2013-08-23 00:00:00','2013-08-26 00:00:00',1,'London','London’s 1st Acrobatics Convention&nbsp;','<div>What is on offer: -&nbsp;</div><div>*four days of acrobatic fun and frolics;</div><div>*free training space with workshop options;</div><div>*includes food and limited accommodation;</div><div>*possible show if there is enough interest;</div><div>*limited to 60 participants only; and</div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">*this will cost £115 all in.</span><div><br></div><div>more info on the link above.</div>','http://www.londonacrobatics.info/'),(34,'LUENECON 2013 - Acrobatics- und Juggling Convention','2013-07-12 00:00:00','2013-07-14 00:00:00',1,'Lueneburg, Northern Germany','<br>','<div>The Convention will take place from July 12th until 14th 2013 in Lueneburg, Northern Germany.</div><div>&nbsp;We offer acrobatics and juggling workshops as well as other circus arts.&nbsp;</div><div>Sleeping in tents or indoor, vegetarian food, games and gala show on saturday night.</div>','http://luenecon2013.wordpress.com/'),(35,'Copenhagen Acro Convention','2013-09-27 00:00:00','2013-09-29 00:00:00',1,'Copenhagen, Denmark','<p style=\"border: 0px; margin: 0.75em 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: none; list-style-position: outside; float: none; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, \'Myriad Web\', Syntax, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px; \"></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\">There will be workshops and training all weekend.&nbsp;</span></p><p></p>','<p style=\"border: 0px; margin: 0.75em 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: none; list-style-position: outside; float: none; text-align: left; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, \'Myriad Web\', Syntax, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 20px; \"></p><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\">As usual food provided. Saturday there wil be a party with music, dance and maybe entertainment.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\">It will be possible to sleep in the gym, bring sleeping gear.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\">Everybody will be asked to help various task during the convention: food, cleaning, washing up, workshops. You can sign up by mail or put your name down on the dutylist upon arrival.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 9px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\">We expect to make an exchange workshop during the weekend, so please consider if there isn\'t some tricks you would like to share with the rest of us. If the possiblity arise we will have an open stage. So if you want to perform with something please send an email to <a href=\"mailto:akrokbh@akrobatik.dk\"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0px; color: rgb(38, 0, 172); \">akrokbh@akrobatik.dk</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 16px; font-size: 16px; line-height: normal; font-family: Georgia; color: rgb(49, 50, 60); min-height: 19px; \"><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px\"></span><br></p><p></p>','http://www.akrobatik.dk/cphacrofestival2013eng.html'),(36,'New Years Acro Retreat','2013-12-27 00:00:00','2014-01-02 00:00:00',1,'Nijmegen, Netherlands','Optional weekend or week long training','<div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Breakfast, lunch and diner will be taken care of, we will sleep in the gym.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">You have the choice between a long weekend from friday 27th of dec. 12:00u to monday 30th of dec. 12:00u or a whole week from friday 27th of dec. untill thursday 2nd of januari 2014.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">We\'ll be having time to do free training and have a few workshops.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">There\'ll be a lunge and we\'ll have enough mats, thick mats, long mat etc.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">On newyearseve there is, of course the possibillity to celebrate in nijmegen city, where there\'ll be a firework show or to just drink a beer or a glas of wine at the gym.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#444444\" face=\"Lucida Sans Unicode, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">The environment is also very suit to go for a hike or to cycle around to get some fresh air. Only a limited amount of people are able to join (min.25-max.40).</span></font></div>','http://acrobatiek.com/indexENG.html'),(37,'Acro, Ski & Snow Convention','2014-02-08 00:00:00','2014-02-15 00:00:00',1,'Saalbach-Hinterglemm, Austria','Daytime skiing or boarding, afternoon sauna, evening acrobatics... or whatever you prefer..','<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: separate; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica; border-spacing: 0px; font-size: medium;\"><div>Accomodation: &nbsp;</div><div>Nice renovated Farmhouse, all rooms&nbsp;with bath/toilet (single, double, 4 or 6 beds)&nbsp;Sauna, half-board from own bio-agriculture&nbsp;</div><div>5 minutes walk to the skibus-stop, 1 stop to the next skilift.</div><div>with good snowconditions its possible to ski direct to the house (for experienced)</div><div><br></div><div>Acrobatics:</div><div>we have a nice gym directly in the house (side-by-side to the sauna..)</div><div>mats are organised</div><div>workshops in different levels are planned.&nbsp;</div><div>(no acro beginners workshops so far)</div><div><br></div><div>Ski-Workshops:</div><div>- a ski-beginners course is planned (so also acrobats without ski experience may join in)</div><div>- \"Short-Workshops\" in skiing are planned (each 1x2h oder 2x2h=):</div><div>&nbsp; - carving</div><div>&nbsp; - moguls</div><div>&nbsp; - offpiste/deepsnow</div><div>&nbsp; - Ski-\"Acrobatics\" ((solo-)tricks with ski from skiacro &amp; freestyle-skiing)</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Price for the Acro-Ski-Week (Saturday dinner to saturday breakfast, 7 nights)</div><div>will be from about 369,- to 430,-, depending on how many people and your choice of room (single, double, 3-, 4-, 6-bed..)</div><div><br></div><div>! Price includes accomodation, breakfast, dinner (food from own biological farming), using the sauna, use of the gym, organisation, ski-workshops!</div><div><br></div><div>NOT included:&nbsp;</div><div>- skipass,&nbsp;</div><div>- fee for ski beginners course (we´ll see to organise this is also held by a qualified acrobat :-)</div><div>(should not be more than 50,-)</div><div>- travel</div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 0px;\"><div>If you´d like to join us,&nbsp;<b>please send me&nbsp;<u>very soon</u>&nbsp;an email</b>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:dieter@artistnet.de\">dieter@artistnet.de</a>&nbsp;and tell</div><div><br></div><div>- if you like to join and the date fits to you</div><div><br></div><div>- if you´d like to join, but its not clear at the moment, if it´s possible on this date</div><div><br></div><div>- if you cannot join this time, but love to take part next time</div><div><br></div><div>You are not enrolled by this! If everything fits, we´ll send you an email with details an bankaccount, and enrollment is confirmed when the money arrived..&nbsp;</div></span></div></span>',''),(38,'Partner Acrobatics European Intensive','2014-08-09 00:00:00','2013-08-24 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','7 or 15 day training with focus on either acrobatic or flying therapeutics. On a beautiful Organic farm in Southern Spain.','<div>The majority of the course is concurrent, however we are offering two different areas of focus.</div><div>Students will be request to apply for one of these two programs:</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Program</div><div><br></div><div>A lot of time will be dedicated to improve your personal acrobatic practice.</div><div>28.5 hours a week of practice in acrobatics.</div><div>6 hours per week will be dedicated for Therapeutics to restore your body.</div><div><br></div><div>Therapeutic Program</div><div><br></div><div>12.5 hours a week of practice in Flying Therapeutics.&nbsp;</div><div>20 of Acrobatics.</div><div><br></div>','http://www.partner-acrobatics.com/program-15.php'),(39,'Australian Partner Acro Convention','2014-02-01 00:00:00','2014-02-02 00:00:00',1,'Melbourne, Australia','This new convention calls together 4 different types of partner acrobatics together for a weekend of skill sharing, workshops and performances.&nbsp;','<div><div>Partner up!!! Join us for a weekend of partner and group acrobatics.</div></div><div><br></div><div>Including trainers from these four disciplines:</div><div>Sports acrobatics&nbsp;</div><div>Circus&nbsp;</div><div>Cheerleading</div><div>Acroyoga</div><div><br></div><div>In Melbourne, we are aiming to reduce the distance between these similar sports and hobbies to inspire new collaborations and help grow Australian acrobatics. Invite your friends! More information to come</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/168399603358707/'),(40,'AcroCamp Midwest  ','2014-07-31 00:00:00','2014-08-03 00:00:00',1,'Illinois, USA','We\'re planning it again for the third year in a row!','<div>Last year was amazing thanks to all of you who showed up to laugh, play and explore.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>This year is certainly going to be bigger and with your help even better than the last two years.</div><div><br></div><div>More details will be out later after they are all sorted</div><div><br></div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/240155386149412/'),(44,'Thailand Slackline and AcroYoga Retreat','2014-12-01 00:00:00','2014-12-08 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','Join the YogaSlackers in their first Retreat in Chiang Mai, Thailand! Redefine your known limits with Sam Salwei, Raquel Hernández and Emily Baxter','<div>This trio of modern day nomads will facilitate a 7 day exploration of your human potential.</div><div><br></div><div>Focused on the dualities a nomadic life, several acrobatic practices and active recovery, they will explore the edges of your perceived limits and will teach you how to surpass them. Through thoughtful exploration on the importance of stillness in movement, the softness found in strength and the art of silent communication, they will facilitate a personal rediscovery like no other.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>All Levels Are Welcome. No Partner Necessary.&nbsp;</div><div>All different skill levels are welcome in this retreat. We will start the 7 days of exploration teaching and reviewing the basics forms of Slackline Yoga and AcroYoga. As we progress through the week we will add more challenges suitable to each individual. We promise you will not feel too new or too experienced to truly enjoy it! You don\'t need a partner, but we\'ll honor people wanting to work with one. This is your retreat. You are welcome to participate in as much or as little in the organized activities as you\'d like.</div><div><br></div><div>ACTIVITIES INCLUDE:</div><div>Morning Yoga Practice</div><div>Slackline Yoga</div><div>AcroYoga</div><div>Slackro</div><div>Partner Acrobatics</div><div>Pool Acrobatics</div><div>Thai Massage and Flying Therapeutics</div><div>Games and Fun Challenges</div><div><br></div><div>INCLUDED AMENITIES:</div><div>7 Night Stay at Kaomai Lanna Resort in Shared Room</div><div>www.kaomailanna.com</div><div>3 Meals per day</div><div>1 Private Thai Massage</div><div>1 Group Excursion</div><div>Transportation from the Chiang Mai Airport</div><div><br></div><div>TEACHING TEAM</div><div>Sam Salwei &amp; Raquel Hernandez-Cruz have infectious drives, and are known for bringing their students to their edges and beyond. As modern day nomads, you can find them driving coast to coast in their \"PeaceLoveCar\", or hopping on a plane to teach overseas. Sam is the co-founder of the YogaSlackers, and has a great deal of knowledge and experience on the slackline, creating amazing spectacles wherever he goes. Raquel\'s extensive training in all different types of yoga, AcroYoga, slacklining, and listening, makes her a motivating and receptive teacher, great at progressing her students further. With their many combined talents and skills, these two always have something new and exciting to share and together, make the perfect teaching team.</div><div><br></div><div>Emily Baxter is dedicated to sharing and teaching whatever she can to inspire freedom in people. A bit of a jack of all trades, she teaches and practices several styles of Yoga asana, including Hatha, Yin, Vinyasa as well as AcroYoga and Slackline Yoga. She teaches anatomy, methodology and adjustments on various Yoga Teacher Trainings and runs her own Yin Yoga Teacher Training programs as well as Partner Acrobatics Intensives and Teacher Trainings. She is also trained as a Postural Therapist. Emily has always had a passion for movement and body awareness. This coupled with her strong background in anatomy manifests in her teachings as clear, precise, thoughtful instruction. She continues to study, travel, teach, play and laugh wherever she may find herself.</div><div><br></div><div>SAMPLE DAY</div><div>7:00 AM Yoga</div><div>8:30 AM Breakfast</div><div>9:30 AM Slackline/AcroYoga</div><div>12:00 PM Lunch Break</div><div>3:00 PM AcroYoga/Slackline</div><div>5:00 PM Conditioning/Acrobatics</div><div>6:00 PM Dinner</div><div>8:00 PM Therapeutics</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>PLANNING &amp; GETTING TO THAILAND</div><div>We recommend you to enjoy Chiang Mai for few days before the training and possibly stay longer afterwards. Most countries automatically receive 30 days upon arrival.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>MORE INFORMATION AND RESERVATIONS</div><div>$1,000USD Before August 1st 2014</div><div>$1,300USD After</div><div><br></div><div>~~~~All teachers receive 20% discount.~~~~</div><div>~~~~ Even on the Early Bird.~~~~</div><div><br></div><div>For More Information Contact Sanjivni.om@gmail.com&nbsp;</div><div>To Register Simply Send us a check to:</div><div><br></div><div>YogaSlackers</div><div>Att: Thailand Retreat.</div><div>1600 E Old Shakopee Rd</div><div>Bloomington, MN 55425-2443</div><div>United States</div><div><br></div><div>After receiving your payment, we will send a welcome letter with more information about the retreat, traveling and lodging.</div><div><br></div><div>(We will add a brown paper link to this event soon. But a check will save you money in processing fees.)</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/641629412542071/'),(45,'AcroYoga Festival','2014-10-10 00:00:00','2014-10-12 00:00:00',1,'Portland, Oregon, USA','\"The Divine Play\"','<div>Divine Play is an annual family gathering of hundreds of yogis, acrobats, massage therapists, athletes, students and master teachers hosted by AcroYoga. It is three full days of intense practice, play, kirtan, celebration, performances, and in depth exploration of yoga, acrobatics &amp; healing arts by those who are cutting edge in the field of health and wellness.</div><div><br></div><div>check the Divine Play homepage.</div>','http://www.acroyoga.org/acroyogafestival/about'),(47,'Partner Acrobatics & Flying Therapeutics Teacher Training','2015-01-03 00:00:00','2015-01-31 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','A Teacher Training in Partner Acrobatics where you can intensively train for 4 weeks. Optional program to become a practitioner in Flying Therapeutics.','<div>The majority of the course is concurrent, however we are offering two different areas of focus.</div><div>Students will be request to apply for one of these two programs:</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Program</div><div>Therapeutic Program</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Program</div><div>This program will give you the skills to teach Partner Acrobatics classes and workshops.</div><div>Moreover plenty of time will be dedicated to improve your personal acrobatic practice.</div><div>Specific time will be dedicated to prepare public performances and work on the aesthetics of your acro moves.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Therapeutic Program</div><div>This program will enable you to become a Flying Therapeutics practitioner as well as Partner Acrobatics teacher.</div><div>The focus will be on refining skills as a bodyworker and creating your own therapeutic flow in a secure manner.</div><div><br></div><div>Please visit our website for more info &nbsp;&nbsp;www.partner-acrobatics.com</div>','www.partner-acrobatics.com'),(46,'Akrobatikurlaub in Andalucia  with  Fons','2014-07-12 00:00:00','2014-01-19 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','<div>12th Acrobatics and Holiday workshop in Andalusia with Fons.</div>','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Once more in July we want to do acrobatics with a lot fun in our extraordinary location in the mediterranean mountains of southern Spain.</span></div><div><br></div><div>While practicing on the open stage, we can enjoy the dreamy surroundings, spectacular views, sun and amazing peace and quiet.</div><div><br></div><div>We can soak up the sun, enjoy the pool, hike to various waterfalls or explore the area on a walk through the lush green valley.</div><div><br></div><div>Fons, our famous teacher from Holland will integrate all levels in the small group.</div>','http://www.akro.rapidrepeat.de/'),(49,'Acro Revolution Teacher Training','2014-06-01 00:00:00','2014-06-15 00:00:00',1,'Virginia, USA','Acro Revolution TT teaches acrobats to train intelligently, embody the practice, teach the practice, and have the tools to succeed as an acro teacher in their community.','<div>Acro Revolution TT is a 2 week residential training focused on the art of being a mindful acrobat. The training will consist of intensive instruction in L-base acrobatics with a focus on skills including; washing machines, foot to hand, hand to hand, whips, pops, and other circus monkey tricks. In addition to learning techniques to fully embody this practice, you will learn how to teach basic partner acrobatics.. Restorative practices including; yoga, massage, and meditation will be incorporated to create a more sustainable acrobatic practice and to help facilitate connection and community. This training will break down the ‘business’ of being an acro teacher, and will teach students techniques for sustainability and success. Sam, Dan, and Raquel of YogaSlackers will be there to help us explore the fundamentals of a Slackline practice and learn how to use each other and the line to redefine our perception of balance.</div><div>All material presented will be taught by using progressions and method based teaching practices. You will come out of this training equipped to not only teach acrobatics, but with the knowledge to train intelligently, heal yourself, and support your community.</div><div>OUR GOALS</div><div>The top 3 goals for the student are;</div><div>1) to be able to teach L- base acro</div><div>2) to have the tools and knowledge to have a sustainable teaching practice</div><div>3) to embody a practice based on safety and healthy communication</div><div><br></div>','http://acropedia.org/acro-teacher-training/'),(48,'Acro Yoga Teacher Training','2014-07-01 00:00:00','2014-07-27 00:00:00',1,'Montreal, Canada','We are looking for participants that have experience in Acro Yoga so we can focus our time on sharing the art of teaching acrobatics with a yogic consciousness, moving well beyond the fundamentals.&nbsp;','<div>Acro Yoga is a fun filled yet serious practice with the potential to reconnect us to our inner child. The participatory, interactive and self-affirming energy of the Acro Yoga practice unites likeminded people from different walks of life. It has many practical and therapeutic applications both in the Acro Yoga community and the world at large.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Yoga’s potential for dealing and helping people cope with trust issues is boundless since the root of the Acro Yoga practice is trust and acceptance. Acro yoga cannot exist without this bond and understanding between practitioners. As Acro Yoga teachers we must be present, to ensure a safe and nurturing environment for our Acro Yoga students.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The mastery of the technique in our own Acro Yoga practice is the foundation we draw on for teaching Acro Yoga. How to communicate verbally and physically to our students the inner &amp;outer experience are the skills we will explore in this Acro Yoga Teacher Training Intensive.</div><div><br></div><div>Upcoming Training Sessions: 2014</div><div>July 1- 27, 2104&nbsp;</div><div>The art of teaching acroyoga with Jessie Goldberg, Eugene Poku and guest teachers.&nbsp;</div><div>4 weeks of physical reintegration, mental sharpening, emotional awakening and remembered wisdom.</div><div>Come back to the source, Montréal the birth place of acroyoga.</div><div><br></div><div>Level 1 only: July 1 - 13, 2014 Cost: $1600 (tax in) Acro Yoga manual included</div><div><br></div><div>Level 2 only: July 15 - 27, 2014 Cost: $1600 (tax in) Acro Yoga manual included</div><div><br></div><div>Discount for Level 1 &amp; 2: July 1 - 27, 2014 &nbsp; Cost: $2600 (tax in) Acro Yoga manual included</div><div><br></div>','http://acroyoga.com/teacher-training/1'),(50,'Israel Acro Convention','2014-06-04 00:00:00','2014-06-07 00:00:00',1,'Israel','The conference program and details will be published later','<br>','http://www.acrobalance.co.il/???-??????????-???????-2014-2/'),(51,'Nordic AcroYoga Festival','2014-06-26 00:00:00','2014-06-29 00:00:00',1,'Mundekulla, Sweden','There will be workshops for both beginners and experienced. All are welcome. Come and share four days full of amazing festival atmosphere in beautiful surroundings. This is an alcohol and drug free event. Chocolate and cookies are welcome !','<div>AcroBhakti invites to AcroYoga Festival at wonderful Mundekulla eco-retreat center in the forest of southern Sweden. AcroYoga blends the wisdom of yoga, the dynamic power of acrobatics and the loving kindness of healing arts. These three lineages form the foundation of a practice that cultivates trust, playfulness and community.</div><div><br></div><div>There will be workshops for both beginners and experienced. All are welcome. Come and share four days full of amazing festival atmosphere in beautiful surroundings. This is an alcohol and drug free event. Chocolate and cookies are welcome !</div><div><br></div><div>\"AcroYoga is a community based practice. We ignite our collective potential as we support each other to reach new heights. AcroYoga invites you to experience the full spectrum of your being through opportunities to: give and receive; to support and to be supported; to be strong and sensitive. It is a systematic approach designed to be accessible to every practitioner, and encourages personal transformation in an atmosphere of acceptance, celebration and safety.\"&nbsp;</div><div>www.AcroYoga.org</div><div><br></div><div>FOR SWEDISH VERSION:&nbsp;</div><div>http://www.acrobhakti.com/p/acroyogafestival.html?lng=swe</div><div><br></div><div>• The Place •</div><div>Mundekulla is located in the southeastern forest of Sweden. A place for stillness, creativity and encounters, with beautiful surroundings. The whole facility is constructed and run environmentally friendly.</div><div>Mundekulla</div><div>Kurs- &amp; Retreatgård</div><div>361 95 Långasjö</div><div>www.mundekulla.se</div><div><br></div><div>• Getting to the festival •</div><div>It\'s easy to get to Mundekulla. On their website, they have several tips for your trip:</div><div>www.mundekulla.se/mundekulla/parse.php?p=location_eng.html</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>+++ Program +++</div><div>Thursday</div><div>16:00 Arrival</div><div>18:30-19.15 Dinner</div><div>20:00-22:30 Opening Circle</div><div><br></div><div>Friday, Saturday</div><div>07:00-08:30 Morning yoga</div><div>08:30-09.15 Breakfast</div><div>10:00-12:30 Workshop: acroyoga, yoga, thai massage, dance</div><div>13:00-13.45 Lunch</div><div>15:00-17:00 Workshop: acroyoga, yoga, thai massage, dance</div><div>17:00-18:30 Jam (open training) or Sauna in Mundekullas woodheated sauna</div><div>18:30-19.15 Dinner</div><div>20:30-22:30 Evening program: party with mantras singing, dancing, music, open stage</div><div><br></div><div>Söndag</div><div>07:00-08:30 Morning yoga</div><div>08:30-09.15 Breakfast</div><div>10:00-12:30 Workshop: acroyoga, yoga, thai massage, dance</div><div>13:00-13.45 Lunch</div><div>14:30-16:00 Closing circle</div><div>(Subject to change)</div><div><br></div><div>• Teachers •</div><div>www.acrobhakti.com/p/acroyogafestival.html?lng=eng#teachers</div><div><br></div><div>• Festival Ticket •</div><div>The festival ticket includes camping space and organic vegetarian food.</div><div>• Early Bird 1 (before February 18): 2700 SEK</div><div>• Early Bird 2 (before April 22): 3000 SEK</div><div>• Regular (after April 22): 3400 SEK</div><div><br></div><div>• Housing •</div><div>If you want to stay indoors in a dormitory or a private room during the festival, you can book it. The number of rooms is limited so book early to secure yours.</div><div><br></div><div>Prices per person for housing during the festival:</div><div>+ 0 SEK camp space (bring your own camping equipment)</div><div>+ 300 SEK dormitory (mattress+pillow+blanket+privacy curtain)</div><div>+ 300 SEK caravan or car place incl. electricity</div><div>+ 450 SEK space in 4-bed room with private shower and toilet &gt;&gt; FULLY BOOKED ! &lt;&lt;</div><div>+ 600 SEK space in double room with shower and toilet in the corridor</div><div>+ 1050 SEK space in double room with private shower and toilet</div><div>+ 1500 SEK space in single room with private shower and toilet&nbsp;</div><div>*(dorms are not heated but works well in the summer)</div><div><br></div><div>• Questions •</div><div>Send an email to Nina &amp; Boris:</div><div>info@acrobhakti.com</div><div><br></div><div>• Sign Up •</div><div>www.acrobhakti.com/p/sign-up-festival.html</div><div><br></div><div>• Read More •</div><div>http://www.acrobhakti.com/p/acroyogafestival.html?lng=eng</div><div><br></div><div>• Organizer •</div><div>The festival is arranged by AcroBhakti in collaboration with Mundekulla.</div><div><br></div><div>♡&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>','http://www.acrobhakti.com/p/acroyogafestival.html?lng=eng'),(52,'French Acrobatics Convention ','2014-07-05 00:00:00','2014-07-14 00:00:00',1,'Ste Eulalie en Born, France','International exchange and free training, as well as workshops with international teachers, mostly in partner-acrobatics, but also in other circus disciplines','<div>For whom:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> All interested adult acrobats, as well as children</div><div>and adolescents.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Costs:</div><div>For \"normal\" participants</div><div>€440 per adult (beginning by 16 years) inclusive of food,</div><div>workshops and camping in own tent.</div><div>€315 for persons between 10 and 15 years old&nbsp;</div><div>€170 for persons up to 9 years old&nbsp;</div><div>€ 65 per day (flat-rate €25, meals €20 and workshops €20)</div><div><br></div><div>For \"helpers\"* (from 18 years old)</div><div>€220 *they has to do 7 jobs during the festival</div><div><br></div><div>A short notice:</div><div>We see ourselves as friends amongst friends who are glad to organise an event, but also naturally expect everyone to help with the everyday chores (especially as we are not planning to make any money from the meeting). As most of the work during the meeting will consist of doing the shopping, cooking, ferrying people, etc., we wish to spread these tasks evenly amongst the participants. In practice, this means that everyone over 15 years old will be asked to help with food preparation or with washing up two times during the meeting. In our experience, work in the kitchen was always a very fun and communicative experience, so many people will probably want to help more than their share…!</div><div><br></div><div>Inscription:<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> Per email at thorsten.bohle@gmx.de</div><div>You will then receive a confirmation with the</div><div>details for payment.</div><div><br></div><div>We have invited professional teachers to the festival, who will organise the daily workshops, at different levels.</div><div>The main orientation of the workshops will again be partner acrobatics; but we will also plan workshops in other circus disciplines, such as silks, dance-acrobatics and Thai massage.</div><div><br></div><div>Provisional daily planning of the acrobatics convention:&nbsp;</div><div>The schedule below is subject to change. It will be adapted to the conditions, the requirements of the&nbsp;</div><div>workshop leaders and the interests of the participants.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>8:00 - 9:00<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Yoga&nbsp;</div><div>8:30 - 10:00<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Breakfast&nbsp;</div><div>9:30 - 10:00<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Warming Up&nbsp;</div><div>10:00 - 10:30<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Handstands&nbsp;</div><div>10:45 - 12:15<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>1. Workshop-Bloc (ap. 4 parallel offers at</div><div>different levels)</div><div>12:15 - 13:45<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>free training with 2 teachers as contact</div><div>13:45 - 15:00<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Lunch/Buffet&nbsp;</div><div>15:00 - 16:30<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Midday-Break&nbsp;</div><div>16:45 - 18:45<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>2. Workshop-Bloc (ap. 4 parallel offers at</div><div>different levels)</div><div>19:00 - 20:15 warm dinner</div><div>20:15 - 21:15<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Thai massage-Workshop</div><div><br></div><div>We have planned again a canoeing day this year.&nbsp;</div><div>What\'s more, we will again spend a day at the seaside, with buffet and romantic sunset.</div><div>An open stage (probably on July 12th ) is planned at the end of the week.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/509790922472969/?ref_newsfeed_story_type=regular&source=1'),(53,'Extreme Convention','2014-04-18 00:00:00','2014-04-20 00:00:00',1,'Antwerp, Belgium','The biggest EXTREME acrobatics and circus convention in Belgium, the BeNeLux and probably in Europe or even the world (and if we\'re not the biggest, then we sure are the best! ;-) (Yes, it\'s true what they say about Antwerp and ego)','<div>When: 18 - 20 april 2014</div><div>Where: Waagnatie, Hanger 29, Antwerpen.</div><div>What: Really? You don\'t know Extreme Convention?</div><div><br></div><div>We\'re transforming a big, empty event hall into a big, crowded acrobatics and training hall.</div><div><br></div><div>More info to be announced soon. We\'ll keep you posted.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/684266544958435/'),(54,'Danish Acro Convention','2014-07-05 00:00:00','2014-07-13 00:00:00',1,'Aalborg, Denmark','<div>Six full days of training with seven workshops a day, five workshops in acrobatics and 2 in other new-circus skills (aerial, slackline, ect.) There will be plenty of time and space for free training</div><div><br></div>','<div>Following the success of the IAC 2012 in Aalborg, Denmark, we are now, after a one years intermission, ready to do it again. This time it is called the DAC and we hope it will be the first of many conventions in Denmark.</div><div><br></div><div>The convention will be held in the same spirit as the IAC, this means that we are going to use the same great venue. The sports science school. Accommodation will be in their small apartments. All the great food will be prepared by the schools kitchen, this means even more time for training as there will be no chores.</div><div><br></div><div>The gym is specially fitted for athletic gymnastics and located within a 100 m of the sports science school. The venue is located in the heart of Aalborg and we consi- der this convention a great way to have a holiday in the beautiful city of Aalborg with a lot of acrobatics and the possibility to see Denmark and Aalborg.</div><div><br></div><div>There will be a relaxation day half way through the convention with a free trip to the local health spa, where we can play in the big pool or relax in the wellness department. (wellness is only allowed from 18 years old)</div><div>Great food, made by the sport school’s kitchen, they normally cook for athletes so there will be plenty of food for both vegetarians and meat eaters.</div><div><br></div><div>Daily program &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">07.30 - 08.00&nbsp;</span>yoga</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">08.30 - 09.30&nbsp;</span>Breakfast</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">10.00 - 11.30&nbsp;</span>Workshops (2 + Bonus)&nbsp;</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">12.00 - 13.00&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Lunch</span></div><div>14.30 - 16.00 &nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Workshops (2 + Bonus) &nbsp;</span></div><div>16.00 - 17.30&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Longe + all level Workshop</span></div><div>&nbsp;18.00 - 19.00&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Dinner</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">19.30 - 20.00</span>Joga/streaching</div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">20.00 - 22.00&nbsp;</span>Free training Space</div><div><br></div><div>400Euro and more info soon!</div><div><br></div><div>Contact - DAC.DGI@gmail.com - www.dgi.dk/nordjylland/gymnastik</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/611604298878192/'),(55,'Move Copenhagen','2014-06-20 00:00:00','2014-06-22 00:00:00',1,'Copenhagen, Denmark','A new international community driven movement festival – the focus is diverse, playful and creative movement.','<div>We seek to challenge these enthusiasts with a great versatility of movement and unique experiences from several movement communities. We want to test, develop and expand the boundaries of what can be achieved within each different movement community.</div><div>An old shipyard in Copenhagen provides an urban setting for Copenhagen’s new festival of movement. We want to create a unique opportunity for the movement of slackline, climbing and bouldering, yoga and acroyoga, dance and parkour. We invite you to join this extraordinary experience together with 400 other movement enthusiasts from many countries.</div><div>Move Copenhagen is for anyone who wants to offer themself a physical challenge within their own practiced disciplines, as well as the challenge of trying a new field of motion exercise and ability. The old shipyard on Refshaleøen has come to life with a bold, raw and urban atmosphere. This area facilitates the activities and challenges you to move within, around and on top of the old towering industrial buildings.</div><div>Participants at Move Copenhagen get the opportunity to become familiar to the cultures of the various communities. Move Copenhagen is trying to strengthen each community by offering a perfect setting in which the community can grow, while empowering the movement communities through one another.</div><div><br></div><div>Tickets and more info on the website:)</div>','http://movecopenhagen.com'),(56,'IAC','2014-08-22 00:00:00','2014-08-29 00:00:00',1,'Hungary','The 2014 International Acrobatics Convention (IAC)<div><br></div>','The 2014 International Acrobatics Convention (IAC) is taking place in Hungary, 22 aug to 29th aug it\'s gonna be camping, 99% sunshine an 100% acrobatics.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>LINK: <a href=\"http://acrobatics.nl/\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">acrobatics.nl</a> for info and registration</div>','http://acrobatics.nl/'),(57,'AkroYoga  & FlowYoga Celebration','2014-05-15 00:00:00','2014-05-18 00:00:00',1,'Ludersdorf, Austria','With Andreas, Juliane, Gabriel, Mito &amp; Rafaela','<div>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K1jkUj327NM&amp;feature=youtu.be</div><div><br></div><div>EVENT INFO:</div><div><br></div><div>AkroYoga &amp; FlowYoga Celebration</div><div>4 Tage pure Lebensfreude und Körperwahrnehmung&nbsp;</div><div>Mit Andreas, Juliane, Gabriel, Mito &amp; Rafaela</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>In 16 abgestimmten und ineinander fließenden Einheiten bieten Gabriel, Mito, Juliane und Andreas ein vielfältiges Angebot aus AkroYoga, Flow Yoga und Thai Yoga Massage. Der Schwerpunkt dieses verlängerten Wochenendes liegt darauf, die Welt des Up-side-downs näher kennen zu lernen und die Kunst des Flows darin verschmelzen zu lassen. Dieses einmalige Event findet im Schloss Freiberg bei Gleisdorf statt. Mitten in der Natur umgeben von Wald und Wiese haben wir für euch den Festsaal des Schlosses gemietet, wo wir täglich gemeinsam mehrere Stunden bewusst praktizieren. In diesen vier Tagen wird jedem/r Teilnehmer/in egal ob beginner oder erfahren das nötige Know-How geboten um das volle Potential einer spielerisch bewussten Praxis zu entfalten. Verfeinert durch Begleitmusik, Tanz, verschiedenen Partner Yoga Übungen und Aspekten aus Akrobatik und Flow Yoga wollen wir die spielerische Seite des Lebens wieder erwecken und mit euch ein Wochenende voller Freude und Community Spirit zelebrieren.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>ZUM TEAM:</div><div><br></div><div>AkroYoga mit Gabriel &amp; Mito:</div><div>Präzise und detailliert, mit Humor und voller Energie führen dich Gabriel und Mito durch die Welten der AkroYoga Praxis. Auf einzigartige Art und Weise bringen sie die Gruppe zusammen und erwecken die spielerische Seite in jedem/jeder Einzelnen/r. Open mind. Open Heart. Open Level.</div><div><br></div><div>Flow Yoga mit Andreas &amp; Juliane:</div><div>Achtsam und bewusst bereiten Juliane und Andi deinen Körper optimal auf das Fliegen vor. Sie unterrichten mal dynamisch-kraftvolles, mal fließend-weiches und tänzerisches Yoga.</div><div><br></div><div>Flying Bodyworks &amp; Thai Massage mit Gabriel &amp; Rafaela:</div><div>In einer Flying Bodyworks Einheit lernen wir den Empfänger in der Luft sowie am Boden passiv und sanft in verschiedene Yogahaltungen zu führen. Wir unterstützen den Körper muskuläre Verspannungen sowie Blockaden in Gelenken und der Wirbelsäule zu lösen, um rufen ein ganzheitliches Entspannungserlebnis herbei. - Eine perfekte Gelegenheit abzuschalten und einen Tag voller intensiver Praxis abzurunden!</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>TAGESABLAUF:</div><div>08:30 - 10:00 Flow Yoga</div><div>10:00 - 11:00 AkroYoga</div><div>11:00 - 12:00 Freier Jam (Yoga, AkroYoga, Musik)</div><div>12:00 - 15:00 Mittagspause &amp; Essen</div><div>15:00 - 16:00 Flow Yoga</div><div>16:00 - 17:00 AkroYoga</div><div>17:00 - 18:00 Flying Bodyworks &amp; Thai Massage</div><div>18:00 - 19:00 Abendessen</div><div>19:00 - open End (Dance Party, Konzert, Freier Jam)</div><div><br></div><div>Ende am Sonntag bis ca. 15 Uhr!</div><div><br></div><div>Info: In den freien Jam Zeiten hast du die Möglichkeiten die zuvor geübten Flows zu wiederholen, mit Lehrern und anderen dich auszutauschen, an Tricks zu tüfteln, Musik zu spielen, zu tanzen oder einfach nur die Seele baumeln zu lassen...</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>BUFFET: (10,- Euro pro 3-gängiger Mahlzeit)</div><div><br></div><div>Täglich gibt es zwei vegane Buffets (mittags und abends) mit Suppe oder Salat, Hauptgericht und Dessert/Kuchen von unserem veganen Koch Tobias Scheuer. Bitte melde dich rechtzeitig im Vorhinein bei uns, damit wir genug Essen für alle haben. Um den Community Geist auch in den Pausen aufrecht zu erhalten würden wir uns freuen mit dir gemeinsam zu essen.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>ÜBERNACHTEN IM SCHLOSS: (For free)</div><div><br></div><div>Es besteht die Möglichkeit die ganzen 4 Tage bei uns im Schloss zu nächtigen - der Schlossgeist ist gerade auf Urlaub ;-) Dafür kannst entweder mit Zelt im Garten Campen oder in einem unserer Festsäle nächtigen. Dafür brauchst du einen Schlafsack und eine Isomatte oder aufblasbare Luftmatratze und gegebenen Falls ein Zelt. Sanitär Anlagen (Klos) sind im Schloss vorhanden und Duschen gibt es im Garten. Auch darüber bitten wir dich uns bei deiner Anmeldung zu informieren.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>SPECIALS:</div><div><br></div><div>!!!DanceParty!!! Am Freitag den 16.5. zelebrieren wir den Beginn des Wochenendes und füllen den Abend mit guter Musik, DJs und schwingen gemeinsam die Hufe. Kosten: For Free / Start: 18:30</div><div><br></div><div>!!!Konzert!!! Am Samstag den 17.5. wird uns Babek Bodien mit seiner Stimme verzaubern und ein Konzert der Extraklasse geben. Kosten: 15,- Euro VKK / 20,- Euro ABK / Start: 19:00</div><div><br></div><div>Zur Person:&nbsp;</div><div>Babek Bodiens deutsch- und englischsprachigen Songs sprechen von Herz zu Herz, mit lichtvollen Lyrics und meditativen Melodien, berührend in ihrer Natürlichkeit und wurzelnd im Wesentlichen. Eingängig und exotisch zugleich verbinden sich Liedermacherpop und Reggae mit Elementen schamanischer und spiritueller Musik verschiedener Traditionen. Dabei kommen, neben der liedbegleitenden Gitarre, auch archaische Instrumente wie Didgeridoo, indianische Flöten und Trommeln zum Tragen, was der Musik zusätzlich eine besondere Note verleiht. Live, mit GastmusikerInnen oder Solo, lädt der Songwriter dazu ein nach Innen zu spüren und sich von der Lebendigkeit des Moments bewegen zu lassen – in stiller Besinnlichkeit oder auch mitsingend und tanzend.</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>KOSTEN:</div><div><br></div><div>EARLY BIRD PRICE: (bis 1. APRIL)</div><div>**4 TAGES CELEBRATION PASS: 240,- Euro</div><div>**2 TAGE (Samstag und Sonntag): 145,- Euro</div><div><br></div><div>LATE BIRD PRICE: (nach 1. APRIL)</div><div>**4 TAGES CELEBRATION PASS: 280,- Euro</div><div>**2 TAGE (Samstag und Sonntag): 170,- Euro</div><div><br></div><div>ANMELDUNG UNTER:</div><div>http://mangalam-yoga.com/anmeldung.html</div><div><br></div><div>Info zur Platzreservierung:</div><div>Sobald deine Überweisung auf dem Celebration Konto eingelangt ist, hast du eine gesicherte Platzreservierung. Falls Du nach Deiner Überweisung absagen müsstest (Krankheit, etc.) bekommst Du für den eingezahlten Betrag einen Gutschein für das nächste von uns angebotene AcroFlowYogaEvent!</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>LOCATION &amp; ANFAHRT:</div><div><br></div><div>Ihr findet das Yoga Mangalam im schönen</div><div>Schloss Freiberg</div><div>Ludersdorf 30</div><div>8200 Ludersdorf</div><div><br></div><div>rechter Aufgang, 2. Stock rechts</div><div><br></div><div>Telefon: +43 3112 27 202 / mobil: +43 699 18 29 5777</div><div><br></div><div>von Graz: A2 Richtung Wien, Abfahrt Gleisdorf-West, linker Abzweig Richtung Ludersdorf, im Kreisverkehr rechts Richtung Ludersdorf, am Ortsende links Richtung Gut/Golfplatz Freiberg, 2km dem Straßenverlauf folgen, der Gästeparkplatz befindet sich unten links.</div><div><br></div><div>von Wien: A23/A2 Richtung Graz, Abfahrt Gleisdorf-West, linker Abzweig Richtung Ludersdorf, im Kreisverkehr rechts Richtung Ludersdorf, am Ortsende links Richtung Gut/Golfplatz Freiberg, 2km dem Straßenverlauf folgen, der Gästeparkplatz befindet sich unten links.</div><div><br></div><div>********************************************</div><div>LINKS:</div><div><br></div><div>www.mangalam-yoga.com</div><div>www.barefootyoga.me</div><div>www.babekbodien.com</div>','h