r=\"#4e5665\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;\">The Preconvention is a unique event right before the Dutch Acro Festival, where you can raise your acrobatic skills in a small Group.</span></font></div>Training with Fons Bennink, Wybren Wouda, Hugo Hansen, Emily Baxter, Bart and Kirsty, Noël Spauwen and Niko Douwes.<br>Acro, Food, Yoga Camping, Sauna and More Acro!!<br>','https://www.facebook.com/Preconvention-to-the-Dutch-Acrobatics-Festival-624309611028414/?fref=ts'),(64,'Dutch Acro','2015-05-22 17:00:00','2015-05-25 14:00:00',1,'Netherlands','The biggest acroconvention in the world- come join the party','Info will be updated when more info comes out. &nbsp;The word is that it will be in the city of Sittard but it is is not sure yet.<br>','http://www.akrobatiek.nl/home.php'),(65,'acrokopenhagen','2014-09-26 17:00:00','2014-09-28 15:00:00',1,'Remisen, Enghavevej 82B, Copenhagen SV ','Acrobatic Convention in Copenhagen from Septemper 26-28.','<p>Prices:</p>\r\n<p>Grownups 400,- dkr.<br>\r\nYoung (age 6-14): Half price.<br>\r\nChildren (under 5): Free<br>\r\nChildren og youg under 15 must be in company with a grownup responsible</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The bar is open Friday and Saturday evening. Remember to bring cash.</p>\r\n<p>The registration is open.<br>\r\nRegistration:<br>\r\nSend an email to akrokbh@akrobatik.dk with the following information: \r\nName, Address, Tlf, email, birthday. Whether your are an vegetarian. If \r\nyou would like to give a workshop.<br>\r\nYou transfer the money to account 2104-6446 120 490 (remember your name).<br>\r\nIf your are coming from abroad and you tell in your registration you can pay on arrival.</p>','http://www.akrobatik.dk/acrocph/'),(66,'Bosnian acroconvention','2014-08-11 00:00:00','2014-08-17 00:00:00',1,'Krupa on the Vrbas river in Bosnia Herzegovinja','Same site, same crew, same Vrbas, NEW summer! The fourth acroconvention in Bosnia and Herzegovina!','Participants from ex-Yu can pay the reduced fee of €90 if they need to, for other nationalities its €175 for Monday-Sunday.<br>\r\nThe fee includes three vegetarian meals per day, the campsite and all-access to the Vrbas.','http://cirkusbanjaluka.wordpress.com/'),(67,'IAC-International Acrobatics Convention','2015-07-13 00:00:00','2015-07-19 00:00:00',1,'Jyväskylä, Finland','The purpose of the festival is to help the sport of acrobatics to spread throughout the world','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">The way we do this by holding a convention of somewhere between 100 and 200 people. We started in Croatia, and went via France and Sweden to Denmark and Italy. We are moving the festival from country to country every year. This is to make sure every acrobat gets to have a change to participate without having to travel half the world. Of course it\'s also nice to go to unknown places that are touristic or otherwise interesting to make a longer stay possible. Meanwhile we hope our influence on the local acrobatic-scene is big enough to make a prolongation possible for a local festival.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\"><br></span></div><div>The 8th and next, 2015 Convention will be held in Finland, at the Circus school of Jyväskylä</div>','http://www.acrobatics.nl'),(68,'Partner Acrobatics Teacher Training in Mexico','2015-09-20 00:00:00','2015-10-18 00:00:00',1,'Chalananda, Mexico','First Teacher Training of Partner Acrobatics in North America. Pure fun with Niko, Emily and Lorenzo!!!','EN: Program in English and Spanish.<div>ES: El programa será en Castellano y Ingles.</div><div><br>This program will give you the skills to teach Partner Acrobatics classes and workshops. Moreover plenty of time will be dedicated to improve your personal acrobatic practice. Specific time will be dedicated to prepare public performances and work on the aesthetics of your acro moves. 6 hours per week will be dedicated for Therapeutics to restore your body.<div><br></div><div>Check the video introduction:</div><div><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JzsYwYsl5Hk\" title=\"Intrducing Partner Acro Teacher Training\" target=\"\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JzsYwYsl5Hk</a></div></div>','http://www.partner-acrobatics.com/program-am.php'),(69,'Partner Acrobatics European Intensive in Spain','2015-08-08 00:00:00','2015-08-22 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','1 or 2 weeks of pure fun and acro practice with Niko, Emily and Lorenzo. In the beautiful location between the mountains of the south of Spain.','A lot of time to dedicate to your personal acro practice and share with many other peeps.<div>Niko leads the acro program and it´s plenty of challenging and amusing tricks.</div><div><br></div><div>The place is in the mountain with a nice temperate both at night and during the day.&nbsp;</div><div>Food is mostly coming from the organic farm where we are hosted.</div>','http://www.partner-acrobatics.com/program-15.php'),(70,'Acro Kiel','2015-03-13 00:00:00','2015-03-15 00:00:00',1,'Kiel, Germany','A Typical hardcore German Acro festival with about 250 participants.','<div><br></div><div>Registration open until 2.3.2015, after that add 5 € \"panic fee\";&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>If you come unregistered, you can\'t get food (because this is ordered by number in advance) and may be not even participate, if the maximum number of particitiants is reached.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>You will receive an email confirmation.</div><div><br></div><div>Friday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> 17-22 o\'clock acrobatics.</div><div>Saturday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> 9-19 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet, vegettarian/non-vegetarian dinner buffet, show and Party.</div><div>Sunday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> 9-15 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet.</div><div><br></div><div>Cost—People less than 6 years: free, people between 6 and 16 years (excl.): 30 €, older people: 55 €, if you don\'t mind, you are welcome to pay a little extra, to sponsor the kids fee (that does not match the costs).</div><div><br></div><div>Payment<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> We are sending the account information with the confirmation eMail, provide the names of all people you are paying for.</div><div><br></div><div>Location——Sports Center of the Christian-Albrecht-University Kiel, Olshausenstrasse 74, Kiel.</div><div><br></div><div>Maximum number of participiants<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span> This year, the maximum number of participiants (250) might be exceeded</div>','http://tiroqrgcykmj4iie.myfritz.net'),(71,'Extreme Convention','2015-04-17 00:00:00','2015-04-19 00:00:00',1,'Antwerp, Belgium','An Extreme Convention:)','More info soon!!!','http://www.extremeconvention.be/extreme/en/index.html'),(72,'Acro Revolution Teacher Training','2015-04-09 00:00:00','2015-04-21 00:00:00',1,'Hawaii','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Acro Revolution Teacher Training teaches acrobats to train, embody, and teach partner acrobatics.</span></div>','<div>Creating teachers that have the knowledge, resources, and support to succeed as a teacher in their community.</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Revolution TT is a 12 day residential training focused on the art of being a mindful acrobat. The training will consist of intensive instruction in L-base acrobatics with a focus on skills including; washing machines, foot to hand, hand to hand, whips, pops, and other circus monkey tricks. In addition to learning techniques to fully embody this practice, you will learn how to teach partner acrobatics at various levels. The restorative practice of Acropeutics will be incorporated to create a more sustainable acrobatic practice and to help facilitate connection and community. In addition to the physical skills, training will include multiple sessions on teaching methodology, the ‘business’ of being an acro teacher, and community facilitation.</div><div><br></div><div>All material presented will be taught by using progressions and method based teaching practices. You will come out of this training equipped to not only teach acrobatics, but with the knowledge to train intelligently, heal yourself, and support your community.</div><div><br></div><div>OUR GOALS</div><div>The top 3 goals for the student are;</div><div><br></div><div>to be able to teach L- base acro</div><div>to have the tools and knowledge to have a sustainable teaching practice</div><div>to embody a practice based on safety and healthy communication</div>','http://acrorevolution.com/acro-revolution-teacher-training/'),(73,'Acro Yoga Montreal Teacher Training','2015-06-30 00:00:00','2015-07-26 00:00:00',1,'Montreal, Canada','<div>The art of teaching acroyoga with Jessie Goldberg, Eugene Poku and guest teachers.&nbsp;</div><div>4 weeks of physical reintegration, mental sharpening, emotional awakening and remembered wisdom. Come back to the source, Montréal the birth place of acroyoga.</div>','<div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Level 1 only: June 30 - July 12, 2015 Cost: $1600 (+ TAX 15%) Acro Yoga manual included</div><div><br></div><div>Level 2 only: July 14 - 26, 2015 Cost: $1600 (+ TAX 15%) Acro Yoga manual included</div><div><br></div><div>Discount for Level 1 &amp; 2: July 1 - 27, 2014 &nbsp; Cost: $2600 (+ TAX 15%) Acro Yoga manual included</div>','http://acroyoga.com/teacher-training/1'),(74,'Spin Circus Short Course','2014-12-08 00:00:00','2014-12-19 00:00:00',1,'Melbourne, Australia','This NEW short course is designed for those who work full time or have other commitments, think of it as a training holiday!','<div><br></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>We are now offering a limited number of places in our 2 Week, Full Time intensive in December 2014. Suitable for practicing and aspiring circus artists, as well as industry professionals looking for an immersive training program with some of Australia\'s TOP Circus Trainers.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>COURSE DETAILS</div><div>Dates: Monday 8th December- Friday 19th December</div><div><br></div><div>Fees:&nbsp;</div><div>$850 (Full time 2 weeks)</div><div>$450 (Full time 1 week)</div><div><br></div><div>Timetable:&nbsp;</div><div>Monday 8:15am - 3:30pm</div><div>Tuesday 8:15am - 3:30pm</div><div>Wednesday 12pm - 4pm</div><div>Thursday 8:15am - 3:30pm</div><div>Friday 12:30pm - 6:30pm</div><div><br></div><div>Location: Flying Trapeze Australia, 26 Cottage Street Blackburn</div><div><br></div><div>Teachers:&nbsp;</div><div>Alex Mizzen (Handstands/Tissu)&nbsp;</div><div>Vanessa McGregor (Basics/Trapeze/Double Trapeze)</div><div>+ more TBA</div><div><br></div><div>Specialties: Handbalance, Adagio/Hand to Hand, Contortion, Tissu, Rope, Straps, Lyra, Trapeze, Flying Trapeze, Doubles Trapeze, Hula Hoops.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>','http://www.spincircusacademy.com/short-courses.html'),(76,'AcroYoga Spring Break','2015-03-28 00:00:00','2015-04-04 00:00:00',1,'Costa Rica','Lead by Ezra \"The Boss\" LeBank &amp; Slava \"The Base\" Goloubov, Born To Fly Bossy 2015 will feature AcroYoga Workshops built on more than 20 years of combined experience in Acrobatics, Yoga, Circus, and Thai Massage that refine your technique, elevate your awareness, expand your creativity, and bring out the boss you were born to be!','<div>BORN TO FLY BOSSY</div><div>AcroYoga Retreat 2015</div><div><br></div><div>W/ Ezra LeBank &amp; Slava Goloubov</div><div><br></div><div>March 28 - April 4, 2015</div><div>Goddess Garden Eco Resort</div><div>Tuba Creek, Costa Rica</div><div><br></div><div>The Bossy Flyer Braintrust was given a secret mission to discover paradise. We were expecting mono-limb goofy inverted hands-free reverse star... or something like that. Instead, this is what they came up with:</div><div><br></div><div>7 Days &amp; Nights in the Costa Rican Rainforest</div><div>Exquisite Healthy Cuisine (W Vegetarian Options)</div><div>Morning Yoga Classes&nbsp;</div><div>Daily AcroYoga Workshops</div><div>360° Open Meditation/Yoga Room</div><div>Leaf-Covered Pavilion&nbsp;</div><div>Restaurant and Bar&nbsp;</div><div>Swimming Pool with Whirlpool</div><div>Hammocks&nbsp;</div><div>Enchanting Tropical Gardens</div><div>Sandy Beaches on the Caribbean</div><div><br></div><div>...And enough Bossy Flying to pack a picnic!*</div><div>*(a particularly bossy picnic.)</div><div><br></div><div>Lead by Ezra \"The Boss\" LeBank &amp; Slava \"The Base\" Goloubov, Born To Fly Bossy 2015 will feature AcroYoga Workshops built on more than 20 years of combined experience in Acrobatics, Yoga, Circus, and Thai Massage that refine your technique, elevate your awareness, expand your creativity, and bring out the boss you were born to be!</div><div><br></div><div>AcroYoga &amp; Yoga will be accessible for all levels with at least 6-months experience, with options available for intermediate and advanced practitioners.</div><div><br></div><div>Fees:</div><div><br></div><div>$1250 USD includes accommodations, meals, all classes, shuttle transportation to and from the retreat center.</div><div>(per person, airfare not included)</div><div><br></div><div>**Early Bird Special $1000**</div><div>With Deposit by November 30th, Pending Availability as Space is Limited.</div><div><br></div><div>Secure Your Spot With $350 Deposit</div><div>Write to: acroyogaretreat@gmail.com</div><div><br></div><div>Want More Info:</div><div><br></div><div>www.bossyflyer.com</div><div>www.acroyogavancity.com</div><div>www.thegoddessgarden.com</div><div><br></div><div>BOSSY BIOS</div><div><br></div><div>EZRA \"The Boss\" LeBank is an internationally recognized movement specialist. As the Head of Movement at California State University - Long Beach, and the Director of the AcroYoga Research Institute, Ezra travels across the globe, teaching acrobats how to fly bossy and performing like a boss... when he feels like it.</div><div><br></div><div>SLAVA Goloubov is solely dedicated to the exploration of the body, mastering arts like Gymnastics, Acroyoga, Circus Hand to Hand, Acrobatics,Yoga Flow, Thai Massage and stillness trough Vipassana Mediation. As a full time teacher he guides his students to find and master their bodies through rigorous exploration and fulfilling integration.</div><div><br></div>','http://acroyogavancity.com/retreats.html'),(77,'YogaSlackers Teacher Training','2015-06-05 00:00:00','2015-06-14 00:00:00',1,'Harrisonburg, Virginia USA','Become a YogaSlackers Teacher','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Teachers that pass the course will receive the YogaSlackers “blessings” to teach. New teachers will be encouraged to begin sharing the work (and adding to it) through workshops, classes, events, performance, tours, and intensives- all backed by the YogaSlackers name and growing support system. Teachers will be listed on the YogaSlackers official website. Teachers will become an admin of the regional YS Facebook Page. Teachers are allowed to purchase at a special Teachers only rate additional eLines, YogaSlackers DVD’s, clothing and whatever else we come up with for retail sales and teaching.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div>TRAINING LOGISTICS</div><div>Location: Harrisonburg, VA</div><div>http://horizonsvalleypike.com/</div><div><br></div><div>Dates: June 5- June 14, 2015</div><div>Arrive on Jun 5th between 3 and 6pm</div><div>Depart on June 14th at noon</div><div><br></div><div>Transportation:&nbsp;</div><div>Most people fly into DC and then&nbsp;</div><div>carpool to Valley Pike. You can also fly into CHO.</div><div><br></div><div>Cost: $2195</div><div><br></div><div>To Request an Application email:</div><div>tt@yogaslackers.com</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/676712809116699/?ref_newsfeed_story_type=regular'),(78,'Fierce Grace','2015-12-27 00:00:00','2016-01-03 00:00:00',1,'Roatan Island,  Honduras','Many days will include activities such as yoga, acrobatics, Slacklining, AcroYoga, and beach time.','<p style=\"padding-top: 0pt; \" class=\"paragraph_style\">Yoga * Slacklining * AcroYoga * Ayurveda * Thai Massage * Snorkeling<br></p>\r\n                  <p class=\"paragraph_style\"><br></p>\r\n                  <p class=\"paragraph_style_1\">In all paths of equanimity, one must feel out the edges in order to settle upon a middle road.&nbsp; This <span class=\"style_2\">full week</span> retreat is meant to explore these boundaries of <span class=\"style_3\">restoration and revitalization</span>, creating an opening for you to find your own comfortable and supported path somewhere in the middle.&nbsp; <br></p>\r\n                  Many days will include activities such as <span class=\"style_2\">yoga, acrobatics, Slacklining, AcroYoga, and beach time</span>.&nbsp;\r\n You’ll get a chance to play and expand and try many new activities!&nbsp; To\r\n move in sync with nature, other days are meant to turn the focus inward\r\n with discussions on <span class=\"style_2\">Ayurvedic self-healing \r\nrituals, guided meditations, Thai massage, interacting with the \r\nmagnificence that surrounds you and time for personal exploration</span>.&nbsp;\r\n We’ll explore how it feels to move boldly and fiercely through this \r\nworld with confidence, and also how to find the courage and \r\nvulnerability to walk with humility and grace.<br><br>Facebook Link:&nbsp; https://www.facebook.com/events/1424267817888380/<br>','http://www.fiercegraceretreat.com/Welcome.html'),(79,'S.A.F.E.','2015-06-19 00:00:00','2015-06-21 00:00:00',1,'Ljubljana, Republic Of Slovenija','S.A.F.E. - Slovenian Acro Festival Event','<div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Acroyoga and partner acrobatics teachers in Slovenia stepped together and decided to offer you weekend full of safety, teamwork and fun.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">So we proudly present S.A.F.E.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">1st Slovenian Acro Festival Event. Our goal is to make family friendly event which will promote acroyoga and partner acrobatics and all the amazing benefits that come with training it.</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Also we wanted to offer you different styles from different teachers all in one place.&nbsp;</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">So mark weekend from 19th to 21st of June 2015 on your calendars and come to join us in beautifull sLOVEnia!</span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font color=\"#373e4d\" face=\"helvetica, arial, lucida grande, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 12.2880001068115px; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></font></div><img src=\"http://safefestival.si/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/SAFE.jpg\" width=\"100%\">','http://safefestival.si/'),(80,'Thailand Slackline and AcroYoga Retreat','2015-12-01 00:00:00','2015-12-08 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','Join the YogaSlackers on their second Retreat in Chiang Mai, Thailand! Redefine your known limits with Sam Salwei, Raquel Hernández and Emily Baxter','<div>ALL INCLUSIVE RETREAT</div><div>December 1st to 8th 2015!</div><div><br></div><div>$1,000 before August 1st 2015</div><div>$1,300 after</div><div><br></div><div>Join the YogaSlackers in their 2nd Retreat in Chiang Mai, Thailand! &nbsp;With Sam Salwei, Raquel Hernández and Emily Baxter. This trio of modern day nomads will facilitate a 7 day exploration of your human potential.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Focused on the dualities a nomadic life, several acrobatic practices and active recovery, they will explore the edges of your perceived limits and will teach you how to surpass them. &nbsp;Through thoughtful exploration on the importance of stillness in movement, the softness found in strength and the art of silent communication, they will facilitate a personal rediscovery like no other. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>INCLUDED ACTIVITIES</div><div>Morning Yoga Practice</div><div>Slackline Yoga</div><div>AcroYoga</div><div>Slackro</div><div>Dutch Acrobatics</div><div>Water Acrobatics</div><div>Thai Massage and Flying Therapeutics</div><div>Games and Fun Challenges</div><div><br></div><div>INCLUDED AMENITIES</div><div>7 Night Stay at Kaomai Lanna Resort in Shared Room&nbsp;</div><div>3 Meals per day</div><div>1 Private Thai Massage</div><div>1 Group Excursion</div><div>Transportation from the Chiang Mai Airport</div><div><br></div><div>TEACHING TEAM</div><div>YogaSlackers Sam Salwei and Raquel Hernández are well known for bringing their students to their edges and beyond. As modern day nomads, you can find them driving coast to coast, or hopping on a plane to teach overseas. Sam is the co-founder of the YogaSlackers, and has a great deal of knowledge and experience on the slackline, creating amazing spectacles wherever he goes. Raquel\'s extensive training in different types of Yoga, AcroYoga, Slacklining, and listening, makes her a motivating and receptive teacher, great at progressing her students further. With their many combined talents and skills, these two always have something new and exciting to share and together, making them the perfect teaching team.</div><div><br></div><div>Emily Baxter is dedicated to sharing and teaching whatever she can to inspire freedom in people. A bit of a jack of all trades, she teaches and practices several styles of Yoga asana, including Hatha, Yin, Vinyasa as well as AcroYoga and Slackline Yoga. &nbsp;She teaches anatomy, methodology and adjustments on various Yoga Teacher Trainings and runs her own Yin Yoga teacher training programs as well as Partner Acrobatics Intensives and Teacher Trainings. She is also trained as a Postural Therapist. Emily has always had a passion for movement and body awareness. This coupled with her strong background in anatomy manifests in her teachings as clear, precise, thoughtful instruction. She continues to study, travel, teach, play and laugh wherever she may find herself.</div><div><br></div><div>SAMPLE DAY</div><div>7:00 AM &nbsp; &nbsp; Yoga</div><div>8:30 AM &nbsp; &nbsp; Breakfast</div><div>9:30 AM &nbsp; &nbsp; Slackline/AcroYoga</div><div>12:00 PM &nbsp; &nbsp;Lunch Break</div><div>3:00 PM &nbsp; &nbsp; AcroYoga/Slackline</div><div>5:00 PM &nbsp; &nbsp; Conditioning/Acrobatics</div><div>6:00 PM &nbsp; &nbsp; Dinner</div><div>8:00 PM &nbsp; &nbsp; Therapeutics</div><div><br></div><div>PLANNING &amp; GETTING TO THAILAND</div><div>We recommend you to enjoy Chiang Mai for few days before the training and possibly stay longer afterwards. &nbsp;Most countries automatically receive 30 days upon arrival. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Check-In and Check-out times at Kaomai Lanna are:&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;In: &nbsp; &nbsp; Monday Dec 1st at 1:00 PM</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Out: &nbsp;Dec 8th at 11:00 AM</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;www.kaomailanna.com</div><div><br></div><div>PRE-REQUISITES</div><div>This retreat will serve as an opportunity to polish your acrobatic skills. &nbsp;Different skill levels are welcome in this retreat. &nbsp;We will start the 7 days of exploration teaching and reviewing the basics forms of Slackline Yoga and AcroYoga. &nbsp;As we progress through the week we will add more challenges suitable to each individual. &nbsp;We promise you will not feel too new or experience to truly enjoy it! &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>During the first day we will review the pre-reqs and move forward from there. Depending on the group skills we might divide into different groups to cover advanced Acrobatics and Slackrobatics. Everyone will have the opportunity to learn from Emily, Sam and Raquel directly. To get the most out of your experience, practice these set of skills beforehand.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>You don\'t need a partner, but we\'ll honor people wanting to work with one.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>ACROYOGA PREREQUISITES&nbsp;</div><div>30 seconds holds</div><div>Fly AND Base</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Free Headstand</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Handstand on the Wall</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Free Bird</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Free Star</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Free Shoulder Stand</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Foot to Hand</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Tuck Sit</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Foot to Shin</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Shin to Foot</div><div><br></div><div>Repetitions... 10 each&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Kick into Handstand (Wall)</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Bird Presses</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Throne Presses</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Star Presses</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Push-ups 15 repetitions&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Washing Machine</div><div>3 repetitions in your main roll (base or fly)</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Barrel Roll</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;4-Steps</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Catherine\'s Wheel</div><div><br></div><div>SLACKLINE YOGA PREREQUISITES</div><div>No set pre-requisites for slacklining. &nbsp;This are a few suggestions on things to work on. &nbsp;But we will cover them during our first slackline classes. &nbsp;</div><div>Watch a Video</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Stand</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Sit</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Kneel</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Pointer</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Tucksit</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>REGISTRATION&nbsp;</div><div>bit.ly/ysthairetreat</div><div>$1,000 before August 1st 2015</div><div>$1,300 after</div><div><br></div><div>All teachers receive 20% discount.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>MORE INFORMATION&nbsp;</div><div>and to get your teacher discount code email:</div><div>raquel@yogaslackers.com</div><div>787-704-9613</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/316475975216524'),(81,'Acro Kiel','2016-02-19 00:00:00','2016-02-21 00:00:00',1,'Kiel, Germany','A Typical hardcore German Acro festival with about 250 participants.','<div>Registration</div><div><br></div><div>Until 5.2.2016, after that add 5 € \"panic fee\"; if you come unregistered, you can\'t get food (because this is ordered by number in advance) and may be not even participate, if the maximum number of particitiants is reached. You will receive an email confirmation automatically, another email, when your payment gets booked, and finally one, where your participation gets confirmed (after we checked the waiting list etc.). If you do not get any mails like this, contact us: Something might go wrong!</div><div><br></div><div>Friday</div><div>17-24 o\'clock acrobatics, ca. 20:30 vegetarian/non-vegetarian dinner buffet (first time with bio components).</div><div>Saturday</div><div>9-19 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet, vegetarian/non-vegetarian dinner buffet (first time with bio components), show and Party.</div><div>Sunday</div><div>9-15 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet.</div><div><br></div><div>Costs</div><div>People less than 6 years: free, people between 6 and 16 years (excl.): 35 €, older people: 60 €, if you don\'t mind, you are welcome to pay a little extra, to sponsor the kids fee (that does not match the costs).</div><div><br></div><div>Payment</div><div>We are sending the account information with the confirmation email, that usually comes right away (i.e.: If you do not receive a confirmation email within 3 days, something went worg; try again or contact AkroKiel@AkroKiel.de). The registrations gets valid with the payment (i.e. without payment, you are not registered!).</div><div><br></div><div>Location</div><div>Sports Center of the Christian-Albrecht-University Kiel, Olshausenstrasse 74, Kiel.</div><div><br></div><div>Maximum number of participiants</div><div>This year, the maximum number of participants (250) might be exceeded again, until now, 0 people registered.</div>','http://tiroqrgcykmj4iie.myfritz.net'),(82,'Move Copenhagen','2015-06-26 00:00:00','2015-06-28 00:00:00',1,'Copenhagen, Denmark','<div>A community driven festival celebrating the diversity of movement. Workshops in Slackline, AcroYoga, Parkour, Climbing, Yoga, Dance and much more!!!</div><div><br></div>','<div>Move Copenhagen is a partnership between multiple sports organizations who have come together to create a unique experience of movement.</div><div><br></div><div>Meet some of the best movers in slacklining, climbing, dance, parkour, yoga and acroyoga.</div><div><br></div><div>There are workshops for beginners and challenges for even the most experienced movers.</div><div><br></div><div>The early bird tickets price is 495 DKK (normal tickets are 695 DKK), which includes entrance fee, workshops &amp; a free spot for your tent.</div><div><br></div><div>Dont forget your mealticket - https://billetto.dk/da/events/meals-move-copenhage...</div><div><br></div><div>More info: Move Copenhagen on Facebook or at our website</div><div><br></div>','http://movecopenhagen.com'),(83,'French Acrobatics Convention ','2015-07-08 00:00:00','2015-06-17 00:00:00',1,'Ste Eulalie en Born, France','International exchange and free training, as well as workshops with international teachers, mostly in partner-acrobatics, but also in other circus disciplines.','<div>*Full!!—Waiting List Only!!</div><div><br></div><div>Open to all interested adult acrobats (as well as children and adolescents) with at least 6 months of experience. There will be a maximum of 130 participants (app. 25 teachers, chiefs, organisators, 15 helpers, 80 adults and 10 adolescents/children).</div><div><br></div><div>In general: this year we would like to try a graduation of prices, to allow people with little money to participate in the convention. The ”normal” price is € 440; we offer to pay</div><div>(by your own judgement) a price between € 400 and € 480. If this system won’t work in summation, than we had to demand later during the convention the missing money...</div><div>For \"normal\" participants</div><div>€ 400 - € 480 per adult (beginning by 16 years) inclusive of food, workshops and camping</div><div>in own tent (participants who has to stay with their camper van or caravan on</div><div>the campsite, has to pay arround € 100 more (to us). € 285 - € 345 for persons between 10 and 15 years old</div><div>€ 100 for persons up to 9 years old</div><div>€ 65 per day (flat-rate € 25, meals € 20 and workshops € 20)</div><div>For \"helpers\" (from 18 years old)</div><div>€ 220 only people staying the whole time could be helpers!</div><div>\"helpers\" will be called upon during the convention to work 8 shifts of 3- 4 hours and have to join the first meeting on the 8th of July, 11 am!</div><div>￼￼</div><div>Inscription:</div><div>1. From the 11th of March per email at thorsten.bohle@gmx.de . Than you’ll receive payment details (if there a free places left) and have to pay a commission</div><div>of € 130. When we receive your money, you’ll get a confirmation about your place and have to pay the rest of the money cash (in € only) on the convention (on the location there is no cash-machine!).</div><div>2. Money must be received by June 8th at latest!</div><div>Otherwise your place will be taken by people on the waiting list...!</div><div>￼Cancelation policy:</div><div>Attention:</div><div>A short notice:</div><div>For every cancelation before the 9th of June, we’ll take a fee from € 15.</div><div>People, who are staying shorter than enrolled, won’t get the rest of the money back! By a cancelation after inclusively June 8th you won’t get back your commission!</div><div>None of the mobile homes will be allowed to park in the convention area.</div><div>Such vehicles must be stationed in the neighboring campsite, where you have to</div><div>register on your own (www.lecampingdulac.com) before the convention!</div><div>We see ourselves as friends amongst friends who are glad to organise an event, but also naturally expect everyone to help with the everyday chores (especially as we are planning to make only very few money from the meeting). As most of the work during the meeting will consist of doing the shopping, cooking, ferrying people, etc., we wish to spread these tasks evenly amongst the participants. In practice, this means that everyone over 15 years old will be asked to help with food preparation or with washing up two times during the meeting. In our experience, work in the kitchen was always a very fun and communicative experience, so many people will probably want to help more than their share...!</div><div>Detailed information about the Acrobatics Convention:</div><div>The meeting will take place in</div><div>“Ste. Eulalie en Born du Lac”, app. 120 km south west of Bordeaux.</div><div>The site of the convention is located directly next to a big campsite,</div><div>itself situated less than 100 m</div><div>from the large \"Etang de Biscarrosse\" lake and otherwise very isolated.</div><div>There is a sandy beach at the lake, where it is possible to play volleyball. Acrobatics can be easily</div><div>practised in the water, as the banks are very shallow. For more information on the campsite, please</div><div>look under: www.lecampingdulac.com</div><div>Our quarters will be located directly next to the campsite. We will have sole use of our own big field with a few oak trees and lots of stag beetles.</div><div>Many of your tents will not have shade as we wish to reserve that space for training and daytime activities.</div><div>￼￼</div><div>￼￼It’s the second year, where we have our own kitchen material, which we had to buy or rent and which we still restock.</div><div>There will be a hot meal every day in the evening, which will be prepared by our chiefs and helpers. For breakfast and lunch, rich buffets will be served.</div><div>Toilets and showers are to be found in the neighbouring camp site. If you must bring a dog, additional costs will need to be paid to the campsite!</div><div>At this time of year the weather is usually great and if it does rain, it goes by quickly thanks to the proximity of the sea. In other words, there is very seldom bad weather! Unfortunately, there are no more backup tents for acrobatics and we would not offer other program in this case!</div><div>Although temperatures during the day are usually around 25° to 30 °C, it can get very cold at night! In any case, take a warm sleeping bag with you.</div><div>We have invited professional teachers to the festival, who will organise the daily workshops at different levels. The main orientation of the workshops will be partner acrobatics; but we will also plan workshops in other circus disciplines, such as silks, dance-acrobatics and Thai massage.</div><div>Provisional daily planning of the acrobatics convention:</div><div>The schedule below is subject to change. It will be adapted to the conditions, the requirements of the workshop leaders and the interests of the participants.</div><div>8:00 - 9:00 8:30 - 10:00 9:30 - 10:00</div><div>10:00 - 10:30 10:45 - 12:15 12:15 - 13:45 13:45 - 15:00 15:00 - 16:30 16:45 - 18:45 19:00 - 20:15 20:15 - 21:15</div><div>Yoga</div><div>Breakfast</div><div>Warming Up</div><div>Handstands</div><div>1. Workshop-Bloc (app. 5 parallel offers at different levels and focus on basics) free training with a teacher as contact person</div><div>Lunch/Buffet</div><div>Midday-Break</div><div>2. Workshop-Bloc (app. 5 parallel offers at different levels and focus on int./advan.) warm dinner</div><div>Thai Massage</div><div>￼￼We have planned again a canoeing day this year. Not far away from the campsite, it’s possible to go paddling for four hours on a scenic, clear river that meanders through a forest before flowing into a lake. From there, we will be towed back by motorboats to our starting point. The river and ultra-stable boats present no dangers even for beginners and guaranteed to be huge fun!</div><div>As an alternative we offer a “Massage-Special”!</div><div>What\'s more, we will again spend a day at the seaside, with buffet and romantic sunset.</div><div>An open stage (probably on July 15th ) is planned at the end of the week; anyone who wishes can present an act on stage, or show off some of the things learned during the week. The show will take place near the lake, where probably many spectators from the campsite will attend.</div><div>If you ́ve got any questions in connection with payment or material, contact Jasper: jasper.janke@gmx.de Jasper 0049 (0)176-21 50 85 25</div><div>If you ́ve got any questions in connection with application and general information, contact Thorsten: thorsten.bohle@gmx.de Thorsten 0049 (0)178-61 62 164</div><div>If you have any ideas, how we could improve the meeting, tell us about them in advance!</div><div>We hope for a wonderful acrobatics meeting in your company, with many people and as many new, diverse artistic ideas!</div><div>Greetings from Jasper and Thorsten</div><div><br></div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/1481915548759031/'),(91,'Moscow Solar Acrobatic Immersion with Jason and Chelsey!','2015-09-30 00:00:00','2015-10-04 00:00:00',1,'Moscow, Russia','Jason and Chelsey lead this 5 day Solar Acrobatic immersion, expect to walk away with an arsenal of progressive acrobatic trainings, dynamic movements and ninja like spotting skills!!','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Pre Reqs: Be able to base or fly the following: 1 min free star hold, 5 candlestick presses, 3 plank to shoulderstand transitions, 30 sec tucksit, 3 barrel rolls (front plank to straddle bat- front plank) See video for a visual.&nbsp;</span></div><div><br></div><div>What to Expect:</div><div>- Learn progressively in a fun and safe environment</div><div>- learn to train safely and take away training regimes</div><div>- train with two very passionate and highly experienced teachers</div><div>- experience the power of play in acrobatics and in nature</div><div>- Release perceived limitations and explore your life at the</div><div>next level!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>*This course fulfills a pre-requisite for AcroYoga Teacher&nbsp;</div><div>Training application.</div><div><br></div><div>Your Teachers:&nbsp;</div><div>Jason and Chelsey Magness built their relationship on a shared passion for adventure. As professional multi-sport athletes and teachers they help thousands of students every year at live workshops, elite training camps and online at JandCTraining.com. As part of Team YogaSlackers they travel the globe competing in some of the toughest races on earth, battling rugged conditions and exploring the edge of human potential. Whether racing&nbsp;</div><div>across remote icebergs, practicing acroyoga or balancing on a slackline a thousand feet above ground, they\'ve learned to train the mind and body to surpass limits and take life to the next level.</div><div><br></div><div>Details on the Extracurricular Activities from our hosts, The Moscow Acro Family:&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>5-day Incredible AcroYoga Festival</div><div>Experience Russian hospitality, enjoy mind blowing acrobatic performances, check our Lenin, Red Square and KGB-agents, try Russian banya , groove the way only Russians can...</div><div>Acro workshops in Moscow are not just long-hours hard-core practices…. Love &amp; light ambience. Genial crew of Russian hosts. Special evening programs, kirtans, performances, games, acrojams ..&nbsp;</div><div>Strong bases, gorgeous flyers and caring spotters cannot wait to play with you</div><div>Starring World famous YogaSlackers (Jason&amp;Chelsey)…. Acromaniacs, extreme path breakers and just awesome guys!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Daily Schedule:&nbsp;</div><div>10:45 Morning meeting (Hugs, kisses, mantras)</div><div>11:00 Practice with Jason &amp; Chelsey</div><div>14:00 Lunch &amp; Rest</div><div>16:00 Practice with Jason &amp; Chelsey</div><div>19:00 Evening Rituals</div><div>19:15 Dinner &amp; Entertainments (optional)</div><div><br></div><div>To get an admission to the Immersion we kindly ask you to send an e-mail to mosacro@gmail.com with a subject “Solar Immersion with JandC” answering following questions</div><div>1. Full name</div><div>2. Country of Origin</div><div>3. Contact details (cell &amp; mail)</div><div>4. Acro Experience (months, years)</div><div>5. Acro Practice Level (washing machines and elements you can play easily with)</div><div><br></div><div>Get surprised with our more than friendly prices:&nbsp;</div><div>15 000 ₽ (current rate around $300 ) before 30.07.2015</div><div>17 500 ₽ (current rate around $350 ) before 30.08.2015</div><div>20 000 ₽ (current rate around $400 ) after 15.09.2015</div><div><br></div><div>Please, take a notice that all the prices are fixed in rubles and the Russian national currency is so unpredictable as the drunk bear is. Therefore we highly recommend you to book and pay in advance to secure oneself against all risks and possible rate changes. You will get an e-mail with all payment details having completed the signing up form.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Visa &amp; info support for all foreign guests: mosacro@gmail.com</div><div><br></div><div>We provide support and facilitate a procedure of obtaining Russian visa, searching for budget flights, free accommodation and would be happy to guide you in Moscow.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/1583045471966718/'),(84,'Partner Acrobatics Thailand Intensive','2016-01-02 00:00:00','2016-01-15 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','<div>Refine your Acro skills and have loads of fun!!!</div><div><br></div>','Working to improve our practice, training hard and enjoying resort life:)<div><br></div><div>More info re prerequisites and fees on or website.</div>','http://www.partner-acrobatics.com/program-thai.php'),(85,'Bosnia Convention','2015-08-10 00:00:00','2015-08-16 00:00:00',1,'Krupa, Bosnia-Herzegovina ','An intimate festival in an undiscovered and unspoiled corner of Europe','<div>5 days of acrobatics and related disciplines under the Bosnian sun. Next to the Vrbas, our icecold and crystal clear river, hosted by the local towns people with vegetarian and locally grown- and prepared food.</div><div><br></div>','http://cirkusbanjaluka.wordpress.com'),(86,'German Kula Celebration','2015-07-30 00:00:00','2015-08-02 00:00:00',1,'Beichlingen, Germany','<div>Get ready to enjoy workshops with an international teaching crew, dance-night, concert, kids program, handstand-privates, Nature, Bodywork &amp; Dessert Party, good food and much more.</div>','<div>We are so looking forward to celebrate the abundance of togetherness, fun playtime and pure delight with all of YOU!!!</div><div><br></div><div>Save the date and be a part of it.</div>','http://www.germankula.de'),(87,'Barcelona Yoga Conference','2015-07-02 00:00:00','2015-07-06 00:00:00',1,'Barcelona, Spain','A Yoga Conference with a lot of Acro:)','<div>Welcome to the V Barcelona Yoga Conference&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>A space of inspiration and growth</div><div><br></div><div>The BYC is a Yogic Celebration open to people from all ages and backgrounds with or without previous experience in yoga. An uplifting open hearted gathering with world leading Yoga teachers and musical artists creating a platform for you to learn, experience, discover and transform.</div><div><br></div><div>One of Europe’s largest Yoga Conferences</div><div>5 full days of Yoga, Music and Dance</div><div>Over 600 vibrant participants from the 5 Continents</div><div>Free activities every day all day</div><div>20 Yoga styles</div><div>50 teachers &amp; artists internationally recognized</div><div>108 Scholarships</div><div>40 Stands</div><div>100 Volunteers&nbsp;</div><div>BYC Kids</div><div>3% Solidarity&nbsp;</div>','http://www.barcelonayogaconference.cat/index.php/en/'),(88,'Nordic AcroYoga Festival','2015-06-26 00:00:00','2015-06-29 00:00:00',1,'Mundekulla, Sweden','AcroBhakti invites you to AcroYoga Festival at wonderful Mundekulla eco-retreat center in the forest of southern Sweden.','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">There will be workshops for both beginners and experienced. All are welcome.</span></div><div>Come and share four days full of amazing festival atmosphere in beautiful surroundings. This is an alcohol and drug free event. Chocolate and cookies are welcome !</div><div><br></div><div>\"AcroYoga is a community based practice. We ignite our collective potential as we support each other to reach new heights. AcroYoga invites you to experience the full spectrum of your being through opportunities to: give and receive; to support and to be supported; to be strong and sensitive. It is a systematic approach designed to be accessible to every practitioner, and encourages personal transformation in an atmosphere of acceptance, celebration and safety.\"</div><div>www.AcroYoga.org</div><div><br></div><div> Organizer </div><div>The festival is arranged by AcroBhakti in collaboration with Mundekulla.</div><div><br></div>','http://www.acrobhakti.com/p/acroyogafestival.html?lng=eng'),(89,'NW AcroYoga Summer Camp-Out','2015-07-16 00:00:00','2015-07-19 00:00:00',1,'Portland, Oregon, USA','3 Days of AcroYoga, Slacklining, Dancing, Camping, and More....','<div>Multiple workshops at all levels each day.....</div><div><br></div><div>Last year was a huge success and this year space is definitely limited so sign up early.</div><div><br></div><div>Location to be announced soon....and this year we will have a swimming hole!</div><div><br></div><div>Teachers: Jacob Handwerker, Lux, Josh Young, and more......</div><div><br></div><div>You are responsible for all camping gear. Organic vegetarian delicious meals from Thursday dinner to Sunday lunch included.</div><div><br></div><div>Kids and families welcome!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Smoke, Alcohol, and Drug free. Please leave pets at home too.</div><div><br></div><div>Price: $275 for Everything!</div><div><br></div><div>Kids under 10 are free</div><div>Kids 11 to 17 are $75.</div><div><br></div><div>To register email: acroyogacampout@gmail.com</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/1539960212946654/'),(90,'Acro Camp','2015-07-30 00:00:00','2015-08-02 00:00:00',1,'Illinois, USA','<div>For the fourth year in a row!</div><div><br></div>','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Last year was amazing thanks to all of you who showed up to laugh, play and explore. We\'re going to open up Thursday night, play all day Friday, Saturday and Sunday.</span></div><div><br></div><div>This year is certainly going to be bigger and with your help even better than the last three years.</div><div><br></div><div>I\'m looking forward to seeing all of my old friends from acro-past and making new ones with you.</div><div><br></div><div>Cost:</div><div>Admissions:</div><div>Three Day Tickets - Thursday night - Sunday</div><div>$100 - Early Registration</div><div>$130 after May 31&nbsp;</div><div>$160 after June 30 - Late Registration</div><div><br></div><div>Two Day Tickets - Friday Night - Sunday</div><div>$85 - Early Admission</div><div>$115 after May 31&nbsp;</div><div>$145 after June 30 - Late Registration</div>','http://www.divineflight.com/acrocamp-2015.html'),(92,'Next Level Acro Intensive','2015-09-25 00:00:00','2015-09-27 00:00:00',1,'Basel, Switzerland','In this 15 hour Acro Intensive with Jason and Chelsey -we\'ll explore a systematic and progressive way to approach the shift from advanced beginner to intermediate and intermediate to advanced - giving you tools to take your practice to the next level.&nbsp;','<div>We\'ll work throughout six acro modalities: standing, handbalancing, popping, inversions, spinning/rotation, and monolimb work. (intermediate and up)</div><div><br></div><div>What to expect:&nbsp;</div><div>-15 hours of fun, intense, and challenging work</div><div>- a training regime that you can remember and take with you.</div><div>- tools and progressions to take your practice to the next level</div><div><br></div><div>Pre-Reqs:&nbsp;</div><div>1 min free star</div><div>30 sec tuck sit</div><div>1 min foot to hand</div><div>1 min shoulderstand</div><div>the ability to be stacked or stack a human on one leg.</div><div><br></div><div>*if you have questions about your ability, please contact Jason and Chelsey at jandc@jandctraining.com.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Your teachers:&nbsp;</div><div>Jason and Chelsey Magness- of the YogaSlackers and two of the founders of AcroGasm and JandCtraining built their relationship on a shared passion for adventure. As professional multi-sport athletes and teachers they help thousands of students every year at live workshops, elite training camps and online at JandCTraining.com. As part of Team YogaSlackers they travel the globe competing in some of the toughest races on earth, battling rugged conditions and exploring the edge of human potential. Whether racing across remote icebergs, practicing acroyoga or balancing on a slackline a thousand feet above ground, they\'ve learned to train the mind and body to surpass limits and take life to the next level.</div><div><br></div><div>Dates:&nbsp;</div><div>September 25 - 27</div><div>Friday 25: 6 - 9pm</div><div>Saturday and Sunday 26.-27: 10 am - 1pm and 2:30 - 5:30 pm</div><div><br></div><div>Location:</div><div>***attention please, we have two different locations, one for Friday, another one for Saturday and Sunday***</div><div><br></div><div>FRIDAY: Sportzentrum (gym) Pfaffenholz, Im Burgfelderhof, 68300 Basel.&nbsp;</div><div>Take Bus Nr. 50 to Friedrich-Miescher-Str (Casino Basel), short 5 min. walk to the Pfaffenholz gym.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>SAT and SUN: Gym Klingenthal, Kasernenstr. 1A, 4058 Basel.&nbsp;</div><div>Tramstation Kaserne (close to Claraplatz), gym on the left side of the lawn.</div><div><br></div><div>Prices:</div><div>Super-Early-Bird price: CHF 260.- (if paid before June 14th)</div><div>Early-Bird price: CHF 280.- ( if paid before August 20th)</div><div>Regular price: CHF 330.-&nbsp;</div><div>20% AY teacher discout</div><div><br></div><div>Registration &amp; Payment:</div><div>Option 1: To Chelsey &amp; Jason (jandc@jandctraining.com) and payment via paypal to their account</div><div>Option 2: For those not using PayPal: email to Alex Attinger (a.attinger@gmail.com) to receive regular bank transfer details (IBAN no. etc.)</div><div><br></div><div>Cancellation policy</div><div>Cancellations before Sep 1st will be issued a refund minus CHF 50. No refunds, no transfers and no credits for cancellations after Sep 1st.</div><div><br></div><div>How to get to Basel:&nbsp;</div><div>The EuroAirport Basel-Mulhouse-Freiburg is very close the workshop locations and there are cheap flight connections to many places in Europe. Basel can also very well reached by train (eg 3 hours from Paris) or overnight train.</div><div><br></div><div>For all non-Basel residents: We will try our best to organize a couch/ cheap sleep over options for you!</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/1059081290786654/'),(93,'Pitch Catch Circus','2016-02-15 00:00:00','2016-04-22 00:00:00',1,'Asheville, United States','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Taught by Niko Douwes, Cassie Drew</span></div>','Taught by Niko Douwes, Cassie Drew Intermediate/Advanced Immersion Pitch Catch Circus is a 9-week intensive partner acrobatic training course for intermediate to advanced acrobats, circus artists or physical movers.&nbsp;<div>Students receive 25 hands on teaching hours a week from world renowned Dutch Coach Niko Douwes in a variety of acrobatic genres including: Hand to Hand, Ikarian, Trio, Banquine, Toss the Girl, Washing Machines and Adagio.&nbsp;</div><div>We also place a special emphasis on tumbling with our amazing instructor Cassie Drew. Other elements such as flexibility, conditioning, handstands and dance are woven throughout the daily schedule of the course.&nbsp;</div><div>The course runs 8am-3:45 pm M-F Beginning Feb. 2016.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Apply online</div>','http://www.pitchcatchcircus.com'),(94,'AcroYoga Week Helsinki','2015-08-03 00:00:00','2015-08-07 00:00:00',1,'Helsinki, Finland','<div><font color=\"#141823\" face=\"helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 15.0080003738403px;\">A WEEK FULL OF ACROYOGA &amp; MORE</span></font></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 15.0080003738403px; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">Helsingin ensimmäinen AcroYoga-viikko on täällä. Kutsumme Suomen nykyiset ja tulevat acrojoogit koolle ja seikkailemme yhdessä akrobatian, hieronnan ja joogan maailmassa.</span></div>','<div>In week 32 Helsinki will be blown away by the world of AcroYoga. We offer a week full of classes and workshops on all levels. Whether you are just getting into Acro or working with some smooth washing machines we’ll give you something to work with. The classes will be mostly outdoors if whether permits. Thai Yoga Massage will be indoors. SUP session will be either monday or thurdsday depending on wheather. Will end the week on Friday night with finnish Sauna bathing ceremony.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Come and join, learn to AcroYoga. AcroYoga combines acrobatic concepts with a yogic consciousness. AY is a playful dance of movement finding balance between two bodies. Playing stimulates us physically and mentally. Those that play together grow together.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/479806068834029/'),(95,'15th Acrobatics Convention in Berlin','2015-11-13 00:00:00','2015-11-15 00:00:00',1,'Berlin','Acro in Berlin','<div>...english version below...</div><div><br></div><div>Liebe Akrobatinnen und Akrobaten,</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>das diesjährige Berliner Akrobatikfestival findet vom 13. - 15. November 2015 statt.</div><div><br></div><div>Informationen zum Festival und Details zur Anmeldung findet Ihr unter <a href=\"http://www.akro-berlin.de/\" title=\"\" target=\"\">http://www.akro-berlin.de/</a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Viele Grüße</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>die Berliner Akrobaten von Akro-Polis e.V.</div><div><a href=\"http://www.akro-berlin.de/\" title=\"\" target=\"\">http://www.akro-berlin.de/</a></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>***</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>English version</div><div><br></div><div>Dear acrobats,</div><div><br></div><div>This year the acrobatics convention in Berlin will take place from 13 to 15 November 2015.</div><div><br></div><div>You will find information concerning the convention and registration details at <a href=\"http://www.akro-berlin.de/\" title=\"\" target=\"\">http://www.akro-berlin.de/</a></div><div><br></div><div>Best regards,</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>the acrobats from Akro-Polis e.V., Berlin</div><div><a href=\"http://www.akro-berlin.de/\" title=\"\" target=\"\">http://www.akro-berlin.de/</a></div>','http://www.akro-berlin.de/'),(96,'Partner Acrobatics Advanced Intensive ','2016-05-20 00:00:00','2016-05-29 00:00:00',1,'Andalusia, Spain','Handstands, one arm progressions, hand to hand, standing acro, pitching and much much more!!','<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Join Partner Acrobatics for 9 days of high level acro training. This intensive will focus on more difficult tricks, geared towards the intermediate/advanced practitioner. If you want to refine your technique in hand to hand and other standing skills, come dial in your current challenges, learn the tricks you covet, and do it all in a supportive community full of lightness, laughter, and general shenanigans.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">No partner necessary, however if you expect to be training with someone of a particular level we recommend you bring that partner. While we have a basic level of prerequisite but there is always a blend of experience level.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">The price of the training includes all classes, accommodation, food and a 30 min private in the longe/spotting belt with your partner or another student from the training&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">A taste of the material we will be training ……</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Handstands, one arm and handstands on body parts</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Pops to hand 2 hand on L base</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Standing hand to hand and reverse hand to hand</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Different entrances into standing h2h</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Foot 2 hand standing and various entrances</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Transitions from the ground up and high transitions</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Pitching, banquina, toss the girl and Icarian</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">The program will be complemented with prehab sessions taught by Chance Kanfoush. Functional exercises for balanced training, reducing pain, improving performance and recovery time. Focus on pulling, low gait work, sequencing and coordination.</p>','http://partneracrobatics.com'),(97,'Acro & Inversions Workshop Series','2016-02-08 00:00:00','2016-02-11 00:00:00',1,'Koh Yao Noi, Phuket - Krabi. Thailand','Flying High Acrobatics presents Inversions &amp; Acro series, with Martin Kvist and Vanille Simeon.&nbsp;<div>We are super excited to share with you this exploration of diverse movements, communication and trust!</div>','<div><span style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\">Flying High Acrobatics presents Inversions &amp; Acro series in Koh Yao Noi, Phuket - Thailand from 8 - 11 February, with Martin Kvist and Vanille Simeon. We are super excited to share with you this exploration of diverse movements, communication and trust!</span></div><span style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><div><span style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></div>Program&nbsp;</span><br style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Feb 8th: Inversions &amp; Handstands MasterClass</span><br style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><span style=\"color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Feb 9th: Balance &amp; Counterbalances</span><span class=\"text_exposed_show\" style=\"display: inline; color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br>Feb 10th: Playfuls flows<br>Feb 11th: Building up trust and confidence</span>','http://flyinghighacrobatics.com/events.php'),(98,'Dutch Acro','2016-05-13 00:00:00','2016-05-16 00:00:00',1,'Rotterdam, Netherlands','<div style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\"><div style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\">Well-known for its large variety of workshops in acrobatics and related activities,<span style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\">&nbsp;by acrobats for acrobats, it is tradition that anyone with something exciting to offer shares this by running one or more workshops.</span></div><div><br></div></div>','<div>On the festival you will find:</div><div><br></div><div>Ten rounds of workshops at all levels</div><div>Two excellent shows with an after party</div><div>The \'crème de la crème\' of Acrobatic teachers</div><div>Camping on short grass (therefore no pollen!)</div><div>Great vegetarian food</div><div>A \'find your level\' opening workshop</div><div><br></div>','http://festival.akrobatiek.nl/home.php?l=en'),(99,'Karlsruher Akrobatikfestival','2016-03-31 00:00:00','2016-04-03 00:00:00',1,'Karlsruhe, Germany','We are looking forward to inviting you again this year at the weekend after Easter to Karlsruhe.&nbsp;','<span style=\"font-size: 14.4px;\">You do have a soft spot for Akrocados? Soft shell and a hard core, that’s what our akrocados are made of. Avocado, pardon, akrocado’s sweet taste takes the center stage and and makes the hearts of fans and friends beat faster. Akrocados are full of fat, well the good kind, but also full of energy. So come and enjoy our new recipes!</span>','http://akrobatik.kleinkunst-ka.de/en/'),(100,'Acro-Share','2016-04-22 00:00:00','2016-04-25 00:00:00',1,' Murfreesboro, TN,  United States','An event for all acrobats to come learn, share, and enjoy everything about the acrobatic world. We will have AcroYoga, Tumbling, Cheerleading stunts, pyramids, Standing Acrobats, Hand balancers and much much more. ','<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18.2px; white-space: pre-wrap; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">An event for all acrobats to come learn, share, and enjoy everything about the acrobatic world. We will have AcroYoga, Tumbling, Cheerleading stunts, pyramids, Standing Acrobats, Hand balancers and much much more. This event is being held in a 20,000 sqft building with mats on every inch of it. It has in-ground trampolines r.e. fluff pits, spring floors, and everything!! It\'s an acrobats dream. This event will have many Certified AcroYoga teachers, as well as current and former cheerleaders, gymnasts, and circus folk to learn from. Come be a part of the Second AcroShare event. If you have ever wanted to learn Acroyoga, standing cheer stunts or tumbling now is the time. This event is appropriate for all levels; from brand new to the most experienced! \r\n\r\n\r\nthe scheduled times are:\r\nFriday April 22nd from 7-10pm \r\nSat April 23rd from 9-12:30 2-7\r\nsun June 21st from 9-12:30 2-6\r\n\r\nInvestment;\r\n\r\nWeekend Pass $125 for all three days!\r\nFriday only $40\r\nSaturday only $70 \r\nSunday only $60\r\nStudent discount and Certified teacher discount given with Valid college ID or confirmed training certification email acroshare@gmail.com for more info\r\n\r\n\r\nDo the math at full per day price it comes out to $9.20 an hour for amazing acobatic training thats INSANE!!!!!\r\n\r\nEven better at the three day rate its only $6.75 an hour so get your weekend pass today!!\r\n\r\nA short list of classes that will be offered below!\r\n\r\nHand balancing &amp; counterbalances \r\nL basing Whips &amp; Pops\r\n3 Person L basing \r\nWashing machines Level 1 Level 2 &amp; Level 3\r\nTumbling, Somersaults &amp; trampoline skills.\r\nStanding Hand 2 Hand and foot 2 hand \r\nStanding Acro high bird high side star and transitions.\r\nCo-ed partner Cheerleading stunts beginner to Advanced\r\nBasket tosses for acroyogis\r\nCheerleading pyramids for acroyogis\r\nThai massage &amp; therapeutic flying\r\n</span>','https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fevents%2F184718688527801%2F&usd=2&usg=AFQjCNGQJ55WJ7oojNKk5Zg7WiPQ6malNw'),(101,'Acro Israel Pre Convention Workshop ','2016-06-03 00:00:00','2016-06-04 00:00:00',1,'Tel-Aviv, Israel','Duo Die - advanced acro workshop ','<div>Caitlin and Dane (Duo-die) come from Sydney, Australia and have a serious love of partner acrobatics. Constantly working hard to refine techniques, their goal is to make skills look effortless. That, as you can imagine, takes a lot of dedication! As well as training and performances, they also enjoy coaching other aspiring acrobats.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Over the course of the two days, we will focus on physical preparation and conditioning for dynamic skills. We will be touching upon tempo, standing in hands, two high, hand to hand and Icarian pops. Students should be ready to work hard and learn new and efficient ways to train for dynamic partner acrobatics.</div>','http://www.acroisrael.com/#!pre-convention-workshop/q60sp'),(102,'Israel Acrobatics Convention','2016-06-09 00:00:00','2016-06-12 00:00:00',1,'Tel-Aviv, Israel','This is the 6th year we are having this event and it will be more fun than you can imagine! Once again, world-class teachers from around the globe are coming together, willing to share their expertise and play with you.','<div>We will have a wide variety of workshops (for absolute beginners up to professional level), plus music and dancing, performances, excellent food and wonderful company! The beautiful desert landscape will be all around us as inspiration.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>If you are planning to attend, you should register early as places are limited and we do expect to be sold out.</div><div>Register at the office of \"Adama\" by phone: +(972) 8 659 5190</div><div>or email them: info@adama.org</div><div>&nbsp;<br></div>','http://www.acroisrael.com/#!about-the-convention/wdtny'),(103,'Chiemsee Acrobatics','2016-06-05 00:00:00','2016-06-12 00:00:00',1,'Chiemsee, Germany','Fons from Holland is coming back to the Chiemsee to teach a 7-day Acrobatics Intensive! Fons is regarded as one of the key pillars of European acrobatics.','<h5 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: Sanchez, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Fons from Holland is coming back to the Chiemsee to teach a 7-day Acrobatics Intensive! Fons is regarded as one of the key pillars of European acrobatics. With over 30 years of experience he shares his immense skills in acrobatics with precision and humour&nbsp;<img src=\"http://maitri-yoga-chiemsee.de/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":-)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%; height: auto; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;His classes cover all levels from complete beginners to very advanced professional performers. With a limited class size you will receive individual attention. Each day willl begin with morning yoga (with Sophia and friends).</h5><h5 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: Sanchez, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">The things he is likely to cover are: Body awareness training Handstand training – whether you’re just beginning to balance, working on your pike-press, or on to a one-armer Spotting and catching partner acrobatic and tempo skills and MUCH more!</h5><h5 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: Sanchez, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">If you are thinking partner acrobatics is just for the young, agile and super fit, think again! Fons meets you where you are. Fons himself started training in acrobatics at the age of 36 and has been hooked ever since. A living example of how this physical practice can become a life long addiction.</h5><h5 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: Sanchez, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Arrival &amp; Departure: Plan to arrive in the evening on Sunday, June 5th 2016. We’ll gather for dinner and ”warm-up” in the sauna. Preliminary schedule Monday June 6th – Saturday June 11th: Yoga with Sophia from 7:45 – 8:45 a.m., Breakfast from 9 – 10 a.m., Acrobatics with Fons from 10 a.m. – 1 p.m., Lunch &amp; Break from 1 – 3 p.m., Acrobatics with Fons from 3 – 6 p.m. followed by dinner and playtime&nbsp;<img src=\"http://maitri-yoga-chiemsee.de/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":-)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; max-width: 100%; height: auto; background: transparent;\">&nbsp;Departure day (Sunday June 12th): Yoga with Sophia from 7:45 – 8:45 a.m., Breakfast from 9 – 10 a.m., Acrobatics with Fons from 10 a.m. – noon, noon – 1 p.m. cleanup, Lunch at 1 p.m.</h5><h5 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 10px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 16px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1em; font-weight: 500; font-family: Sanchez, Georgia, \'Times New Roman\', serif; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;</h5>','http://maitri-yoga-chiemsee.de/project/chiemsee-acrobatics/'),(104,'Partner Acrobatics Intensive','2016-07-04 00:00:00','2016-07-17 00:00:00',1,'Andalusia, Spain','Optional 1 or 2 week training at Cortijo Caseria Del Mercado-a small organic farm high in the Alpujarras mountains. ','<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; line-height: 1.1; color: rgb(71, 163, 216); margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 1.5em; padding: 0.5em; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Andalucia, Spain<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">7 or 15 days from July 4th to 17th, 2016</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Optional 1 or 2 week training at Cortijo Caseria Del Mercado-a small organic farm high in the Alpujarras mountains.&nbsp;<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"></p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">In our Partner Acrobatics programs we cover many different acrobatic disciplines including standing acrobatics, handstand training, washing machines, trio tricks, Icarian games and much more.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">This physical intensity is balanced out with our therapeutic sessions, which aim to heal and restore the body.</p><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(90, 90, 90); font-family: \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">This program will give you the chance to refine your Acro skills and to have loads of fun.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">You have the freedom to choose how many hours you spend on Acro vs Therapeutics.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\"></p><div><br></div>','http://partneracrobatics.com/program-15.php'),(105,'British Acro Convention','2016-08-11 00:00:00','2016-08-14 00:00:00',1,'Oxford, UK','The event is run by a community of acrobats for other acrobats, of every level.&nbsp;','<div>We run along similar lines to the Dutch Acrobatics Convention and other European events.</div><div><br></div><div>We have many great workshop leaders coming from the UK and all over the world. The festival is run by volunteers - everyone will be asked to help out to make it a great event.</div><div><br></div><div>Tickets are great value: from £180 (before June) for a 4 day event, accomodation and food! Space this year is limited to 200 people, make sure you are one of the first to register your interest now.</div><div><br></div><div>In order to keep costs down we are providing camping facilities or a scout hall. Other accomodation options are available nearby. Why not visit the World Heritage site of Oxford during your stay?</div>','http://britishacrobatics.org/'),(106,'Partner Acrobatics Teacher Training','2016-08-01 00:00:00','2016-08-28 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','Intensively train for four weeks, whilst learning the skills and tools to teach successful acro classes and workshops.','<div>Our Partner Acrobatics programs cover many different acrobatic disciplines including standing acrobatics, handstand training, washing machines, trio tricks, Icarian games and much more. This physical intensity is balanced out with our therapeutic sessions, which aim to heal and restore the body.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>At the heart of our training programs is the concept of sustainability – the use of proper alignment and the principles of sports science to increase performance and decrease the risk of pain and/or injury.&nbsp;</div><div>This element of our trainings is weaved into our Prehab program – a selection of exercises specifically aimed at promoting injury prevention, structural integration and correct movement technique for long term physical health and fitness. These include postural realignment exercises, resistance training and correct breathing techniques.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>We encourage and support our students in developing their own teaching style, based on the latest principals of neuroscience and motor learning and our own extensive teaching experience.<div><br></div><div>Check out the website for prerequisite info and prices etc</div>','http://partneracrobatics.com/program-tt.php'),(107,'French Acro Convention','2016-07-06 00:00:00','2016-07-16 00:00:00',1,'Ste-Eulalie-En-Born, France','International exchange and free training, &nbsp;as well as workshops with international teachers, mostly in partner-acrobatics, but also in other circus disciplines.','<div>This year, despite the new organizing team, the convention will be very alike the ones in the past years.</div><div><br></div><div>We have invited professional teachers to the festival, who will organise the daily workshops at &nbsp;different levels. The main orientation of the workshops will be partner acrobatics; but we will also plan workshops in other circus disciplines, such as dance-acrobatics and &nbsp;Thai-massage</div><div><br></div><div>Includes a canoeing day, a day at the sea, and a final show, a tradition for the French Acro!</div><div><br></div><div>For Whom</div><div><br></div><div>All interested adult acrobats (as well as children and adolescents) with at least 6 months of experience. There will be a maximum of 130 participants (app. 15 teachers, chiefs, organizers, 15 helpers, 80 adults and 10 adolescents / children).</div><div><br></div><div>A short but important note</div><div><br></div><div>We see ourselves as friends amongst friends who are glad to organise an event, but also naturally expect everyone to help with the everyday chores (especially as we are not making money through this gathering). As most of the work during the event will consist of shopping, cooking etc., we wish to spread these tasks evenly amongst the participants. In practice, this means that everyone elder that 15 years will be asked to help with food preparation or with washing up two times during the meeting. In our experience, work in the kitchen was always a very fun and communicative experience, so many people will probably want to help more than initially assigned</div><div><br></div><div>Provisional Daily Planning</div><div><br></div><div>We would like to keep the spirit of the convention the way Thorsten and Jasper have built it, so we are planning a very similar type of schedule as for the previous years..!</div><div><br></div><div>The schedule below is subject to a change. It will be adapted to the conditions, the requirements of the workshop teachers and the interests of the participants.</div><div>8:00 – 9:00 Yoga</div><div>8:30 – 10:00 Breakfast</div><div>9:30 – 10:00 Warm-up</div><div>10:00 – 10:30 Handstand training</div><div>10:45 – 12:15 Workshop block (app. 5 parallel offers at different levels and focuson basics)</div><div>12:15 – 13:45 &nbsp;Free training with a supervising teacher</div><div>13:45 – 15:00 Lunch/Buffet</div><div>15:00 – 16:30 Midday-Break</div><div>16:45 – 18:45 Workshop block (app. 5 parallel offers at different levels and focuson basics)</div><div>19:00 – 20:15 Warm dinner</div><div>20:15 – 21:15 Thai-Massage</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>For “normal participants”: €480 per adult (17 years and above). This includes food, workshops and camping in an own tent.</div><div><br></div><div>There is an extra fee for participants wishing to stay with their camper van/caravan/mobile home on the campsite. Please contact us for that in advance.</div><div><br></div><div>In case you are bringing kids or teenagers with you, please contact us for special prices.</div><div>For daily pass: €70 includes: one night in your tent, 3 meals and a day of workshops</div><div><br></div><div>For “helpers”(18 years and above): €240 Only people staying the whole time could be helpers! “Helpers” will be called upon during the convention to work 8 shifts of 3-4 hours and have to join the ﬁrst meeting on the 6th of July, 11 am.</div>','https://frenchacro.wordpress.com'),(108,'International Acro Convention','2016-07-23 00:00:00','2016-07-30 00:00:00',1,' Beek, Netherlands','<div>The purpose of the festival is to help the sport of acrobatics to spread throughout the world.</div><div><br></div>','<div>The way we do this is by holding a convention every year for all acrobats; beginners to advanced.&nbsp;</div><div>We are open to allround acrobats as well as freetime acrobats, hand-to-hand, arial, acro-yoga and other variations of the theme.&nbsp;</div><div>We started in Croatia, and went via France, Sweden, Denmark, Italy, Hungary to Finland this year</div><div>We are moving the festival from country to country every year in an attempt to make sure every acrobat on this globe gets to have a change to participate at least once in a lifetime without having to travel half the world.&nbsp;</div><div>Ofcoarse it\'s also nice to go to unknown places that are touristic or otherwise interesting to make a longer stay possible.&nbsp;</div><div>Meanwhile we hope our influence on the local acrobatic-scene(s) is big enough to make a prolongation possible for a local festival, so we can move on to another country or region. &lt;...&gt;</div><div>See you there soon!</div>','http://www.acrobatics.nl '),(109,'AcroYoga Fest Divine Play','2016-10-07 00:00:00','2016-10-09 00:00:00',1,'Portland, OR, United States','You are invited to the 7th Annual AcroYoga Fest aka: Divine Play in Portland, Oreogn.&nbsp;','<div><br></div><div>the 3 day tickets for Friday-Sunday are on Sale at $250 now until March 31st - ( There will be 16 Friday Day Long Choices, you will get to pick yours in May )</div><div><br></div><div>http://tickets.acroyoga.org/event/AcroYogaFestPortlandOregon</div><div><br></div><div>after that the price will go up to $350 with the complete schedule and details May 1st&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Pre-Festival tickets will go on sale May 1st and we will offer a combo ticket to include the full week long event,&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>This year we will have 60,000 square feet of AcroYoga space!&nbsp;</div>','http://tickets.acroyoga.org/event/AcroYogaFestPortlandOregon'),(110,'Acro Revolution Teacher Training','2016-06-18 00:00:00','2016-07-01 00:00:00',1,'Hawaii, USA','<div>A 13 day residential teacher training that consists of intensive instruction in L-base acrobatics with a focus on skills including; washing machines, foot to hand, hand to hand, whips, pops, and other circus monkey tricks.&nbsp;</div>','<div>In addition to learning techniques to fully embody this practice, you will learn how to teach partner acrobatics at various levels. The restorative practice of Acropeutics will be incorporated to create a more sustainable acrobatic practice and to help facilitate connection and community. In addition to the physical skills, training will include multiple sessions on teaching methodology, the ‘business’ of being an acro teacher, best practices for social media promotion, and community facilitation. All material presented will be taught by using progressions and method based teaching practices. You will come out of this training equipped to not only teach acrobatics, but with the knowledge to train intelligently, heal yourself, and support your community.</div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: center;\"><br></span></div><div>The top 3 goals for the student are:</div><div><br></div><div>1. &nbsp;Graduates will be able to teach L- base acro</div><div><br></div><div>2. &nbsp;Gain knowledge and have the tools to have a sustainable teaching practice</div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">3. &nbsp;Get self experience in order to fully embody a practice based on safety and healthy communication</span></div><div><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: center;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">To learn more about the training and apply go to http://acrorevolution.com</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</span></div>','http://acrorevolution.com'),(111,'ACROATIA Croatia Acrobatic Festival','2016-08-01 00:00:00','2016-08-07 00:00:00',1,'Karlova?ka, Croatia','Be ready to enjoy workshops with an international teaching crew, acrobatics, handstands, yoga, therapy, good food, nice people, beautiful nature and much more.','<div>TEACHERS &amp; ARTISTS confirmed so far:</div><div>Kirsty Stuart &amp; Acro Bart, Lokke Gennissen &amp; Roos de Groen ,Maja Turčić, Luka Agreš,...</div><div><br></div><div>We are so looking forward to share and to accommodate playfulness of acrobatics, joy of movement, yoga mornings, therapy evenings, and lots of small things in between ;)</div><div><br></div><div>Save the date and be a part of it, places are limited, so make sure that you are among them.</div><div><br></div><div>LOCATION:</div><div>Gornji Zvečaj bb, Gornji Zvečaj, Karlovačka, Croatia</div><div><br></div><div>Prices:</div><div>Early bird price (before 1 April 2016)</div><div>€310 for the whole festival</div><div>€250 price for Balkan region</div><div><br></div><div>After early bird ( from 1 April 2016)</div><div>€350 for the whole festival</div><div>€270 for people from Balkan region</div><div><br></div><div>What you get for your money:&nbsp;</div><div>- the price includes program, all workshops, plentiful vegetarian food, rafting and amazing camping place in nature next to even more amazing river</div><div><br></div><div>Registration:</div><div>If you would like to come, to secure a place you need to send us the following registration information:</div><div>Please fill this form:</div><div>https://goo.gl/CN8Bpo</div><div><br></div><div>We will confirm the price and send you the payment details. Your place will be secure once you have paid.</div><div><br></div><div>Mail for information &amp; additional questions:</div><div>e-mail: info@acroatia.org</div><div><br></div><div>Participants will be accommodate in nice cosy wooden huts.</div><div>You can see some pictures of the location here:</div><div>https://goo.gl/h5fn0t</div><div><br></div><div>Much Smiles,</div><div>Acroatia team:</div><div>Maja &amp; Luka</div><div><br></div><div>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; ☺☺☺☺☺ &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;</div><div><br></div><div>How to get to the Acroatia location:</div><div>Venue: Robinson camp Sound &amp; Vision</div><div>Address: Gornji Zvečaj bb, Gornji Zvečaj, Karlovačka, Croatia</div><div><br></div><div>closest airport: Zagreb International Airport</div><div>There is an airport bus which is going to centre. 12km distance, half an hour ride.</div><div>closest train station: Gornji Zvečaj</div><div><br></div><div>There is a train from Zagreb Main Train Station to Gornji Zvečaj approximately every two hours.</div><div><br></div><div>Croatian railways website:</div><div>http://www.hzpp.hr/en</div><div><br></div><div>If you have any questions don’t hesitate to contact us.</div><div>e-mail: info@acroatia.org</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/187277771631280/'),(112,'AcroYoga Teacher Training','2016-07-05 00:00:00','2016-07-31 00:00:00',1,'Montreal, Canada','<div>Acroyoga Montreal Teacher Training&nbsp;</div><div>The art of teaching acroyoga with Jessie Goldberg, Eugene Poku and guest teachers.</div><div>4 weeks of physical reintegration, mental sharpening, emotional awakening and remembered wisdom. Come back to the source, Montréal the birth place of acroyoga.</div>','<div>This is a month long Acro Yoga Teacher Training Intensive, we are looking for participants that have experience in Acro Yoga so we can focus our time on sharing the art of teaching acrobatics with a yogic consciousness, moving well beyond the fundamentals.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Yoga is a fun filled yet serious practice with the potential to reconnect us to our inner child. The participatory, interactive and self-affirming energy of the Acro Yoga practice unites likeminded people from different walks of life. It has many practical and therapeutic applications both in the Acro Yoga community and the world at large.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Acro Yoga’s potential for dealing and helping people cope with trust issues is boundless since the root of the Acro Yoga practice is trust and acceptance. Acro yoga cannot exist without this bond and understanding between practitioners. As Acro Yoga teachers we must be present, to ensure a safe and nurturing environment for our Acro Yoga students.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The mastery of the technique in our own Acro Yoga practice is the foundation we draw on for teaching Acro Yoga. How to communicate verbally and physically to our students the inner &amp;outer experience are the skills we will explore in this Acro Yoga Teacher Training Intensive.</div><div><br></div>','http://acroyoga.com/teacher-training/1'),(113,'AcroYoga Teacher Training','2016-12-05 00:00:00','2016-12-18 00:00:00',1,'Tuscon, AZ, USA','<div>The art of teaching acroyoga with &nbsp;Jessie Goldberg , Eugene Poku , &nbsp;Natalie Nguyen &nbsp;and &nbsp;Jill Campbell . 2 weeks of physical reintegration, mental sharpening, emotional awakening, community building and remembered wisdom.</div><div><br></div>','<div>This is a two week long Level 1 Acro Yoga Teacher Training Intensive in the style of Acroyoga Montreal. It can stand alone as your Level 1 teaching certification, or will qualify you to take the Level 2 Acro Yoga Teacher Training offered in Montreal each July.</div><div><br></div><div>This Acro Yoga teacher training intensive will give participants the tools to teach the fundamentals of Acro Yoga Montreal including yoga, acrobatics, partner body balancing; intro to seamless and dynamic Acro Yoga transitions and the creative process of Acro Yoga Montreal.</div>','http://acroyoga.com/acroyoga-mtl-teacher-training-in-tucson,-arizonia/210'),(114,'AcroYoga Teacher Training','2016-10-17 00:00:00','2016-11-01 00:00:00',1,'Guadalajara, Mexico','Join us for 15-days of learning, embodiment, community and practice on how to teach the AYI curriculum in a safe and fun way. This training will be hosted at the beautiful Chalananda retreat site just outside of Guadalajara.','<div>With Bonnie Argo and Mimi Nunez, Jason Nemer will be there for part of the training as well.</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;We have been at Chalananda for many trainings and we love it. &nbsp;Housing options include camping, clamping, shared and private rooms. Prices range from $3000-$4200 USD. Tuition covers: 10+ hours a day of instruction, AYI Teacher Training manual, 3 vegetarian/vegan meals each day and lodging.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>','http://www.acroyoga.org/teacher-training'),(115,'Partner Acrobatics Intensive ','2017-01-03 00:00:00','2017-01-16 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','2 weeks intensive training, handstands, standing acro, sequences and washing machines, general shenanigans and much more!','more info soon-the program will be comparable to our July intensive in Spain','http://partneracrobatics.com'),(116,'Extreme Convention','2016-04-08 00:00:00','2016-04-10 00:00:00',1,'Antwerp, Belgium','At Extreme Convention, we practice contemporary and extreme circus and acrobatics techniques in a rather interactive way. For three days, circus devotees of all levels can participate in different workshops, initiated by many skillful artists.','<div>EXTREME CONVENTION, THIS MEANS WORKSHOPS IN DIFFERENT KINDS OF EXPLOSIVE CIRCUS TECHNIQUES FOR BEGINNERS&nbsp;</div><div>AS WELL AS ADVANCED STUDENTS, BY HIGHLY QUALIFIED ARTISTS AND TRAINERS.</div><div>ARE YOU A CIRCUS ADDICT? SEARCHING FOR A WAY TO BRIGHTEN YOUR KNOWLEDGE AND TECHNIQUE?</div><div>THEN, WITHOUT A DOUBT, EXTREME CONVENTION IS YOUR PLACE TO BE!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>WORKSHOPS 2016</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>HAND TO HAND - TEETERBOARD - FLOOR ACROBATICS - CHINESE POLE - HAND BALANCING TISSUE - CYR WHEEL - GERMAN WHEEL - AIR TRACK JUGGLING - TRAPEZE - TRAMPOLINE - AND MANY MORE...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>DOWNLOAD THE OVERVIEW OF THIS YEARS WORKSHOPS A FEW DAYS BEFORE THE FESTIVAL ON THE WEBSITE OR ON FACEBOOK,</div><div>MAKE YOUR PLANNING, AND BRING IT TO EXTREME!</div>','http://extremeconvention.be/extreme/en/index.html'),(117,'Frankfurt Acro Convention','2016-04-22 00:00:00','2016-04-24 00:00:00',1,'Frankfurt, Germany','Sorry the festival is full! There is a waiting list','<div>Start Friday 6 p.m., End Sunday 3 p.m.</div><div>Place : 63128 Dietzenbach (near Frankfurt), Philip-Fenn-Halle, Rodgaustr. 1.&nbsp;</div><div>As usual you receive our full-convenience-service including:&nbsp;</div><div>Sleeping in the gym (don´t forget to bring your sleeping bag and -mats) or Van. (Tents are not possible!)&nbsp;</div><div>Food : almost around the clock &nbsp;</div><div>free mineral water, coffee &amp; tea and workshops, games, party, fun...</div><div>Massage is available (sorry, not for free...;o)</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Deadline for enrollment is April 6. Who enrolls after that, wants definitely to do a little volunteer helping job on the festival, great!</div><div><br></div><div>Please enroll quickly, for our space is limited!</div><div>Participants from other countries can pay cash at arrival, but have to enroll before, too.</div><div>WORKSHOPS: Offer a workshop and maybe improve your odds on the waitinglist..</div><div>SHOW: Your act ist wanted!! :o) It´s worth it! Look under „the Show“</div><div>We’re looking forward to see you !&nbsp;</div><div>The Orga-Team and all frankfurt acrobats</div>','http://www.akrobatik.info/Akrobatikfestival_Frankfurt/General.html'),(118,'Irish Acro Convention','2016-05-20 00:00:00','2016-05-22 00:00:00',1,'Dublin, Ireland','You are cordially invited to the first irish acrobatics convention. Based in the idyllic Cellbridge, 15 minutes outside the city centre of Dublin, this is a weekend of intensive acrobatic workshops instructed by international teachers.&nbsp;','<div>&nbsp;Additional features include sauna, bar, shower facilities and homecooked meals not forgetting all workshops held in a big top circus tent. Camping provided on site in beautiful wooded garden, a nice countryside getaway for any city dwelling acrobat. Focus is on Partner acrobatics and we will cater for both beginners and seasoned acrobats.</div><div><br></div><div>Ticket prices is €80 for the weekend including camping, all workshops and meals provided. Not forgetting a renegade/open stage/ party on saturday evening.</div><div><br></div><div>If interested please fill out the registration form (follow the link below). As places for the convention work first come first served basis.</div><div><br></div><div>Teachers:&nbsp;</div><div>Bart Venne (Acro Bart)</div><div>Jonah McGreevey</div><div>Judith Groot &amp; Leander van de Visse</div><div><br></div><div>Register to secure your spot:</div><div><br></div><div>http://goo.gl/forms/HYVkmTlXv1</div><div><br></div><div>Hope to see you there!</div><div>Aileen and Henrik</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/955173241185527/'),(119,'EJC-European Juggling Convention','2016-07-30 00:00:00','2016-08-07 00:00:00',1,'Almere, Netherlands','The biggest juggling event in Europe. Professional jugglers, street performers and amateur jugglers from all over the world travel to this festival to juggle, exchange tricks and have fun together. The convention takes place in a different place in Europe each year.&nbsp;','There are three large sports halls (4892 m²) and a swimming pool surrounded by a spacious site that includes a campsite and a festival village. The site is conveniently located right next to the train station Almere Poort, at approximately half an hour train ride from Amsterdam and Schiphol airport (Airport of Amsterdam). To top it all off, there is a lake with a beach within walking distance of the festival site! Who is the convention for? For everyone! The programme includes activities for jugglers and circus enthusiasts of all ages and all levels. There are beginners’ workshops as well as special master classes at an advanced level. The programme is filled with world-class shows and performances. There will be a special slackline area, a gym for acrobatics and aerial, a fire spot and of course a lot of space to juggle! Even for non-jugglers there is plenty to do, and by the end of the convention they may have become jugglers too! Who is organising the EJC 2016? The EJC is organised by an enthusiastic team of Dutch jugglers who have founded the European Juggling Convention 2016 Foundation. They are looking forward to welcoming you and thousands of other jugglers to Almere in the summer of 2016 to make it an amazing festival!','http://www.ejc2016.org'),(120,'First Austrian Acrobatics Convention','2016-08-05 00:00:00','2016-08-14 00:00:00',1,'Ebbs, Austria','The (F)AAC is the First Austrian Acrobatic Convention, organized by Kreativsport. The aim of the convention is the exchange of partner acrobatic skills at all levels with the help of international teachers.','<div>Costs</div><div><br></div><div>€ 490, - adult 2 bed room apartment (private bathroom &amp; kitchen) (SOLD OUT!)</div><div>€ 440, - adult 2 bed room (common bathroom) (SOLD OUT!)</div><div>€ 440, - adult dormitory (common bathroom)</div><div>€ 380, - adult in vans or camper (common bathroom)</div><div>Reductions of prices for children/helpers:</div><div><br></div><div>0-4 year olds - free</div><div>5-9 year olds - minus € 250,-</div><div>10-15 year olds - minus € 150,-</div><div>helpers - minus € 140,-</div><div>The participation fee is per person and includes 9 nights in a 2 bed room apartment with private bathrooms or a dormitory/bed room with a common bathroom. There is the possibility to sleep in your own van, mobile home or camp and use the common bathrooms. The fee also includes food and drinks, acrobatic workshops and free training with teachers’ support, and common activities. As the convention should be a collective experience, every participant is asked to help 2 times during the convention (e.g., cooking, shopping, washing up,…)</div><div><br></div><div>Helpers: There are 6 “helper” jobs. To be a helper means to work 8 shifts of 3-4 hours during the convention. That means that you can’t participate in all workshops. If you are interested please contact us.</div><div><br></div><div>Cancellation policy</div><div><br></div><div>We will take a cancelation fee of € 20,- when cancelling your registration before May 31, 2016. After that we cannot promise to give back your commission, but we will try to find someone from the waiting list. There is no reduction of the participation fee if you cannot stay for the whole convention.</div><div><br></div><div>Risk and liability</div><div><br></div><div>The participation and training at the (F)AAC is at your own risk. We do not take any legal responsibility for accidents and property damage at the compound. There is also no liability for the loss or theft of any valuables. Persons under the age of 18 who are not accompanied by an adult require a signed authorization from their legal guardian.</div>','http://www.kreativsport.at'),(121,'Edinburgh Aerial and Acrobatics Convention','2016-09-09 00:00:00','2016-09-11 00:00:00',1,'Edinburgh, Scotland','Now in its tenth year, EAAC is a 3 day aerial and acro convention and is the UK’s largest event of its kind with over 250 workshops!&nbsp;','It brings together individuals and groups from all over the world wishing to expand their existing practice through a wide range of disciplines. Workshops are led by world class performers and teachers who are passionate about passing on their skills and techniques. We have workshops for absolute beginners all the way to advanced workshops for professional performers This year’s convention is bigger and better than ever as we have invited some of the highest standards of professional artists to run our workshops that we have ever seen. We have a huge range of Workshops on offer and EAAC is a great opportunity to try out new skills that you may never before had the chance to! Alongside classes in Yoga, Flexibility, Trapeze, Hoop and Silks, you will also have the chance to do Bungee Trapeze, Teeterboard, Russian bars, Cyr Wheel… and much more!&nbsp;','http://eaac.info'),(122,'Akrobatik Bremen','2016-10-06 00:00:00','2016-10-09 00:00:00',1,'Bremen, Germany','Your typical hardcore German Acro Convention','<br>','http://www.akrobatik-bremen.de/acrobatics-bremen-english/'),(123,'AcroVenture Retreat','2016-09-10 00:00:00','2016-09-17 00:00:00',1,'Istria, Croatia','More than thirty-five hours of body movement will be happening in a unique and secluded location. In the midst of endless hectares of olive groves we will find shelter in 200-year-old, newly renovated farmhouses','<div>About the Practice:</div><div>This venture will offer you a wide range of playful elements, including important principals of open play, acrobatics, L-basing, partner-acro, acroyoga, dutch &amp; israeli flows, washing machines, monkey business, contact improv, axis syllabus, acronatomy and much, much more. The heart of this week will be about cultivating trust, strength and flexibility, within ourselves and as a community of dedicated movement lovers.</div><div>Daily routine:</div><div>08:00-09:30 Movement Feast</div><div>09:30-11:00 Breakfast</div><div>11:00-13:00 AcroYoga &amp; L-Basing</div><div>13:00-16:00 Lunch &amp; Siesta</div><div>16:00-18:00 Partner Acrobatics &amp; Contactro</div><div>18:00-20:00 Bodywork &amp; Yin Time</div><div>20:00-21:00 Dinner</div><div>21:00-22:00 Community Time</div><div><br></div><div>Following a variety of morning movement improvements, we will build up the day with an important skill set where each individual will find their level and achievement goals. The integration and focus on handstands, inversions and hand-to-hand training will be as important as the oxygen we breathe daily. The afternoons will be packed with another acro session where you will find yourself in the weirdest and most loving moments of your life. Followed by a calm, fluid and connective bodywork practice, we will finish the day with a delicious dinner and a sunset on the roof garden.</div><div><br></div><div><div>What can you expect to learn?</div><div>-Basic &amp; advanced techniques</div><div>-Flow, rhythm &amp; body language</div><div>-Choreography &amp; the freedom of flow</div><div>-Partner work, calibrations &amp; progressions</div><div>-30 minutes of individual 1 on 1 movement &amp; postural refinement</div><div>-Endless fun with international teachers from all around the globe</div><div>Your AcroVenture Team 2016:</div><div><br></div><div>Ishine Gape: is well known for his dynamic, humorous and at the same time profound teaching. He is a trained massage therapist, yoga and acrobatics teacher, social worker and globetrotter and has been working in the field of bodywork for more than 10 years. Gape is the owner of barefootyoga.me and spreads his love for movement and teamwork all over Austria and Europe. When Gape isn’t hosting one of his barefootyoga.me retreats, you will most definitely find him behind the lens of a camera, or somewhere on a tree, representing the local monkeys. His goal is to lead people back into a life filled with joy and lightness. He believes that the only way into a valuable, free and sustainable life is to recognise the value of community and the confrontation on every level. www.barefootyoga.me</div><div><br></div><div>Emily Baxter: is dedicated to sharing and teaching whatever she can to inspire freedom in people. A bit of a jack of all trades, she teaches and practices several styles of Yoga asana, including Hatha, Yin, Vinyasa as well as AcroYoga and Slackline Yoga. After discovering AcroYoga Emily pursued Acrobatics and loves the challenges and fears that the practice brings up then breaks through. She teaches anatomy, methodology and adjustments on Astanga Vinyasa Teacher Trainings with Tribe Yoga. She is also trained as a Postural Therapist. Emily has always had a passion for movement and body awareness. This coupled with her strong background in anatomy manifests in her teachings as clear, precise, thoughtful instruction. She continues to study, travel, teach, play and laugh wherever she may find herself. www.specialblendyoga.com</div><div><br></div><div>Yaeli Margalit: Israeli born, Irish bred, and well-travelled vagabond, Yaeli is a mishmash of all things fun and playful. She is an experienced body mover, clinical massage therapist and professional acro monkey. Having spent her early twenties in the world of academia, she abandoned her medical lab coat and decided what she wanted most in this life was to move her body, give and receive massage and follow the sun. Currently living in Dublin, Yaeli teaches yoga and Contact Improvisation Dance. Combining all her movement and healing loves, she hosts regular AcroPlayShops, with her best buddy Cian. Drawing from the principles and practices of Contact Improv they create curious, fun and inviting ways of exploring partnered acrobatics. Ultimately her wish in life is to be a good friend and a good clown.</div><div><br></div><div>Cian O Reilly: Cian spent his childhood dreaming about playing in the circus but dared not tell anyone lest they tell him that’s ridiculous. After completing much of society’s regular assigned ‘Life To-Do’s, such as university and a 9-5 day job, Cian completed a year in an Irish school of Performing Arts, where he was told he was a terrible actor but a good clown. Thus, he went to train and work in Belfast Circus School, specialising in aerial dance, acrobatics, juggling and being a good friend. He subsequently ran away from the circus to learn how to integrate such hard-core body punishing acrobatics into juicier, healthier more yogically-aligned movement fun. He’s now living in Dublin teaching handstand workshops to yoga teachers, co-facilitating AcroPlayShops with Yaeli and contemplating life’s important questions like – what is the stars?</div><div><br></div><div>The price includes:</div><div>6 x Lodging (please bring your own tent if you chose the tent option)</div><div>3 warm vegetarian meals a day</div><div>8 hours of teachings daily</div><div>Holiday and training all rolled into a juicy package</div><div>Meeting true friends for life</div><div><br></div><div>Prices: www.barefootyoga.me/registration-av</div><div>(Attention: There is a limited number of early bird tickets. If they are sold the price automatically changes to the late bird price!)</div><div><br></div><div>Directions:</div><div>Stancija Negrin d.o.o.</div><div>Negrin 56, HR 52215 Vodnjan</div><div><br></div><div>By Car:</div><div>Graz – Istria 4:25 h</div><div>Vienna – Istria 6:00 h</div><div>Munich – Istria 6:00 h</div><div><br></div><div>By Plane:</div><div>Nearest Airport is Pula or Rovinj / Pick Up &amp; Shuttle Service from the airport available for €10.-</div><div><br></div><div>Looking for a ride? Post your inquiry on our facebook event page “barefootyoga.me – AcroVenture Retreat”</div><div><br></div><div>Extras:</div><div>We are looking for volunteers who support our kitchen crew during the upcoming retreats. For more information click here: http://www.barefootyoga.me/?page_id=2637</div><div>/?page_id=2637</div><div><br></div><div>Email: info@barefootyoga.me</div><div>Facebook: www.facebook.com/barefootyoga.me</div></div>','http://barefootyoga.me/en/barefootyoga-me-acroventure-retreat-10-17-september-2016/'),(124,'AcroColors','2016-11-11 00:00:00','2016-11-18 00:00:00',0,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">Refresh and Refine: &nbsp;This training is suitable for Beginners to Intermediate acro practitioners who are looking to refresh and refine their acro skills, as well as learning something new.</span></div>','<div>United for the first time to offer you a unique and fun acro experience, six Partner Acrobatics teachers: Kendra Charts, Francis Tabin, Kelly Thayer, Roj Sangkasaba, ZsaZsa Mak &amp; Emily Baxter, along with guest teachers, are coming together.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">You\'ll get the tools to transform your acrobatic skills and expand your creativity with the practice!</span></div><div><br></div><div>A ONE WEEK long ACRO intensive training in gorgeous Kaomai Lanna resort with a wonderful training facility in beautiful Chiangmai province, (AKA) the rose of northern Thailand.</div><div><br></div><div>http://www.kaomailanna.com/</div><div><br></div><div>This training is suitable for Beginners to Intermediate acro practitioners who are looking to refresh and refine their acro skills, as well as learning something new.</div><div><br></div><div>You will learn how to create a flow of your own showing yourself and skills through the creative process. Best of all you will leave this training with a smooth acro flow of your own!</div><div><br></div><div>Gain crisp fundamentals and do what you want to be able to do with acro moves and clear spotting. Also, you\'ll improve your training through conditioning and gain strength to prevent injuries and have more fun.</div><div><br></div><div>AcroColors gives you an authentic taste of Thai culture, flavors, textures, experiences and colors to awaken your senses. Inspire innovation and celebrate connection of the country &amp; worldwide community, making delicious discoveries and feeding your mind.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>TRAINING COVERS:&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>- Morning conditioning: prehab movements, gymnastics or yoga to prep you through active day</div><div><br></div><div>- L basing foundations: poses, transitions, mounts and dismounts</div><div><br></div><div>- Inversions: headstands, handstands &amp; prep exercises&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>- Slackro: Dual balance combining slackline and acro techniques</div><div><br></div><div>- Creating a flow or short performance of your own&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>- Costume making: why not make your acro colorful &amp; fun with what you wear!!&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>- Trios + group acro: make beautiful acro shapes with three or more people</div><div><br></div><div>- Standing acrobatics and counterbalance foundations</div><div><br></div><div>- Acro consult with one of the coaches from the teaching team</div><div><br></div><div>- Jam time!</div><div><br></div><div>- Therapeutics and rest time: its good to also rest and let yourselves be pampered</div><div><br></div><div>*** This training will also prep your skill levels &amp; to help you meet the prerequisites for Partner- Acrobatics Intensive trainings.</div><div><br></div><div>TRAINING INCLUDES</div><div><br></div><div>- 7 nights of double accommodation at Kaomai Lanna resort&nbsp;</div><div>- Approximate 5 hrs of acro class time per day&nbsp;</div><div>- Other movement and creative classes</div><div>- Buffet breakfast, lunch and dinner - mostly vegetarian with one meat dish + yummy local treats!!</div><div>- An excursion or authentic Thai cooking session or Thai massage with #acrofoodie tour!</div><div>- 360° Open Meditation/Yoga Room</div><div>- Restaurant and Bar for extra yummies and fresh coconuts</div><div>- Big swimming pool&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>(Single accommodation extra. Airfare &amp; transfer NOT included.)</div><div><br></div><div>PRICES:&nbsp;</div><div>Deposit: $350 USD to secure your spot!</div><div><br></div><div>$1450 USD Full price</div><div>$1150 USD paid by August 15th (Early Bird)</div><div><br></div><div>SIGN UP NOW at https://goo.gl/jWqvVJ</div><div><br></div><div>Discounts</div><div>10% Discount for the following:</div><div>- Couple or partnership&nbsp;</div><div>- Thai residents&nbsp;</div><div>- If you are planning to and committed to join Partner-Acrobatics - Thailand Intensive 2017</div><div>** Please email acrocolorsinfo@gmail.com for discount prices and additional info.</div>',''),(125,'AYM Immersion','2016-10-24 00:00:00','2016-10-28 00:00:00',0,'Madrid, Spain','<div>European AcroYoga Montreal “Acro Expressions”</div><div>For intermediate &amp; advanced practitioners.</div><div>We are happy to announce one of the first AcroYoga Montreal intensive trainings in Europe.</div><div><br></div>','<div>This 5–day immersion is based on AcroYoga Montreal’s principals, techniques and skills, offered in a constructive and progressive way, by several experienced and certified teachers from Europe.</div><div><br></div><div>The characteristics of the Montreal style are ‘AcroYoga flow, slow core controlled movements, creativity, acrobatics with yogic consciousness, out of the box thinking’, precise and safe spotting.</div><div><br></div><div>This training is open for intermediate and advanced AcroYoga practitioners, and is offered to deepen and expand your practice as a base, flyer and spotter. It is also a good preparation for upcoming AcroYoga Montreal Teacher Training in Europe and in Canada.</div><div><br></div><div>You will rediscover &amp; improve your core through yoga, workouts, group training and a lot of acro. Redefine, refine &amp; deepen your acro techniques: learning first to move slow &amp; controlled in order to open a door to a wider range of possibilities. You will definitely discover original AcroYoga Montreal material, presented in a constructive &amp; progressive way. For example: counter and contra balance, supported handstands, (supported) back bending, shoulder stand and handstand presses, AcroYoga flow, arts of movement, contact improvisation and more, under a dedicated spotting.</div><div><br></div><div>Besides the technical approach, you will learn how to think from a creative point of view - thinking ‘out of the box’; how to create a flow, how to give your practice more personality, how to connect with your partner, communicate, switching roles, stepping out of your comfort zone.</div><div><br></div><div>• TEACHERS</div><div>Ruslan Khalilov &amp; Saar Wouters from AcroContactYoga.com, the founders of AcroYoga Antwerp (BE), are among leading AcroYoga teachers in Belgium. Inspired &amp; certified by AcroYoga Montreal founders: Eugene Poku &amp; Jessie Goldberg.</div><div>Co - teachers: Sebastien AY from Strasbourg (FR) &amp; Maša Nobilo (Luxembourg)</div><div><br></div><div>• PREREQUISITES:</div><div>YOGA:</div><div>- Chaturanga Dandasana hold: full plank min 3 breathes, with knees on the ground min 5 breathes</div><div>- Utkatasana followed by a transition to Navasana: minimum 3 transitions combined with min 3 beathes hold for each position</div><div>- Stable tripod headstand min 30 seconds PLUS min 3 Pike presses or 5 Straddle Pike presses</div><div>- Handstands with a spotter min 30 seconds hold: standing AND spotting</div><div><br></div><div>ACROYOGA:</div><div>- Back Bird plank hold min 15 seconds + min 3 presses (basing AND flying)</div><div>- Front Bird Workout min 5 times (basing OR flying). Explanation: Front Bird -&gt; Base sets feet under the knee caps of the flyer -&gt; Flyer does tuck and back to straight</div><div>- Stable Side Star min 20 seconds + Straddle Bat Tic Tocs min 3 times (basing OR flying)</div><div>- Stable Free Shoulder hold min 30 seconds (basing OR flying)</div><div>- Stable Star hold min 30 seconds (basing AND flying)</div><div>- Stable Tuck Sit hold: min 10 seconds OR min 15 seconds with Flyer\'s feet on Base\'s knees (basing OR flying)</div><div>- Barrel Rolls (basing OR flying)</div><div><br></div><div>PREREQUISITES VIDEO will be available soon.</div><div><br></div><div>• DAY &amp; TIME:</div><div>24 - 28 October 2016&nbsp;</div><div>From 9.00 till 17:45</div><div><br></div><div>• DAILY PROGRAM:</div><div>9.00 - 11.00 Warm Up</div><div>11.00 – 11.15 Short Break</div><div>11.15 – 13.15 AcroYoga</div><div>13.00 – 15.00 Lunch Break</div><div>15.00 – 17.45 AcroYoga</div><div><br></div><div>• PLACE TO BE:</div><div>Madrid, Spain. More info soon.</div><div><br></div><div>• PRICES:</div><div>EARLY BIRD before 1st of October 2016</div><div>410€ all 5 days</div><div>270€ only 1st 3 days</div><div>190€ only 1st 2 days</div><div><br></div><div>LATE BIRD after 1st of October 2016</div><div>450€ all 5 days</div><div>300€ only 1st 3 days</div><div>210 only 1st 2 days</div><div><br></div><div>• REGISTRATION &amp; CONTACT INFORMATION:</div><div>AcroContactYoga@gmail.com</div><div><br></div><div>Learn more about AcroYoga Montreal, it\'s founders, team and principles</div><div>https://acroyoga.com/about-us</div><div><br></div><div>Learn more about AcroContactYoga and it\'s teachers</div><div>http://www.acrocontactyoga.com/#!about/y0ufv</div><div><br></div><div>• FULL TEAM:</div><div>Saar Wouters &amp; Ruslan Khalilov – AcroContactYoga (Antwerp, Belgium)</div><div>Sebastien AY (Strasbourg, France) &amp; Maša Nobilo (Luxembourg)</div><div><br></div><div>With acro regards and looking forward to meet you all on the mats!</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/814100738689611/'),(126,'Partner Acrobatics Intensive ','2017-06-08 00:00:00','2016-06-21 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','Optional 1 or 2 week training at Cortijo Caseria Del Mercado-a small organic farm high in the Alpujarras mountains.&nbsp;','<div>In our Partner Acrobatics programs we cover many different acrobatic disciplines including standing acrobatics, handstand training, washing machines, trio tricks, Icarian games and much more.</div><div>This physical intensity is balanced out with our therapeutic sessions, which aim to heal and restore the body.</div><div><br></div><div>This program will give you the chance to refine your Acro skills and to have loads of fun.</div><div>You have the freedom to choose how many hours you spend on Acro vs Therapeutics.</div>','http://partneracrobatics.com/program-15.php'),(127,'Partner Acrobatics Teacher Training','2017-08-01 00:00:00','2017-08-28 00:00:00',1,'Andalucia, Spain','Our Partner Acrobatics teacher training program offers an opportunity to intensively train for four weeks, whilst learning the skills and tools to teach successful acro classes and workshops.&nbsp;','<div>We encourage and support our students in developing their own teaching style, based on the latest principals of neuroscience and motor learning and our own extensive teaching experience.</div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Moreover plenty of time will be dedicated to improve your personal acrobatic practice. Some time will be dedicated to prepare public performances and work on the aesthetics of your acro moves. A minimum of six hours per week is dedicated to therapeutics to restore your body. Students have the option to focus their training and choose the amount of hours spent practicing acrobatics and/or therapeutics.</div>','http://partneracrobatics.com/program-tt.php'),(128,'Partner Acrobatics Intensive ','2017-11-06 00:00:00','2017-11-19 00:00:00',1,'Guadalajara, Mexico','<div><span style=\"font-size: 0.9em;\">An optional 1 or 2 week long Intensive Training in Partner Acrobatics.</span></div>','<div>PartnerAcrobatics.com Intensives are unique in that students get to create their own personal acro adventure. Simultaneous classes are offered daily, each with varying levels of acrobatic competency but all geared towards having students increase their own abilities. Higher level offerings will have separate pre-reqs that will need to be met in order to participate in the class, meaning that students will be able to work with other participants working on similar skill sets.</div>','http://partneracrobatics.com/program-am.php'),(129,'New Years Acro Retreat','2016-12-29 00:00:00','2017-01-01 00:00:00',1,'Olstead, Denmark','The level is intermediate to advanced. In most workshops you will be able to choose the advanced level or the intermediate level workshop, depending on your preferences and experience level.','<div>Enter 2017 feeling/flying higher than ever before.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>We are happy to invite you for this four day high level acro training with world class teacher Ellio Blox (Canada) and the Danish acro community core trio Julie, Peter and Emil.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The retreat takes place in a new, architecturally beautiful cabin by Roskilde Fjord. There is plenty of space to train indoors.</div><div><br></div><div>PRICES</div><div>Full experience - 29th December to 1st January: 2000 DKK (270 EUR)</div><div>Just here for the acro - 29th to 31st December: 1700 DKK (230 EUR)</div><div>Just here for the party - 31st December to 1st January: 600 DKK (80 EUR)</div><div>Accommodation and food is included. The meals are mostly vegetarian and organic.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Early Bird until 24th October (prices above)</div><div>Early Bat until 4th December (10 percent price increase)&nbsp;</div><div>Late High Flying Whale (20 percent price increase)&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>REGISTRATION</div><div>Sign up here: https://goo.gl/RRFJn1</div><div><br></div><div>There is room for up to 40 participants. There are also some extra spots available at a discount if you want to help in the kitchen, or if you want to join the Party Planning Committee. Contact Emil if you are interested in one of those options.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>PROGRAM&nbsp;</div><div>December 29th&nbsp;</div><div>12-13 arrival</div><div>13-14 lunch</div><div>15-18 acro workshop I</div><div>19-20 dinner</div><div>20-22 ice breaking and team building activities</div><div><br></div><div>December 30th</div><div>08.00-09.00 wake up workout / yoga&nbsp;</div><div>09.00-10.00 breakfast</div><div>10.30-13.00 acro workshop II</div><div>13.00-14.00 lunch</div><div>15.30-18.00 acro workshop III</div><div>19.00-20.00 dinner</div><div><br></div><div>December 31st&nbsp;</div><div>08.00-09.00 wake up workout / yoga&nbsp;</div><div>09.00-10.00 breakfast</div><div>10.30-13.00 acro workshop IV</div><div>13.00-14.00 lunch</div><div>15.00-16.00 departure/arrival if you\'re “only here for the acro” or “only here for the party”</div><div>16.00-18.00 acro workshop V (party edition)</div><div>19.00 NEW YEARS PARTY&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>January 1st&nbsp;</div><div>10.00-12.00 brunch</div><div>12.30-15.00 Acro workshop VI (hangover edition) OR cinema style film watching (also hangover edition)</div><div>15.00-16.00 lunch</div><div>17.00-18.00 departure.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>ABOUT US</div><div>Ellio Blox has nourished a lifelong fascination for peering over edges and discovering footholds in the unlikeliest of places. A full time world-traveling teacher with his company Blox Acrobatics, he offers quality instruction on a deep bag of tricks. Blox is a head coach of Pitch Catch Circus School of Acrobatics in Asheville, NC, is a member of the Partner Acrobatics teaching team on intensives and teacher trainings, and has performed partner acrobatics across North America and the Caribbean with his performing arts and production company, Acrodisiac. Rooted in many years of pedagogic study, acrobatics training under world-class teachers since 2010, and a commitment to health and happiness, Blox is a powerful resource for acrobatic advancement and personal growth.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Emil and Blox have trained together a lot during the Partner Acrobatics teacher training and advanced intensive (where Blox was teaching). Their friendship started in Thailand two years ago when they were roommates for a month during the teacher training.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Peter and Julie are two devoted acro-teachers who have been part of shaping the acroyoga-community in Copenhagen through their participation and teaching over three years. They embody an effortless practice, and they are always fun and inspiring company. Although they will take you far and deep in your practice, you won\'t find any of them taking Acroyoga or themselves too seriously. They teach many regular classes in Copenhagen with Emil (for next semester offerings, see https://www.facebook.com/events/1727078030893077/ ).&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>We really look forward to this holiday with you all.&nbsp;</div><div>Kind regards from&nbsp;</div><div>Julie, Peter, Blox and Emil.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/994954283937094/'),(131,'Dutch Acro','2017-06-02 00:00:00','2017-06-05 00:00:00',1,'unknown','the 31st edition of the dutch acrobatics festival will be like always a festival by acrobats for acrobats. With a grand choice of classes for all levels and ages.<br>','The festival is organized by volunteers and will like always probably have organic Vegetarian/vegan food. An open stage and a gala show next to the big array of acrobatics classes. Because of the organizational structure it mostly takes time to put all the information on the website until 4 months before it starts. Also the location of the festival is hard as the organizers need time to set up the place as it is in a different location every year. As it is very big and popular you have to keep an eye out and check the website because they do sell out most of the time.<br>&nbsp;<br>','http://www.akrobatiek.nl/'),(132,'Extreme Convention','2017-04-14 00:00:00','2017-04-16 00:00:00',1,'Antwerp, Belgium','A wide assortment of workshops about different circus techniques. At night Atlas Festival offers a number of high quality shows, created by several international circus companies.','https://www.facebook.com/atlas.extreme/','http://extremeconvention.be/extreme/index.html'),(133,'YogaSlackers Retreat','2016-12-01 00:00:00','2016-12-08 00:00:00',1,'Chiang Mai, Thailand','Join the YogaSlackers in their 3rd Retreat in Chiang Mai, Thailand! This trio of modern day nomads will facilitate a 7 day exploration of your human potential.&nbsp;','<div>Focused on the dualities a nomadic life, several acrobatic practices and active recovery, they will explore the edges of your perceived limits and will teach you how to surpass them. Through thoughtful exploration on the importance of stillness in movement, the softness found in strength and the art of silent communication, they will facilitate a personal rediscovery like no other. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>TEACHING TEAM</div><div>*Sam Salwei and Raquel Hernández*</div><div>YogaSlackers Sam Salwei and Raquel Hernández are lovers of movement. Limitations are a foreign concept to this teaching duo, as they spend their time traveling the world and fulfilling their dreams of being true modern-day nomads. Whether it’s driving coast-to-coast, or hopping on an airplane to travel overseas, the motivation is usually the same: bringing their passion for teaching to students all over the world.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>What they lack in square footage for living space, they make up for with the wealth of expertise and knowledge they bring with them. Sam Salwei co-founded the YogaSlackers in 2005, and his passion for Slacklining has only grown since then. He typically can be found aweing crowds with his spectacles at every opportunity. Raquel perfectly complements Sam with her extensive training in Yoga, Acroyoga, Slacklining, and Healing Arts.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>What makes this couple truly exceptional is their joint ability to spark in their students the same passion that they share for movement. Together, they create a playful, supportive, disciplined, and energetic environment in which learning comes naturally, and show their students that there is no limit to what they can achieve with a positive attitude and dedication. In fact, after taking enough of Sam and Raquel’s classes, “I can’t” may become as foreign of a concept to you as it is for the YogaSlackers!</div><div><br></div><div>*Emily Baxter*</div><div>Emily Baxter is dedicated to sharing and teaching whatever she can to inspire freedom in people. A bit of a jack of all trades, she teaches and practices several styles of Yoga asana, including Hatha, Yin, Vinyasa as well as AcroYoga and Slackline Yoga. She teaches anatomy, methodology and adjustments on various Yoga Teacher Trainings and runs her own Yin Yoga Teacher Training programs as well as Partner Acrobatics Intensives and Teacher Trainings. She is also trained as a Postural Therapist. Emily has always had a passion for movement and body awareness. This coupled with her strong background in anatomy manifests in her teachings as clear, precise, thoughtful instruction. She continues to study, travel, teach, play and laugh wherever she may find herself.</div><div><br></div><div>INCLUDED ACTIVITIES</div><div>Morning Yoga Practice</div><div>Slackline Yoga</div><div>AcroYoga</div><div>Slackro</div><div>Dutch Acrobatics</div><div>Water Acrobatics</div><div>Conditioning&nbsp;</div><div>Games and Fun Challenges</div><div><br></div><div>INCLUDED AMENITIES</div><div>7 Night Stay at Kaomai Lanna Resort in Shared Room&nbsp;</div><div>3 Thai Meals per day</div><div>1 Private Thai Massage</div><div>1 Group Excursion</div><div>Transportation from the Chiang Mai Airport</div><div><br></div><div>SAMPLE DAY</div><div>7:00 AM Yoga</div><div>8:30 AM Breakfast</div><div>9:30 AM Slackline/AcroYoga</div><div>12:00 PM Lunch Break</div><div>3:00 PM AcroYoga/Slackline</div><div>5:00 PM Conditioning/Acrobatics</div><div>6:00 PM Dinner</div><div>8:00 PM Stretching or Therapeutics</div><div><br></div><div>PLANNING &amp; GETTING TO THAILAND</div><div>We recommend you to enjoy Chiang Mai for few days before the training and possibly stay longer afterwards. Most countries automatically receive 30 days upon arrival. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Check-In and Check-out times at Kaomai Lanna are:&nbsp;</div><div>In: Monday Dec 1st at 1:00 PM</div><div>Out: Dec 8th at 11:00 AM</div><div>www.kaomailanna.com</div><div><br></div><div>PRE-REQUISITES</div><div>This retreat will serve as an opportunity to polish your acrobatic skills. Different skill levels are welcome in this retreat. We will start the 7 days of exploration teaching and reviewing the basics forms of Slackline Yoga and AcroYoga. As we progress through the week we will add more challenges suitable to each individual. We promise you will not feel too new or experience to truly enjoy it! &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>During the first day we will review the pre-reqs and move forward from there. Depending on the group skills we might divide into different groups to cover advanced Acrobatics and Slackrobatics. To get the most out of your experience, practice these set of skills beforehand.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>You don\'t need a partner, but we\'ll honor people wanting to work with one.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>ACROYOGA PREREQUISITES&nbsp;</div><div>30 seconds holds</div><div>Fly AND Base</div><div>Free Headstand</div><div>Handstand on the Wall</div><div>Free Bird</div><div>Free Star</div><div>Free Shoulder Stand</div><div>Foot to Hand</div><div>Tuck Sit</div><div>Foot to Shin</div><div>Shin to Foot</div><div><br></div><div>Repetitions... 10 each&nbsp;</div><div>Kick into Handstand (Wall)</div><div>Bird Presses</div><div>Throne Presses</div><div>Star Presses</div><div>Push-ups 15 repetitions&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Washing Machine</div><div>3 repetitions in your main roll (base or fly)</div><div>Barrel Roll</div><div>4-Steps</div><div>Catherine\'s Wheel</div><div><br></div><div>SLACKLINE YOGA PREREQUISITES</div><div>No set pre-requisites for slacklining. This are a few suggestions on things to work on. But we will cover them during our first slackline classes. &nbsp;</div><div>Stand</div><div>Sit</div><div>Kneel</div><div>Pointer</div><div>Tucksit</div><div><br></div><div>Need more info?</div><div>Contact plc@yogaslackers.com</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/313213022136208/'),(134,'Preconvention to the dutch acro convention','2017-05-28 00:00:00','2017-06-02 00:00:00',1,'Beuningen near Nijmegen','4 days leading up to the Dutch acro festival, with well known teachers warming you up for the big one.','Come and warm up, 4 days of acro before the dutch acro festival. If you are coming from far or just want more acro time come join us. It will be a campsite event with optional airbnb farm housing close. Vegetarian food, Sauna, well known teachers and lots of acro time. Very kids friendly just outside of Nijmegen in the Netherlands.<br>','https://www.facebook.com/Preconvention-to-the-Dutch-Acrobatics-Festival-624309611028414/?fref=ts'),(135,'Tasmanian Acro Flyaway','2017-02-10 00:00:00','2016-10-20 00:00:00',0,'Tasmania, Australia','Come FlyAway to the beautiful Tasmanian bush for 10 days of acro training away from it all.  We\'ll dive into washing machines, standing acro, yoga, therapeutics, thai massage, lakeside shenanigans and more.  Join Scott &amp; Ebony of Threads, Niko Douwes and Mimi Nunez of partneracrobatics.com','<br>','http://www.threadstasmania.com/new-page-5/'),(136,'French Acro Convention','2017-07-06 00:00:00','2017-10-15 00:00:00',1,'Ste-Eulalie-En-Born, France','A nice festival at a camp ground, every one volunteers to help the camp run, there is a day off for canoeing and also a beach day at the sea side.','<br>','https://www.facebook.com/events/301830816868378/'),(137,'End of year Acrobatics','2016-12-27 00:00:00','2016-12-31 00:00:00',1,'Millingen, Netherlands','In a gym close to forest, hills and the meadows full of birds along the river Rhine we are having a newyears Acro Festival. Just after X-mas, Five days of acrobatics.&nbsp;','<div>Breakfast, lunch and vegetarian diner will be taken care of, we will sleep in the gym.</div><div>From tuesday 27th of dec. 12:00u to saturday 31th of dec. 18:00u,</div><div>We\'ll have time for free training and have a few workshops.</div><div>There\'ll be a lunge and we\'ll have enough mats, thick mats, long mat etc.</div><div><br></div><div>The environment is also very suit to go for a hike or to cycle around to get some fresh air. Only a limited amount of people are able to join (min.35-max.60).</div><div>Questions? contact us via E-mail</div><div>Be quick to register before we\'re full.</div><div><br></div><div>or you\'ll be outside, and that\'s cold in december. and you don\'t want that, because you want to do acrobatics, with the others, in a warm gym with good food with possibillities for a good price and register here and not wait because it all seems to be happening rather tomorrow than next week...</div>','http://acrobatiek.com/indexENG.html'),(138,'International Acro Convention','2016-06-24 00:00:00','2016-07-01 00:00:00',1,'Skradin, Croatia','We will be celebrating our 10th anniversary!','<br>','http://acrobatics.nl/next.php'),(139,'Acroatia- Croatia Acrobatic Festival','0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,'','<br>','<br>',''),(140,'Move Copenhagen','2017-07-14 00:00:00','2017-07-17 00:00:00',1,'Copenhagen, Denmark','Move Copenhagen is an international movement festival celebrating the diversity of movement.','<div>a 4-day festival with the opportunity to participate in some of the more then 100 workshops. There will be workshops for movers in all levels – beginners, intermediate and advanced.</div><div><br></div><div>Move Copenhagen is for everyone who wants a challenge and who wants to explore new forms and shapes of movement. Meet and learn from some of the best movers in slacklining, climbing and bouldering, yoga, acroyoga, dance and parkour. The ticket includes:</div><div><br></div><div>– Free acces to all workshops</div><div>– 4 days of fun</div><div>– A free spot for your tent</div><div>– Free use of shower and toilets</div>','http://movecopenhagen.com'),(141,'Manchester Aerial & Acrobatics Converntion','2017-04-28 00:00:00','2016-04-30 00:00:00',1,'Manchester, UK','<div>After the overwhelmingly positive response we had to our first convention last April, we decided to go massive this time.</div><div><br></div>','<div>The ticket link is manchesteraac.co.uk. DO NOT TYPE www. first, just exactly as above. There are 200 tickets and once they\'re gone they\'re gone. Tickets are non-refundable for any reason but you\'re welcome to sell your ticket on.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>GO BIG OR GO HOME! After the overwhelmingly positive response we had to our first convention in April, we decided to go massive this time.</div><div><br></div><div>We\'re hiring out Bowlers Exhibition Centre for the whole weekend so we can host more workshops, more teachers and of course more amazing students!! We anticipate being able to host 200 students this time, quadrupling our capacity from 2016. The space has a few thousand square feet so we\'ll be able to host an amazing six classes at once, giving you more choice and more variety.</div><div><br></div><div>The venue has an amazing 8m of height so we\'ll be able to rig all the usual silks, trapezes, ropes and hoops as well as new aerial equipment such as cloud swings, aerial nets and maybe something bungee related!</div><div><br></div><div>With the additional floor space we\'re also looking at running cyr wheel workshops as well as your favourite floor workshops from last time, including hula hoop, stilt walking and of course acro acro acro!</div><div><br></div><div>The level of teachers last year was amazing, the calibre of students was incredible and the atmosphere was indescribable. So let\'s do it all again!!</div><div><br></div><div>Obviously this is a good few months away so at this stage we\'re in early planning and we\'ll release details of workshops and teachers as we get them.</div><div><br></div><div>Teachers so far:</div><div>Colm &amp; Mona from Newton\'s Ladder teaching rope, rope doubles and counterweighting</div><div>Kat Clark from Rogueplay teaching rope</div><div>Kit from Cloud teaching aerial beats and floor gymnastics</div><div>Will Duncan from Pendragon Circus teaching trapeze</div><div>Jo Jordan from DirtyFeet teaching aerial hoop</div><div>Julie from Rockahula teaching hula hoop</div><div>Scott &amp; Michaela teaching acro workshops, hand to hand and standing tricks</div><div>Ed Swift teaching silks</div><div>Brendan from Cloud teaching aerial net</div><div>Kris Madden teaching Cyr Wheel</div><div>Forma Fortis teaching acrobalance</div><div>Amy Capper teaching hoop</div><div>Kim Charnock teaching silks</div><div>Andi ActiveCherry teaching weird &amp; wonderful aerial apparatus</div><div>Belinda Grantham teaching yoga and aerial yoga</div><div>Andi Semeseriasu teaching straps and handbalancing</div><div><br></div><div>SAVE THE DATE RIGHT NOW AND SPREAD THE WORD! MAAC 2017 is going to be insane.</div>','https://www.facebook.com/events/751035601702463/788775844595105/?notif_t=admin_plan_mall_activity&notif_id=1477216696956692'),(142,'Akro Kiel','2017-02-24 00:00:00','2017-02-26 00:00:00',1,'Kiel, Germany','<div><br></div><div>AkroKiel is overbooked heavily. They had to close registration, sorry...</div>','<div>AkroKiel 2017</div><div><br></div><div>Registration<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Until 9.2.2016, after that add 5 € \"panic fee\"; if you come unregistered, you can\'t get food (because this is ordered by number in advance) and may be not even participate, if the maximum number of particitiants is reached (the festival is booked out since years, therefore, you usually just have to travel back home, coming unregistered). You will receive an email confirmation automatically, another email, when your payment gets booked, and finally one, where your participation gets confirmed (after we checked the waiting list etc.). If you do not get any mails like this, contact us: Most definitely, something went go wrong!</div><div><br></div><div>Friday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>17-24 o\'clock acrobatics, ca. 20:30 vegetarian/non-vegetarian dinner buffet (with bio components again).</div><div><br></div><div>Saturday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>9-19 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet, vegetarian/non-vegetarian dinner buffet (with bio ingredients), show and Party.</div><div><br></div><div>Sunday<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>9-15 o\'clock acrobatics, workshops, breakfast buffet.</div><div><br></div><div>Costs<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>People less than 6 years: free, people from 6 and below 16 years: 35 €, older people: 60 €, if you don\'t mind, you are welcome to pay a little extra, to sponsor the kids fee (that does not match the costs).</div><div><br></div><div>Payment<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>We are sending the account information with the confirmation email, that usually comes right away (i.e.: Within a few minutes, if nothing comes, something went worg; try again or contact AkroKiel@AkroKiel.de). The registrations gets valid with the payment (i.e. without payment, you are not registered!).</div><div><br></div><div>Location<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>Sports Center of the Christian-Albrecht-University Kiel, Olshausenstrasse 74, Kiel.</div><div><br></div><div>Maximum number of participiants<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>The maximum number of participants of 250 has been reached again, there are 134 people on the waiting list.</div><div><br></div><div>AkroKiel is overbooked heavily. We had to close registration, sorry...</div><div>© AkroKiel · Fon: +49-431-1220510 · eMail: Orga@AkroKiel.de</div>','http://tiroqrgcykmj4iie.myfritz.net');
