d colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Ensalada Mixta o One Minute Practice</td>\r\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Ensalada Mixta o One Minute Practice</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progTeaching\'>Práctica de Enseñanza</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>6-8</td>\r\n    <td colspan=\'7\' class=\'progFood\'>Cena</td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n  <tr>\r\n    <td>8-9</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Actividades Opcionales</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progLecture\'>Lectura</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Actividades Opcionales</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Actividades Opcionales</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progLecture\'>Lectura</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Actividades Opcionales</td>\r\n    <td class=\'progOffTime\'></td>\r\n  </tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Legend</h3>\r\n<div class=\'progLegend\'>\r\n  <p><span class=\'progHandstand\'>Parada de Manos</span>: cada día dedicaremos este tiempo para que su parada de mano se ponga genial.</p>\r\n  <p><span class=\'progFoundations\'>Fundamentos</span>: Los trucos y habilidades que todos necesitan aprender.</p>\r\n  <p><span class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Ensalada Mixta</span>: 2 o 3 talleres presentados a la misma vez donde el estudiante escoje a cual quiere atender.  Habrán talleres de acrobacia en pie, washing machines, acrobacia al estilo Holandés, Icarian, vuelo terapéutico, etc. </p>\r\n  <p><span class=\'progTherapy\'>Práctica Terapéutica</span>: Una mezcla de masaje Tailandés, vuelo terapéutico y práctica de un minuto para descansar y relajarnos un poco. <a href=\'http://flyingtherapeutics.org/\' target=\'_blank\'>Flying Therapeutics</a>, <a href=\'http://one-minute-practice.com\' target=\'_blank\'>One Minute Practice</a> Para recuperar el cuerpo.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progTeaching\'>Práctica de Enseñanza</span>: tiempo para mostrar como enseñarias una clase de acrobacia en pareja</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progLecture\'>Lectura</span>: desde ciencia del deporte a mercadeo, siempre hay algo de que charlar para ayudarnos como practicantes y profesores.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progOptional\'>Optional</span>: este tiempo estará abierto para que personas compartan sus habilidades con el grupo o para hacer su propia práctica.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progWarmUp\'>Calentamiento</span>: la mejor manera para prepararte para tu día de entrenamiento.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progFood\'>Comida</span>: comidas mayormente vegetarianas.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\'progOffTime\'>Tiempo Libre</span>: hasta los acróbatas necesitan descansar :)</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>Certificación</h2>\r\n<p>Al haber cumplido el profesorado, estudiantes podrán recibir un certificado mostrando que han entrenado más de 150 horas de acrobacia de pareja y estarán destacados en la página de profesores de PartnerAcrobatics.com. Aunque la realización de un programa de certificación es útil en su camino a convertirse en un profesor, es aún más importante construir una práctica fuerte y segura que puedas compartir con confianza a otras personas.\r\n</p>'),(327,0,1,'mexico_location_main','mexico_location_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h2>Venue</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    Chalananda is located inside a beautiful hot springs water park,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    overlooking a natural protected lake and migratory bird sanctuary in Villa Corona, Jalisco, 45 min. away from the state´s capital Guadalajara.  The\r\n    beautiful surroundings of the park serve as the perfect place to practice and learn.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nMore infos about the venue available on their website:<br> <a href=\'http://www.chalananda.com\' target=\'_blank\'>www.chalananda.com<a/>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3739.35252787624!2d-103.669007!3d20.4095692!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8425fbb2f7ab02c9%3A0xfcdfe9db22d34917!2sSanta+Mar%C3%ADa+16%2C+Los+Veleros%2C+45790+Villa+Corona%2C+JAL%2C+Mexico!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sth!4v1415695703888\' width=\'600\' height=\'450\' frameborder=\'0\' style=\'border:0\'></iframe>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2> Facilities </h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> 104°F. Giant thermal water pools\r\n<li>Water massage pool\r\n<li>Lazy river\r\n<li>Water slides\r\n<li>Free wireless internet (Wi-Fi)\r\n<li>Laundry\r\n<li>Nursery\r\n<li>Bungalows\r\n<li>Grocery store and market nearby\r\n<li>Lake and bird sanctuary\r\n<li>Very safe place and premises\r\n<li>Camping area with bathrooms and showers\r\n<li>Massage service\r\n<li>Restaurant\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQ</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do I need a visa to enter Mexico?  </h3>\r\n<p>Check out which nationalities require a visa in this website:  <a href=\'http://www.inm.gob.mx\'>www.inm.gob.mx</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to get to Chalananda? </h3>\r\n<p>You can hire a Taxi from the airport or anywhere in Guadalajara city,  directly to Chalananda.  If you do so, make sure to specify to the taxi driver to take you to:  Villa Corona, Chimulco (the water Park in which Chalananda is based), don\'t tell them to take you to Chalananda because they will not know where this is.   We are also providing private transportation from these two places that will cost you less depending on the number of passengers. For more info about this service, email:  edubetancourt@gmail.com</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to get to Guadalajara,  Jalisco (GDL)? </h3>\r\n<p>The best way is to fly directly into Guadalajara International Airport (Don Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla).<br>\r\nYou can also fly into the following international airports in Mexico: Puerto Vallarta, Cancun, Mexico City.<br>\r\nFrom all these you can connect with one of the local low cost airlines that fly into Guadalajara:<br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.volaris.com\'>www.volaris.com</a><br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.vivaaerobus.com\'>www.vivaaerobus.com</a><br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.interjet.com\'>www.interjet.com</a><br>\r\nIf you are flying into Puerto Vallarta or Mexico City you can also take a bus to Guadalajara.<br>\r\nWe recommend checking these options and  see what works best for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is it possible to stay in Chalananda before and after the retreat? </h3>\r\n<p>Yes it is possible.  Please contact us if you would like to do that.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is it safe?</h3>\r\n<p>Chalananda is inside a private water park that is very safe and secure. Jalisco has always been a  tourist friendly state but in the last years Mexico has seen an upsurge in drug related violence. Although tourists and travelers are hardly ever targeted we advise you to take necessary precautions if you are staying or traveling in Mexico</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What is the weather like in Jalisco around Oct? </h3>\r\n<p>This area of Jalisco has one of the best climates in the world.  During our fall retreats, the weather is cool in the evening and in the morning, (min. 6 C) and warm during the day (max. 27 C) Occasional rains are also expected.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What about sanitation?  </h3>\r\n<p>No problem, we only advise you to take precaution with street food before and after the retreat.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What About Credit Cards, Cash, Exchange Rates & Money Changers?  </h3>\r\n<p>The exchange rate is approximately $13.00 Pesos = US$1.00, but it is always fluctuating so check before coming. We do not accept credit cards.  Banks for money changing services  you can find in the pueblo Villa Corona just outside the retreat center and an ATM Machine can be found inside the retreat center.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Suggested Reading about Jalisco? </h3>\r\n<p><a href=\'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalisco\'>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalisco</a><br>\r\nJuan Rulfo\'s \'Pedro Paramo\' and \'El llano en llamas\' </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What to bring? </h3>\r\n<p>Water bottle, sweater or jacket for the night,  flash light, notebook, pen, mosquito repellent, towel and swimming suit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>If I\'m camping, do I have to bring a tent and sleeping bag? </h3>\r\n<p>You don\'t need to, Bring your own sleeping bed.</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2015-05-01 11:19:03',NULL,NULL,'','<h2>Ubicación</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    Chalananda se encuentra ubicada dentro de un hermoso parque de agua termal, en Villa Corona, Jalisco, a sólo 45 minutos de Guadalajara.  Con vista a un lago natural protegido y santuario de aves migratorias, los bellos alrededores de este parque invitan e inspiran a practicar y aprender.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMas informacions sobre el lugar estan disponibles en sus pagina web:<br> <a href=\'http://www.chalananda.com\' target=\'_blank\'>www.chalananda.com<a/>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3739.35252787624!2d-103.669007!3d20.4095692!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x8425fbb2f7ab02c9%3A0xfcdfe9db22d34917!2sSanta+Mar%C3%ADa+16%2C+Los+Veleros%2C+45790+Villa+Corona%2C+JAL%2C+Mexico!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sth!4v1415695703888\' width=\'600\' height=\'450\' frameborder=\'0\' style=\'border:0\'></iframe>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2> Instalaciones </h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> 2 Albercas gigantes de agua termal 39 ° C\r\n<li>Alberca de hidro masaje\r\n<li>Lazy river\r\n<li>Toboganes\r\n<li>Internet inalámbrico (Wi-Fi)\r\n<li>Lavandería\r\n<li>Sección acuática infantil y Guardería\r\n<li>Bungalows\r\n<li>Tienda y de mercado cercana\r\n<li>Lago y santuario de aves\r\n<li>Seguridad y vigilancia\r\n<li> Área de campamento con baños y duchas\r\n<li>Servicio de masaje\r\n<li>Restaurante\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Preguntas Frecuentes</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Necesito visa para entrar a México? </h3>\r\n<p>En este enlace podrás ver los países que requieren visa: <a href=\'http://www.inm.gob.mx\'>www.inm.gob.mx</a> </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Cómo llegar a Chalananda? </h3>\r\n<p>Chalananda esta ubicado a 1 hora del Aeropuerto Internacional de Guadalajara.  Una opción es tomar un taxi desde el aeropuerto o cualquier punto de Guadalajara.  Indicandole al taxista que te lleve a Chimulco en Villa Corona. Chalananda también ofrece transporte privado desde el aeropuerto o la ciudad de Guadalajara que costará menos dependiendo del número de pasajeros. Para más info acerca de este servicio manda un correo a: edubetancourt@gmail.com</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Cómo llegar a Guadalajara, Jalisco? </h3>\r\n<p>La mejor manera es volar directamente al Aeropuerto Internacional de Guadalajara (Don Miguel Hidalgo y Costilla). Otra opción es volar a otro de los aeropuertos internacionales de México, como: Puerto Vallarta, Cancún o Ciudad de México. Desde allí puedes conectar con una de las siguientes aerolíneas de bajo costo locales que vuelan a Guadalajara:<br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.volaris.com\'>www.volaris.com</a><br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.vivaaerobus.com\'>www.vivaaerobus.com</a><br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.interjet.com\'>www.interjet.com</a><br>\r\nSi decides volar a Puerto Vallarta o Ciudad de México puedes desde ahí tambien tomar un autobus a Guadalajara.  Te recomendamos contemplar todas estas opciones y ver que te es mas conveniente.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Es posible quedarse en Chalananda antes o despues del retiro?</h3>\r\n<p>  Si es posible.  Ponte en contacto con nosotros si deseas hacer esto.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Es Jalisco seguro? </h3>\r\n<p>Chalananda está dentro de un parque acuático privado muy seguro. Jalisco ha sido siempre un estado turistico y amigable. No obstante te aconsejamos que tomes las precauciones necesarias en caso de que decidas viajar por México antes o después del retiro.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Como es el clima en Jalisco en el mes de Octubre? </h3>\r\n<p>Esta zona de Jalisco tiene uno de los mejores climas del mundo. Durante los retiros de otoño el clima es fresco por la noche y la mañana (min. 6 C) y soleado durante el día (max. 27 C)  Es probable que llueva algunos dias.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Qué pasa con la salubridad? </h3>\r\n<p>no hay problema, sólo te aconsejamos ser precavido a la hora de consumir alimentos fuera de Chalananda, especialmente comida callejera.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Como esta el tema de las tarjetas de crédito,  el tipo de cambio y casas de cambio? </h3>\r\n<p>El tipo de cambio es de aproximadamente $ 13.00 pesos = $ EE.UU. 1,00. Aunque fluctúa constantemente. Chalananda no acepta tarjetas de crédito.  Bancos pra cambiar dinero y cajeros automáticos (ATM) podras encontrar sin problema.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Lecturas recomendadas sobre Jalisco</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalisco\'>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalisco</a><br>\r\nJuan Rulfo \'Pedro Páramo\' y \'El llano en LLamas\'</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>¿Qué traer? </h3>\r\n<p> Botella de agua, suéter pora la noche, linterna, traje de baño, repelente para mosquitos, cuaderno y un bolígrafo.  Si vas a acampar no olvides tu bolsa de dormir y tienda de campaña.</p>'),(326,0,1,'mexico_program_intro','mexico_program_intro',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<p>An optional 1 or 2 week long Intensive Training in Partner Acrobatics.<br> <br>\n\n\nIn our Partner Acrobatics programs we cover many different acrobatic disciplines including standing acrobatics, handstand training, washing machines, trio tricks, Icarian games and much more.<br>\nThis physical intensity is balanced out with our therapeutic sessions, which aim to heal and restore the body.\n<br>\n<br>\nThis program will give you the chance to refine your Acro skills and to have loads of fun.\nYou have the freedom to choose how many hours you spend on Acro vs Therapeutics.\n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-14 06:03:14',NULL,NULL,'','<p>Un programa de profesorado en Acrobacia en Pareja (Partner Acrobatics) donde podrás entrenarte intensamente durante 4 semanas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instrucciones en Español y Ingles!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Este curso intende prepararte para que puedas dar clases y talleres de Acrobacia en Pareja (Partner Acrobatics)<br>\r\nAdemas tendrás mucho tiempo para mejorar tus practica personal de acrobata<br>\r\nHabrá tiempo dedicado para mejorar tus capacidades de actuar en público y afinar tus movimientos acrobáticos. <br>\r\n6 o más horas a la semana estarán dedicadas al trabajo terapéutico para recuperar y mantener tu cuerpo sano\r\n</p>'),(328,0,1,'mexico_location_subtitle','mexico_location_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h2>Jalisco, Mexico<br>From Nov 6 to 19, 2017</h2>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-07 19:07:22',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br>\r\nDesde el 20 de Septiembre hasta el 18 de Octubre 2015</h3>'),(329,0,1,'mexico_program_subtitle','mexico_program_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Jalisco, Mexico<br>Nov 6 -19, 2017','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-14 07:53:32',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br>\r\nDesde el 20 de Septiembre hasta el 18 de Octubre 2015</h3>'),(330,0,1,'mexico_info_main','mexico_info_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h2> Prerequisites</h2>\n\nWe <b>do require</b> require you have some acrobatic skills. We need you to honestly and accurately asses whether the following skills are accessible/of ease to you (while working with someone of similar skill level) as a base OR flyer, <b>at the time of application</b> you must be able to accomplish the skills without a spotter helping (they can be there for safety).\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Proficiency/comfort spotting tricks at your level\n<li> Kick up into a handstand (you can have a spotter but without help to get in)\n<li> Hold a handstand at the wall for at least a minute.\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=237&title=Side+positions+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232&#37;23content\'>Sidestar</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=251&title=Acro+L-Base+Transition+Basics+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Prasarita twist</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Star (shoulderstand on feet)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=243&title=Shoulderstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free shoulderstand in hands (flyer holding bases arms)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Thighstand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=249&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Foot to Hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<!-- <li><a href=\'\'>...</a><br> -->\n</ul>\n\n<p>On your application you will be asked to rate your comfort level in the following.... while they are not prerequisites, the more experience you come with the more you will gain out of the training!</p>\n<ul>\n<li> L-BASING (base lying down)\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=183&title=Tic+Tocks+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Tic tocks</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=180&title=Corkscrew+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Corkscrew</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=246&title=Reverse+shoulder+stand+on+feet+%28reverse+star%29+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Reverse star</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free star (no hands)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=248&title=Hand+to+Hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Hand to hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li> STANDING\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Flag (either variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=273&title=Two+High+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>2 man high (hands on calves)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=285&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Foot to hand</a><br>\n<li>Hand to hand<br>\n</ul>\n<p> Send us 1 video</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1-2 minute acrobatic flow of your choice.\n</ul>\n<p>The video should represent where you are at skill-wise, however, it doesn’t \nneed to be all of the craziest things you can do---think elements from the \npreqs! The video also doesn’t need to be of high production quality, a \nquick one on your cell phone is fine:)\n</p>\n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-02 09:02:10',NULL,NULL,'','<h2> Requisitos previos </h2>\r\n<p>Cuanta mas experiencia en el enseñamiento tienes cuanto mejor. Comienza practicando con tus amigos y familia para tener cuanta mas costumbre posible al enseñamiento. De esa forma podras aprender mucho mas durante el curso. </ p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n <b> Se requiere </b> que  tengas algunas habilidades acrobáticas. Necesitamos que nos envía un video por cada elemento en la lista de abajo.\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> Una parada de cabeza sólida, lo que significa que\r\nen parada de cabeza en trípode tu puedas carpar y levantar piernas unas cuantas veces sin tener que bajar tus piernas al suelo.\r\nSin pared o cuidador. (<a href=\'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BfRHNyT7KBc\' target=\'_blank\'> mirar este vídeo </a>). <br>\r\n<li> Mantener una parada de manos en la pared, por lo menos de un minuto.\r\n<li> Estar de base y volar en Star ( Estrella = parada de hombros en los pies) durante al menos un minuto.\r\n<li> <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L7wvnSGOvbY\'> Prasarita </a>\r\n<li> Un video de un minuto de flow acrobatico en pareja sobre lo que te gusta mas.\r\n</ul>\r\n<p> Antes de aplicar subir tus videos a youtube o facebook. </p>\r\n<h2>Ejercicios recomendados</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEn los días previos a la formación será útil que usted comience a practicar algunos de los ejercicios que vamos a hacer como parte del condicionamiento. Aquí algunas descripciones y enlaces a vídeos. En todos estos ejercicios menos es más, es mucho mejor hacer menos repeticiones y de la forma apropiada. Repita hasta que puedas con buena forma.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Círculos  en parada de cabeza </h3>\r\n<iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/gYfCkhNs9-I?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\r\n<p> Cualquier variación de parada de cabeza (o parada de manos si la tienes) está bien, jugar con los círculos en ambas direcciones, tratando de mantener las piernas rectas y los pies en punta.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> V ups </h3>\r\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/hAAMBQrHH14?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\r\n<p>Trate de mantener la columna recta. Relaje los hombros, nunca trabajar a través del dolor y ser consciente de su espalda baja.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Tuck up, Straddle up, Pike up  </h3>\r\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/STuoafM2zhk?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\r\n<p> En parada de cabeza (o en pino :)) practicar tuck up (en una bola), straddle up (teniendo las piernas abiertas a los lados) y piking (ambas piernas por delante y recto). Trate de no saltar. Estamos en busca de control, tratamos de bajar lento como se sube. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Tabla inversa hasta Tuck Sit </h3>\r\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/CtHrtD__mJA?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\r\n<p> Comience con sus muñecas bajo los hombros y las rodillas sobre las tobillos, utilice su centro para mover las caderas hacia atrás entre los brazos y volver a la posición inicial </p>\r\n\r\n<h3> Equilibrio  sobre antebrazos</h3>\r\n<p> Trate de abrir a través de los hombros, sacar las costillas bajas en el cuerpo. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3> flexiones </h3>\r\n<p> Usted sabe lo que son! ;) </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Estiramiento de isquiotibiales </h3>\r\n<p> Para cualquier persona que tiene dificultades para mantener las piernas rectas a 90 grados para hacer de base </p>\r\n'),(852,NULL,1,'mexico_program_title','mexico_program_title',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Program of the Intensive Training in Mexico','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(815,269,1,'One leg dead lift','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<iframe width=\'560\' height=\'315\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/Ua5mb4Jt6xE?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=56\'>Martin Kvist</a><br>','manual',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-17 09:26:51',NULL,NULL,'',''),(816,269,1,'Split squat','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<iframe width=\'560\' height=\'315\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/t9K2idig9Xc?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\n\r\n <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=56\'>Martin Kvist</a><br>','manual',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-17 09:27:18',NULL,NULL,'',''),(331,0,1,'mexico_fees_main','mexico_fees_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Prices</h3>\n<p>Prices include the two weeks training, accommodation and three vegetarian meals daily. Meat is offered every second day.</p>\n\n<p>The price of the course <b>does not include</b> flights or airport pickup.</p>\n\n<p>Arrival time November 6th evening (dinner included), departure time November 19th morning (breakfast included).</p>\n\n\n<h3>Early Bird (discounted price)</h3>\n<b> Coming soon...</b>\n<!--\nPaid in full before July 1st 2017 ( 50&#37; refundable before Sept 15th).<br><br>\n\n<p>Room options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for 2 weeks - 1700 USD\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for 2 weeks -  \n<li><b>Shared room</b> for first week only - 1000 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for first week only -  750 Euro<br>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Regular Price</h3>\n\nAfter Feb 10th\n<p>Room options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for 2 weeks - 1700 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for 2 weeks -  1450 Euro\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for first week only - 1100 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for first week only -  850 Euro<br>\n (Prices are 50% refundable before May 10th) \n</ul>\n-->\n</ul><h2> Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>Before applying upload the videos of yourself practicing the <a href=\'info-am.php\'>prerequisites</a> to youtube or facebook.</p>\n\n<h2> Application</h2>\n\n<p>Space is limited and will fill up. </p>\n<p>\nPlease fill out the form, send a photo of yourself and the link to your videos\nto <b>info@partneracrobatics.com</b>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n<a href=\'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1XKfV5hWrhxJl8bIuva8lIq_QE1QwJRAXb6B_XUIwdaQ/viewform\' target=\'_blank\'>click here to go to the form</a>\n</p>\n<p>\nAfter being accepted we will send payment details.<br>\n<b>Only once you have paid your space will be guaranteed at the training</b>.\n</p>\n \n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-02 09:25:28',NULL,NULL,'','<h2>Precios</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n  Los precios incluyen la formación por todo el més, alojamiento y tres comidas vegetarianas diarias. Cada dos días se ofrecerá carne.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El precio del curso de <b> no incluye </b> vuelos o recogida en el aeropuerto.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tiempo de llegada  20 de septiembre por la noche (cena incluida), hora de salida 18 de octubre por la mañana (desayuno incluido).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<!--<h4>Inscripción anticipada</h4>\r\n<p>Pagado por completo antes de 20 de mayo (50% <b> no reembolsable </b>).</p>\r\n<p>Opciones de alojamiento:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Camping</b> - 3400 USD -  hay que traer tienda y saco de dormir\r\n<li><b>Bungalows compartidos</b> - 4100 USD - compartido con 6/10 personas\r\n<li><b>Habitación doble</b> - 4400 USD - 1 cama doble\r\n</ul>-->\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Precio</h4>\r\n<p><!--Pagado por completo después de 20 de mayo (-->50% <b> no reembolsable </b>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Camping</b> - 3900 USD -   just bring your sleeping bed\r\n<li><b>Bungalows compartidos</b> - 4600 USD -  shared from 6 to 10\r\n<li><b>Habitación doble</b> - 4900 USD -  1 cama doble\r\n</ul><h2> Requisitos previos </h2>\r\n<p> Antes de aplicar, utiliza a youtube o facebook para subir los videos de tu práctica respetando los <a href=\'info-am.php\'> prerrequisitos </a>. </p>\r\n<h2> Aplicación </h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> El espacio es limitado y se llenará. </ p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPor favor complete el formulario, enviar una foto de sí mismo y la lista de sus vídeos\r\n<b> info@partneracrobatics.com </b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDespués de ser aceptado le enviaremos los detalles de pago. <br>\r\n<b> Sólo una vez que haya pagado se garantizará su plaza en el curso </b>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1qJlT1p66jITI8NSlYzdG8lfqdzdBXqDuEYx8DanhoJQ/viewform\' target=\'_blank\'>haga clic aquí para ir al formulario</a>\r\n</p>\r\n'),(368,NULL,1,'15_location_main','15_location_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h3>Venue</h3>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_shala.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n                <p><b>Cortijo Caseria Del Mercado</b> is a small organic farm high in the Alpujarras mountains of Andalucia, southern Spain.</p>\n                <p>In addition to the huge array of fruit and vegetables grown on site the farm has goats, horses and a peacock breeding sanctuary and the farm produces its own organic olive oil.</p>\n                <p>Not only is the cortijo a working farm it has been adapted as a retreat centre with traditional Spanish accommodation, a natural mineral water swimming pool and a yoga shala.</p>\n                <p>The local area is fantastic hiking country with spectacular mountain views and isolated “White villages”.</p>\n                <p>More info on the venue can be found <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'http://cortijolacaseria.com\'>here</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Accommodation</h3>\n<p>\nThe accommodation <b>is included</b> as part of the course price.<br>\n</p>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_main.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n\n                <p>The venues farm buildings offer various basic but comfortable accommodations with a communal and family feel .</p>\n                <p>Shared accommodation is included in the course fee, numbers permitting and for an additional fee single accom may be available, please contact us for availability.</p>\n        		<p>For those camping bring all your own gear, we don\'t provide tents but we have lots of extra blankets.</p>\n<h3>Food</h3>\n                <p>3 mostly vegetarian meals daily are included in the training fee.  Organic and local when possible.</p>\n                <p>There is a large communal kitchen and 3 smaller kitchens where students can prepare their own snacks etc.  Seasonal fruits and vegetables are available from the farm and they are amazing!</p>\n\n<h3>How to get there</h3>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_acro.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n\n                <p>The cortijo is high in the mountains close to a tiny village called Castaras. The closest town is Orgiva.  </p>\n                <p>We will provide pick up and trasport to and from Orgiva on the 8th, 15th and 22nd.</p>\n                <p>The closest airport Granada is about 1.5 hours away from our venue.</p>\n                <p>Malaga is just as close but has limited bus connection to Orgiva. Check <a href=\'http://www.alsa.es/en/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.Alsa.es</a> timetable.</p>\n                <p>There are several cheap flights daily from Madrid and Barcelona to Granada.</p>\n                <p></p>\n                <p>From Granada you can catch a bus to Orgiva (1 hour). Check <a href=\'http://www.alsa.es/en/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.Alsa.es</a> timetable. </p>\n\n                <p><b>GPS coords:</b> 36° 55.543, -3° 16.388</p>\n\n                <p>On <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://www.google.com/maps?t=h&ll=36.92571669999994&#37;2C-3.273133300000014&spn=0.009194283237178443%2C0.01533507242441279&output=classic\'>google maps</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Internet</h3>\n<p> A wifi connection is available at the Cortijo. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h3>Recommendations</h3>\n\n\n\n\n<p>\nWe do recommend that you invest in a good <b>travel insurance</b> then if the unexpected happens you will be well looked after financially.\n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-09 11:37:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,0,1,'mexico_fees_subtitle','mexico_fees_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br>From Nov 6-19, 2017</h3>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-01 07:29:29',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br>\r\nDesde el 20 de Septiembre hasta el 18 de Octubre 2015</h3>'),(333,0,1,'mexico_base_this_subtitle','mexico_base_this_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br> A month long Teacher Training from Sep 20th to Oct 18th, 2015</h3>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2015-06-02 21:21:15',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Jalisco, Mexico<br>\r\nDesde el 20 de Septiembre hasta el 18 de Octubre 2015</h3>'),(334,0,1,'mexico_base_this_main ','mexico_base_this_main ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Winners!</h3>\n<p>Announcing the winners of the ‪#‎basethisvideochallenge‬!<br>\nWe are super impressed by the effort, creativity and passion that people put into their videos!!!<br><br>\n1st--Ellio Blox and Athena Masters <br>\n2nd-- Saffron Van Rossem and Amy<br>\n3rd--Luka Agreš with Crocrobatis<br>\n4th--HanNy BUn and Meli Acro Art<br>\n5h--Sue and Jim Acro SUP<br>\nCheck out the <a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/770501809723983/\'>other videos on the event page!</a>\n\n<p>\n<h3>PartnerAcrobatics.com BASE THIS Video Challenge!</h3>\n<p>Want to come to the month long Partner Acrobatics teacher training in Mexico FOR FREE?!? Enter the ‪#‎basethis‬ video challenge for your chance to win!\nUpload a video of you doing partner acro and if your video is chosen you can win major discounts to the TT! We will have five winners and prizes are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1st 100% discount (for 1 person) ---><b>FREE!!!!</b></li>\n<li>2nd 50% discount (for 1 person) </li>\n<li>3rd 30% discount (for 1 person)</li>\n<li>4th 20% discount (for 1 person)</li>\n<li>5th 10% discount (for 1 person)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The winning videos will be chosen based on entertainment value, creativity and amount of likes received. This is not as much about creating the perfectly executed flow as it is about making something that is just fun (and maybe even funny) to watch! Join the fun and follow the steps below:</p>\n<ol>\n<li> Follow @partneracrobatics on Instagram</li>\n<li>Upload your video to Instagram and tag <b>@partneracrobatics</b> Use hashtags ‪<b>#‎partneracrobatics‬ ‪#‎basethisvideochallenge‬ #basethis ‪#‎nailedit‬</b></li>\n<li>Share your video on Facebook and post to the <a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/770501809723983/\' target=\'_blank\'>Partner Acrobatics Mexico TT event page</a>  (only likes on Instagram and on the event page will be counted)</li>\n<li> Tell your friends to vote for you!!!</li>\n</ol>\n<p><b>Voting ends on June 30</b>! Happy basing and good luck!</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2015-07-16 13:37:02',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>¿Quieres venir al profesorado de Partner Acrobatics en México de GRATIS?</h3>\r\n<p> Participa en el ?#?basethis? video challenge!!</p>\r\n<p>Sube un video haciendo acro y si su video es elegido podrás ganar grandes descuentos para el TT. Tendremos 5 premios y los descuentos serán así:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> 1er lugar 100% de descuento (para una persona) ---><b>¡GRATIS!</b></li>\r\n<li> 2do lugar 50% de descuento (para una persona)</li>\r\n<li> 3er lugar 30% de descuento (para una persona)</li>\r\n<li> 4to lugar 20% de descuento (para una persona)</li>\r\n<li> 5to lugar 10% de descuento (para una persona)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Los ganadores serán elegidos por cual entretenido es el video, creatividad y número de likes recibido. No es crear un video con la ejecución perfecta de un flow de acro, si no cuan divertido (y quizás hasta gracioso) es. Participa y sigue las siguientes instrucciones:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li> Sigue a @partneracrobatics en Instagram</li>\r\n<li> Sube tu video a Instagram y taguea <b>@partneracrobatics</b>. Usa los hashtags <b>#partneracrobatics #basethisvideochallenge #basethis #?nailedit</b></li>\r\n<li> Comparte tu video en Facebook y postea lo a la <a href=\'https://www.facebook.com/events/770501809723983/\' target=\'_blank\'>página del profesorado de Partner Acrobatics en México</a> \r\n(solo los likes en Instagram y en la página del evento serán contados)</li>\r\n<li>Dile a tus amigos que voten!!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>La votación será <b>hasta el 30 de junio</b>. ¡Buena suerte!</p>'),(335,0,1,'thai_program_subtitle','thai_program_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Chiang Mai, Thailand<br>Jan 3rd to 16th, 2017','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-14 07:52:48',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Tailandia<br>\r\nDesde el 2  hasta el 15 de Enero 2016</h3>'),(336,0,1,'thai_program_intro','thai_program_intro',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<p>A two week long Intensive Training in Partner Acrobatics.</p><br>\n\n<p>PartnerAcrobatics.com Intensives are unique because our students get to create their own personal acro adventure. Simultaneous classes are offered daily, each with varying levels of acrobatic competency; all classes are geared towards having students increase their own abilities. Higher level offerings will have separate pre-requisites that will need to be met in order to participate in the class. This encourages students to be able to work with other participants in the course who are working on similar skill sets. </p><br>\n\n<p> In our Partner Acrobatics programs we cover many different acrobatic disciplines: standing acrobatics, handstand training, washing machines, trio tricks, Icarian games, to name a few.<br> This physical intensity is balanced out with our therapeutic sessions, which aim to heal and restore the body. You have the freedom to choose how many hours you spend on Acro vs Therapeutics.<br></p><br>\n\n<p>This program will give you the chance to refine your Acro skills and to have loads of fun.<br>\n\n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-21 15:22:58',NULL,NULL,'','<p>Un programa de entreno en Acrobacia en Pareja (Partner Acrobatics) donde podrás entrenarte intensamente durante 2 semanas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Instrucciones son en Ingles pero muchos de los profes hablan Español</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Este curso esta dedicado a mejorar tus práctica personal de acróbata<br>\r\nHabrá tiempo dedicado para mejorar tus capacidades de actuar en público y afinar tus movimientos acrobáticos. <br>\r\n6 o más horas a la semana estarán dedicadas al trabajo terapéutico para recuperar y mantener tu cuerpo sano\r\n</p>'),(337,0,1,'thai_location_subtitle','thai_location_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Thailand<br>From Jan 3rd to 16th, 2017</h3>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-05-29 09:21:50',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Tailandia<br>\r\nDesde el 2  hasta el 15 de Enero 2016</h3>'),(338,0,1,'thai_location_main ','thai_location_main ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<b>Chiang Mai</b> is located in the North of Thailand.  \r\n<br>Kaomai Lanna Hotel and Resort is a unique boutique accommodation on the route from Chiang Mai to Doi Inthanon, the highest mountain in Thailand.  <br>\r\n\r\n<br>Kaomai Lanna offers us a luxury stay with high standards and great service. The resort facilities include air conditioning, wifi and swimming pool.\r\n<br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.kaomailanna.com</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Accommodation</h3>\r\n<img src=\'img/gallery_photo_11b.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\r\n<p>\r\nThe accommodation <b>is included</b> as part of the course price.<br>\r\nAt Kaomai Lanna Hotel there are three types of rooms available:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Superior</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_superior.php\' target=\'_blank\'>check here</a> for details and pictures </br>\r\n<li><b>Deluxe</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_deluxe.php\' target=\'_blank\'>check here</a> for details and pictures </br>\r\n<li><b>Kaomai Deluxe</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_kaomai.php\' target=\'_blank\'>check here</a> for details and pictures </br>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Food</h3>\r\n<p>Food is also <b>included</b>.  At Kaomai Lanna Resort you\'ll receive three vegetarian meals per day.<br>\r\nA bar is available for extra food or beverage (bar consumption is  not included).\r\n</p>\r\n<img src=\'img/gallery_photo_14b.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\r\n\r\n<h3>Internet</h3>\r\n<p> A wifi connection is available at Kaomai Lanna. <br>\r\nIf you want to be sure of the quality of the connection you are recommended to aquire a 3G usb connector in Chiang Mai or Bangkok.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Mobile phones</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n Bring yours and buy a local sim card if you want to make and receive local or international calls.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Planning & Getting to Thailand</h2>\r\n<p>We recommend you to enjoy Chiang Mai for few days before the training and possibly stay longer afterwards.</p>\r\n<p>If you want to stay longer than 30 days apply for a 2 month visa before you come to Thailand.<br>\r\nMost countries automatically receive 30 days upon arrival.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Visas</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Check this page about visa policies of Thailand</b>: <a href=\'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visa_policy_of_Thailand\'>Visa policy of Thailand</a> <br>\r\nOr contact the Thai Embassy in your country for details on how to apply for a visa. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Vaccinations</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nWe have visited Thailand several times and have never taken vaccinations or anti malaria drugs etc.  Malaria is not prevalent. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nCheck with your local travel clinic and ask their advice so you can make your own informed choice as to whether you want to take any vaccines or medicines. <br>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWe do recommend that you invest in a good travel insurance then if the unexpected happens you will be well looked after by the great hospitals and medical teams in Chiang Mai. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Getting to Kaomai Lanna</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nYou can take a taxi or songtao (shared taxi) from Chiang Mai to Kaomai Lanna (25 km).\r\n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2015-06-12 00:32:56',NULL,NULL,'','<b>Chiang Mai</b> está localizado en el norte de Tailandia.  \r\n<br>Kaomai Lanna Hotel and Resort es un alojamiento único en la ruta desde Chiang Mai a Doi Inthanon, la montaña más alta de Tailandia.  <br>\r\n\r\n<br>Kaomai Lanna nos ofrece una estancia de lujo con gran servicio. Las instalaciones del complejo incluyen aire acondicionado, wifi y piscina.\r\n<br>\r\n<a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.kaomailanna.com</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Alojamiento</h3>\r\n<img src=\'img/gallery_photo_11b.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\r\n<p>\r\nEl alojamiento <b>está incluido</b> como parte del precio del curso.<br>\r\nEn Kaomai Lanna Hotel hay tres tipos de habitaciones disponibles:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>Superior</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_superior.php\' target=\'_blank\'>marque aquí</a> para más detalles y fotos </br>\r\n<li><b>Deluxe</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_deluxe.php\' target=\'_blank\'>marque aquí</a> para más detalles y fotos </br>\r\n<li><b>Kaomai Deluxe</b> - <a href=\'http://www.kaomailanna.com/barnroom_kaomai.php\' target=\'_blank\'>marque aquí</a> para más detalles y fotos </br>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Comida</h3>\r\n<p>La comida también está <b>incluida</b>.   En Kaomai Lanna Resort Ud. recibirá tres comidas vegetarianas por día.<br>\r\nEl Restaurante está disponible para consumir comidas o bebidas adicionales (el consumo adicional no está incluido).\r\n</p>\r\n<img src=\'img/gallery_photo_14b.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\r\n\r\n<h3>Internet</h3>\r\n<p> Una conexión wifi está disponible en Kaomai Lanna. <br>\r\nSi quiere estar seguro de la calidad de la conexión se recomiende adquirir un conector usb 3G en Chiang Mai o en Bangkok.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Teléfonos Móviles</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n Traiga el suyo y compre una tarjeta SIM local si desea realizar y recibir llamadas locales o internacionales.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Planificando su viaje a Tailandia</h2>\r\n<p>Le recomendamos que disfrute de Chiang Mai unos días antes del entrenamiento y que posiblemente se quede más tiempo después. ¡Es un lugar muy simpático!</p>\r\n<p>Si usted desea permanecer en Tailandia más de 30 días, debería solicitar una visa de 2 meses antes de llegar a Tailandia.<br>\r\nLa mayoría de los países automáticamente reciben 30 días a la llegada.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Visas</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Consulte esta página sobre visas en Tailandia</b>: <a href=\'http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visa_policy_of_Thailand\'>Visa policy of Thailand</a> <br>\r\nO póngase en contacto con la Embajada de Tailandia en su país para obtener más información sobre cómo solicitar una visa.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Vacunas</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nHemos visitado a Tailandia varias veces y nunca hemos tenido vacunas o medicamentos contra la malaria etc. La malaria no es frecuente. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nConsulte en una clínica de viaje local para que pueda hacer su propia decisión en cuanto a vacunas o medicamentos. <br>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLe recomendamos que usted consiga un buen seguro de viaje.  Así, si sucede lo inesperado usted estará bien atendido por los grandes hospitales y equipos médicos en Chiang Mai. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Como llegar a Kaomai Lanna</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nUsted puede tomar un taxi o Songtao (taxi compartido) de Chiang Mai a Kaomai Lanna (25 km).\r\n</p>'),(339,0,1,'thai_info_main','thai_info_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Thailand<br>From Jan 3rd to 16th, 2017</h3>\n<h2> Prerequisites</h2>\n\nWe <b>do require</b> require you have some acrobatic skills. We need you to honestly and accurately asses whether the following skills are accessible/of ease to you (while working with someone of similar skill level) as a base OR flyer, <b>at the time of application</b> you must be able to accomplish the skills without a spotter helping (they can be there for safety).\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Proficiency/comfort spotting tricks at your level\n<li> Kick up into a handstand (you can have a spotter but without help to get in)\n<li> Hold a handstand at the wall for at least a minute.\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=237&title=Side+positions+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232&#37;23content\'>Sidestar</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=251&title=Acro+L-Base+Transition+Basics+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Prasarita twist</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Star (shoulderstand on feet)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=243&title=Shoulderstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free shoulderstand in hands (flyer holding bases arms)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Thighstand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=249&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Foot to Hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<!-- <li><a href=\'\'>...</a><br> -->\n</ul>\n\n<p>On your application you will be asked to rate your comfort level in the following.... while they are not prerequisites, the more experience you come with the more you will gain out of the training!</p>\n<ul>\n<li> L-BASING (base lying down)\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=183&title=Tic+Tocks+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Tic tocks</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=180&title=Corkscrew+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Corkscrew</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=246&title=Reverse+shoulder+stand+on+feet+%28reverse+star%29+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Reverse star</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free star (no hands)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=248&title=Hand+to+Hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Hand to hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li> STANDING\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Flag (either variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=273&title=Two+High+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>2 man high (hands on calves)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=285&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Foot to hand</a><br>\n<li>Hand to hand<br>\n</ul>\n<p> Send us 1 video</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1-2 minute acrobatic flow of your choice.\n</ul>\n<p>The video should represent where you are at skill-wise, however, it doesn’t \nneed to be all of the craziest things you can do---think elements from the \npreqs! The video also doesn’t need to be of high production quality, a \nquick one on your cell phone is fine:)\n</p>\n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-05-29 10:11:17',NULL,NULL,'','<h2> Requisitos previos </h2>\n<p>\n <b> Se requiere </b> que  tengas algunas habilidades acrobáticas. Necesitamos que nos envía un video por cada elemento en la lista de abajo.\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Una parada de cabeza sólida, lo que significa que\nen parada de cabeza en trípode tu puedas carpar y levantar piernas unas cuantas veces sin tener que bajar tus piernas al suelo.\nSin pared o cuidador. (<a href=\'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BfRHNyT7KBc\' target=\'_blank\'> mirar este vídeo </a>). <br>\n<li> Mantener una parada de manos en la pared, por lo menos de un minuto.\n<li> Estar de base y volar en Star ( Estrella = parada de hombros en los pies) durante al menos un minuto.\n<li> <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L7wvnSGOvbY\'> Prasarita </a>\n<li> Un video de un minuto de flow acrobatico en pareja sobre lo que te gusta mas.\n</ul>\n<p> Antes de aplicar subir tus videos a youtube o facebook. </p>\n<h2>Ejercicios recomendados</h2>\n\n<p>\nEn los días previos a la formación será útil que usted comience a practicar algunos de los ejercicios que vamos a hacer como parte del condicionamiento. Aquí algunas descripciones y enlaces a vídeos. En todos estos ejercicios menos es más, es mucho mejor hacer menos repeticiones y de la forma apropiada. Repita hasta que puedas con buena forma.\n</p>\n\n<h3> Círculos  en parada de cabeza </h3>\n<iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/gYfCkhNs9-I?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\n<p> Cualquier variación de parada de cabeza (o parada de manos si la tienes) está bien, jugar con los círculos en ambas direcciones, tratando de mantener las piernas rectas y los pies en punta.\n</p>\n\n<h3> V ups </h3>\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/hAAMBQrHH14?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\n<p>Trate de mantener la columna recta. Relaje los hombros, nunca trabajar a través del dolor y ser consciente de su espalda baja.</p>\n\n<h3> Tuck up, Straddle up, Pike up  </h3>\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/STuoafM2zhk?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\n<p> En parada de cabeza (o en pino :)) practicar tuck up (en una bola), straddle up (teniendo las piernas abiertas a los lados) y piking (ambas piernas por delante y recto). Trate de no saltar. Estamos en busca de control, tratamos de bajar lento como se sube. </p>\n\n<h3> Tabla inversa hasta Tuck Sit </h3>\n  <iframe width = \'300\' height = \'200\' src = \'http://www.youtube.com/embed/CtHrtD__mJA?rel=0\' frameborder = \'0\' allowfullscreen> </iframe>\n<p> Comience con sus muñecas bajo los hombros y las rodillas sobre las tobillos, utilice su centro para mover las caderas hacia atrás entre los brazos y volver a la posición inicial </p>\n\n<h3> Equilibrio  sobre antebrazos</h3>\n<p> Trate de abrir a través de los hombros, sacar las costillas bajas en el cuerpo. </p>\n\n<h3> flexiones </h3>\n<p> Usted sabe lo que son! ;) </p>\n\n<h3>  Estiramiento de isquiotibiales </h3>\n<p> Para cualquier persona que tiene dificultades para mantener las piernas rectas a 90 grados para hacer de base </p>\n'),(340,0,1,'thai_fees_subtitle','thai_fees_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Thailand<br>From Jan 3rd to 16th, 2017</h3>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-05-29 09:22:30',NULL,NULL,'','<h3>Chiang Mai, Tailandia<br>\r\nDesde el 2  hasta el 15 de Enero 2016</h3>'),(342,0,1,'thai_fees_main','thai_fees_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','\n\nPrices are per person, including the 2 week training, accommodation and three vegetarian meals daily.(sometimes there will optional meat)<br><br>\n\nThe price of the course does not include flights or airport pickup.<br><br>\n\nArrival time January 3rd evening (dinner included), departure time January 16th morning (breakfast included).<br><br>\n\n<h3>Regular Price</h3>\n\nPaid in full after September 10th 2016 non refundable.<br><br>\n\n\'\'Superior\'\' shared (2 single beds) - 1850 Euros per person<br>\n\'\'Deluxe\'\' shared (2 single beds) - 2350 Euros per person<br>\n\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' couple (king size bed) - 4750 Euros per couple<br>\n\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' private (king size bed) - 3450 Euros per person<br>\n\'\'Princess room\'\' private (2 people) - 5000 Euros per couple<br>\n\n<h3>Prerequisites</h3>\nBefore applying upload the videos of yourself practicing the prerequisites to youtube or facebook.<br>\n\n<h3>Application</h3>\nSpace is limited and will fill up.<br>\n\n<a href=\'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd3P8C7_JGC4LoXtIVckHnEViXxrGLz2lflF6f-BheapQfyCQ/viewform\' target=\'_blank\'>Click here to fill out a form</a>, if you have any further questions drop an email to <a href=\'mailto:info@partneracrobatics.com\'>info@partneracrobatics.com</a> <br><br>\n\nAfter being accepted we will send you payment details.  Only once you have paid your space will be guaranteed at the training.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-12-01 13:59:09',NULL,NULL,'','<p>Prices include the month long training, accommodation and three vegetarian meals daily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The price of the course <b>does not include</b> flights or airport pickup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arrival time January 2nd evening (dinner included), departure time January 15th morning (breakfast included).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Early Bird (discounted price)</h4>\r\n<p>Paid in full before September 10th (50% <b>non refundable</b>).</p>\r\n<p>Room options:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Superior\'\' shared</b>  (2 single beds) - 1400 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Deluxe\'\'  shared</b> (2 single beds) - 1900 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' couple</b>  (king size bed) - 3200 Euros </li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' private</b>  (king size bed) - 3000 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Princess room\'\' private</b> (2 people) - 4300 Euros</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4>Regular Price</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Paid in full after September 10th (50% <b>non refundable</b>).</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Superior\'\' shared</b>  (2 single beds) - 1800 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Deluxe\'\'  shared</b> (2 single beds) - 2300 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' couple</b>  (king size bed) - 4000 Euros </li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Kaomai Deluxe\'\' private</b>  (king size bed) - 3400 Euros</li>\r\n<li><b>\'\'Princess room\'\' private</b> (2 people) - 4700 Euros</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2> Prerequisites</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Before applying upload the videos of yourself practicing the <a href=\'info-thai.php\'>prerequisites</a> to youtube or facebook.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2> Application</h2>\r\n<p>Space is limited and will fill up. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nPlease fill out the form, send a photo of yourself and the link to your videos\r\nto <b>info@partneracrobatics.com</b>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAfter being accepted we will send payment details.<br>\r\n<b>Only once you have paid your space will be guaranteed at the training</b>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1068N6I1u3bos4tQcwet_X6vbmS4YvsGQs-qCr2E4Is0/viewform\' target=\'_blank\'>click here to go to the form</a>\r\n</p>\r\n'),(665,NULL,1,'tt_info_main','tt_info_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>\nWe <b>do require</b> require you have some acrobatic skills. We need you to honestly and accurately asses whether the following skills are accessible/of ease to you (while working with someone of similar skill level) as a base OR flyer, <b>at the time of application</b> you must be able to accomplish the skills without a spotter helping (they can be there for safety).\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Proficiency/comfort spotting tricks at your level\n<li> Kick up into a handstand (you can have a spotter but without help to get in)\n<li> Hold a handstand at the wall for at least a minute.\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=237&title=Side+positions+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232&#37;23content\'>Sidestar</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=251&title=Acro+L-Base+Transition+Basics+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Prasarita twist</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Star (shoulderstand on feet)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=243&title=Shoulderstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free shoulderstand in hands (flyer holding bases arms)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Thighstand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=249&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Foot to Hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<!-- <li><a href=\'\'>...</a><br> -->\n</ul>\n\n<p>On your application you will be asked to rate your comfort level in the following.... while they are not prerequisites, the more experience you come with the more you will gain out of the training!</p>\n<ul>\n<li> L-BASING (base lying down)\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=183&title=Tic+Tocks+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Tic tocks</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=180&title=Corkscrew+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Corkscrew</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=246&title=Reverse+shoulder+stand+on+feet+%28reverse+star%29+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Reverse star</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free star (no hands)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=248&title=Hand+to+Hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Hand to hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li> STANDING\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Flag (either variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=273&title=Two+High+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>2 man high (hands on calves)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=285&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Foot to hand</a><br>\n<li>Hand to hand<br>\n</ul>\n<p> Send us 1 video</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1-2 minute acrobatic flow of your choice.\n</ul>\n<p>The video should represent where you are at skill-wise, however, it doesn’t \nneed to be all of the craziest things you can do---think elements from the \npreqs! The video also doesn’t need to be of high production quality, a \nquick one on your cell phone is fine:)\n</p>\n\n<h2>Suggested Conditioning/Drills</h2>\n<p>\nLeading up to the training it will be helpful for you to start to practice some of the exercises we will be doing as part of conditioning, here are some descriptions and links to videos.  In all these exercises less is more, it’s much better to do fewer repetitions with proper form than to compensate and recruit other muscles.  Repeat as many as you can with good form.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Headstand Circles </h3>\n<iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/gYfCkhNs9-I?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>Any variation of headstand(or handstand if you’re there!) is fine, play with the circles in both directions, try to keep the legs straight and toes pointed\nWork on maintaining your balance, core and integrity through the shoulder girdle\n</p>\n\n<h3>V ups</h3>\n <iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/hAAMBQrHH14?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>Option to modify by starting with leg lifts, keeping the hands under the hips and/or bending the knees.  Try to keep the spine straight if you are bringing it up.  Relax the shoulders, never work through pain and be mindful of your low back.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Tuck up, Straddle up, Pike up </h3>\n <iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/STuoafM2zhk?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>In headstand(or handstand:)) practice coming up into position by tucking(into a ball), straddling(taking legs wide to the sides) and piking(both legs in front and straight).  Try not to hop.  We are looking for control, try to come down slower than you go up.</p>\n\n<h3>Reverse Table to Tuck Sit </h3>\n <iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/CtHrtD__mJA?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>Start with your wrists under your shoulders and knees over hips, use your core to draw your hips back through your arms and return to starting position</p>\n\n<h3>Forearm Balance </h3>\n<p>Try to open through the shoulders, draw the low ribs into the body.</p>\n\n<h3>Push Ups</h3>\n<p>You know what it is! ;)</p>\n\n<h3>Hamstring Stretches</h3>\n<p>For anyone who has difficulty keeping the legs straight at 90 degrees for basing</p>\n</div>\n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,0,1,'Acro l-base intermediate/advanced','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','manual',NULL,NULL,8,NULL,'2016-08-03 11:51:29',NULL,NULL,'Acro l-base intermediate/advanced',''),(345,0,1,'Acro standing Intermediate/Advanced','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','manual',NULL,NULL,9,NULL,'2015-06-09 11:14:24',NULL,NULL,'Acro standing Intermediate/Advanced',''),(346,271,1,'Walking up to two high ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<iframe width=\'65%\' height=\'500\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/RPoLUnPynGA?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\nbase: <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=72\'>Roj</a><br>\r\nflyer: <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=73\'>Blox</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n','manual',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-03 12:36:27',NULL,NULL,'Walking up to two high ',''),(347,232,1,'Walk into shoulderstand ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','<iframe width=\'65%\' height=\'500\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/G36RDgrAhKk?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\nbase: <a href=\'http://partner-acrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=73\'>Blox</a><br>\r\nflyer: <a href=\'http://partner-acrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=52\'>Fons</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<iframe width=\'65%\' height=\'500\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/aQ959DLFzzY?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\nbase: \r\n<a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=32\'>Lorenz