llscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\nbase: \r\n<a href=‘#’>Else</a><br>\r\nflyer: \r\n<a href=‘www.monikakolb.de’>Monika</a>\r\n','manual',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-03 12:39:39',NULL,NULL,'Rolling up to chair, facing away ',''),(366,0,1,'Trios - Passing the flyer','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','manual',NULL,NULL,10,NULL,'2015-06-09 11:12:43',NULL,NULL,'Trios - Passing the flyer',''),(369,NULL,1,'15_location_subtitle','15_location_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>1 or 2 weeks from June 8th-21st, 2017</h2>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-29 21:23:03',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(370,NULL,1,'15_info_subtitle','15_info_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Andalucia, Spain<br><br>June 8th - 21st, 2017</h2>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-29 21:23:14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(371,NULL,1,'15_fees_subtitle','15_fees_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Andalucia, Spain</h2><br><h2>7 or 15 days from June 8th to 21th, 2017</h2>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-08-29 19:48:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(372,NULL,1,'15_info_main','15_info_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>\nWe <b>do require</b> require you have some acrobatic skills. We need you to honestly and accurately asses whether the following skills are accessible/of ease to you (while working with someone of similar skill level) as a base OR flyer, <b>at the time of application</b> you must be able to accomplish the skills without a spotter helping (they can be there for safety).\n</p>\n<ul>\n<li> Proficiency/comfort spotting tricks at your level\n<li> Kick up into a handstand (you can have a spotter but without help to get in)\n<li> Hold a handstand at the wall for at least a minute.\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=237&title=Side+positions+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232&#37;23content\'>Sidestar</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=251&title=Acro+L-Base+Transition+Basics+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Prasarita twist</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Star (shoulderstand on feet)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=243&title=Shoulderstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free shoulderstand in hands (flyer holding bases arms)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Thighstand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=249&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Foot to Hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<!-- <li><a href=\'\'>...</a><br> -->\n</ul>\n\n<p>On your application you will be asked to rate your comfort level in the following.... while they are not prerequisites, the more experience you come with the more you will gain out of the training!</p>\n<ul>\n<li> L-BASING (base lying down)\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=183&title=Tic+Tocks+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Tic tocks</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=180&title=Corkscrew+-+Acro+Manual&parent=175%23content\'>Corkscrew</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=246&title=Reverse+shoulder+stand+on+feet+%28reverse+star%29+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Reverse star</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=244&title=shoulderstands+on+feet+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Free star (no hands)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=248&title=Hand+to+Hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=232%23content\'>Hand to hand (any variation)</a><br>\n<li> STANDING\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=272&title=Thighstands+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Flag (either variation)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=273&title=Two+High+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>2 man high (hands on calves)</a><br>\n<li><a href=\'/manual.php?id=285&title=Foot+to+hand+-+Acro+Manual&parent=271%23content\'>Foot to hand</a><br>\n<li>Hand to hand<br>\n</ul>\n<p> Send us 1 video</p>\n<ul>\n<li> 1-2 minute acrobatic flow of your choice.\n</ul>\n<p>The video should represent where you are at skill-wise, however, it doesn’t \nneed to be all of the craziest things you can do---think elements from the \npreqs! The video also doesn’t need to be of high production quality, a \nquick one on your cell phone is fine:)\n</p>\n\n<h2>Suggested Conditioning/Drills</h2>\n<p>\nLeading up to the training it will be helpful for you to start to practice some of the exercises we will be doing as part of conditioning, here are some descriptions and links to videos.  In all these exercises less is more, it’s much better to do fewer repetitions with proper form than to compensate and recruit other muscles.  Repeat as many as you can with good form.\n</p>\n\n<h3>Headstand Circles </h3>\n<iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/gYfCkhNs9-I?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>Any variation of headstand(or handstand if you’re there!) is fine, play with the circles in both directions, try to keep the legs straight and toes pointed\nWork on maintaining your balance, core and integrity through the shoulder girdle\n</p>\n\n<h3>Tuck up, Straddle up, Pike up </h3>\n <iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/STuoafM2zhk?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>In headstand(or handstand:)) practice coming up into position by tucking(into a ball), straddling(taking legs wide to the sides) and piking(both legs in front and straight).  Try not to hop.  We are looking for control, try to come down slower than you go up.</p>\n\n<h3>Reverse Table to Tuck Sit </h3>\n <iframe width=\'300\' height=\'200\' src=\'http://www.youtube.com/embed/CtHrtD__mJA?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p>Start with your wrists under your shoulders and knees over hips, use your core to draw your hips back through your arms and return to starting position</p>\n\n<h3>Forearm Balance </h3>\n<p>Try to open through the shoulders, draw the low ribs into the body.</p>\n\n<h3>Push Ups</h3>\n<p>You know what it is! ;)</p>\n\n<h3>Squats</h3>\n<p>Work on keeping your torso vertical, shoulders over hips</p>\n\n<h3>Hamstring Stretches</h3>\n<p>For anyone who has difficulty keeping the legs straight at 90 degrees for basing</p>\n</div>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-05-29 13:18:45',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(373,NULL,1,'15_fees_main','15_fees_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Prices</h2>\n<p>Prices include the training, accommodation and three mostly vegetarian meals daily.</p> </p>\n\n<p>\nThe price of the course <b>does not include</b> flights or transportation.</p>\n\n<p>For <b>1 week program</b> the arrival time is June 8th evening (dinner included), departure time June 15th morning\n (breakfast included).</p>\n <p>For <b>2 week program</b> the arrival time is June 8th evening (dinner included), departure time June 21st morning\n (breakfast included).</p>\n\n\n<h3>Early Bird (discounted price)</h3>\n\nPaid in full before February 10th 2017 ( 50&#37; refundable before April 10th).<br><br>\n\n<p>Room options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for 2 weeks - 1500 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for 2 weeks -  1250 Euro\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for first week only - 1000 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for first week only -  750 Euro<br>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Regular Price</h3>\n\nAfter Feb 10th\n<p>Room options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for 2 weeks - 1750 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for 2 weeks -  1450 Euro\n<li><b>Shared room</b> for first week only - 1100 Euro\n<li><b>Camping</b>  for first week only -  850 Euro<br>\n (Prices are 50% refundable before May 10th) \n</ul>\n\n<h2> Prerequisites</h2>\n\n<p><b>Before applying</b> please upload your <a href=\'info-15.php\'>prerequisite</a> video to youtube/facebook etc.</p>\n\n\n<h2> Application</h2>\n\n\nSpace is limited and expect to fill up.<br>\n\n <a href=\'https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdP9sNm8raBy-_sjuR5Q6VNTTXl6cBNsHQnGamkZfTLtfA5sw/viewform\' target=\'_blank\'>Click here to fill out an application form</a>, if you have any further questions don\'t hesitate to email <a href=\'mailto:info@partneracrobatics.com\'>info@partneracrobatics.com</a> <br><br>\n\nAfter being accepted we will send payment details. Only once you have paid your space will be guaranteed at the training.\n\n</p>\n\n\n</div><!--. content -->\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2017-01-11 17:35:06',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(374,NULL,1,'tt_program_subtitle','tt_program_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Andalucia, Spain<br>Aug 1st to Aug 28th, 2017','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-14 07:53:14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(375,NULL,1,'tt_location_subtitle','tt_location_subtitle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Andalucia, Spain<br>From Aug 1st to Aug 28th, 2017</h2>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-09-01 07:48:33',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(376,NULL,1,'tt_location_main','tt_location_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h3>Venue</h3>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_shala.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n                <p><b>Cortijo Caseria Del Mercado</b> is a small organic farm high in the Alpujarras mountains of Andalucia, southern Spain.</p>\n                <p>In addition to the huge array of fruit and vegetables grown on site the farm has goats, horses and a peacock breeding sanctuary and the farm produces its own organic olive oil.</p>\n                <p>Not only is the cortijo a working farm it has been adapted as a retreat centre with traditional Spanish accommodation, a natural mineral water swimming pool and a yoga shala.</p>\n                <p>The local area is fantastic hiking country with spectacular mountain views and isolated “White villages”.</p>\n                <p>More info on the venue can be found <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'http://cortijolacaseria.com\'>here</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Accommodation</h3>\n<p>\nThe accommodation <b>is included</b> as part of the course price.<br>\n</p>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_main.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n\n                <p>The venues farm buildings offer various basic but comfortable accommodations with a communal and family feel .</p>\n                <p>Shared accommodation is included in the course fee, numbers permitting and for an additional fee single accom may be available, please contact us for availability.</p>\n        		<p>For those camping bring all your own gear, we don\'t provide tents but we have lots of extra blankets.</p>\n<h3>Food</h3>\n                <p>3 mostly vegetarian meals daily are included in the training fee.  Organic and local when possible.</p>\n                <p>There is a large communal kitchen and 3 smaller kitchens where students can prepare their own snacks etc.  Seasonal fruits and vegetables are available from the farm and they are amazing!</p>\n\n<h3>How to get there</h3>\n<img src=\'img/cortijo_acro.jpg\' width=\'300px\' align=\'right\'>\n\n                <p>The cortijo is high in the mountains close to a tiny village called Castaras. The closest town is Orgiva.  </p>\n                <p>We will provide pick up and trasport to and from Orgiva on the 8th, 15th and 22nd.</p>\n                <p>The closest airport Granada is about 1.5 hours away from our venue.</p>\n                <p>Malaga is just as close but has limited bus connection to Orgiva. Check <a href=\'http://www.alsa.es/en/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.Alsa.es</a> timetable.</p>\n                <p>There are several cheap flights daily from Madrid and Barcelona to Granada.</p>\n                <p></p>\n                <p>From Granada you can catch a bus to Orgiva (1 hour). Check <a href=\'http://www.alsa.es/en/\' target=\'_blank\'>www.Alsa.es</a> timetable. </p>\n\n                <p><b>GPS coords:</b> 36° 55.543, -3° 16.388</p>\n\n                <p>On <a target=\'_blank\' href=\'https://www.google.com/maps?t=h&ll=36.92571669999994%2C-3.273133300000014&spn=0.009194283237178443%2C0.01533507242441279&output=classic\'>google maps</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>Internet</h3>\n<p> A wifi connection is available at the Cortijo. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h3>Recommendations</h3>\n\n\n\n\n<p>\nWe do recommend that you invest in a good <b>travel insurance</b> then if the unexpected happens you will be well looked after financially.\n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(377,NULL,1,'tt_program_intro','tt_program_intro',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n<p>Our Partner Acrobatics teacher training program offers an opportunity to intensively train for four weeks, whilst learning the skills and tools to teach successful acro classes and workshops. We encourage and support our students in developing their own teaching style, based on the latest principals of neuroscience and motor learning and our own extensive teaching experience.</p>\n <br>\n<p>Moreover plenty of time will be dedicated to improve your personal acrobatic practice. Some time will be dedicated to prepare public performances and work on the aesthetics of your acro moves. A minimum of six hours per week is dedicated to therapeutics to restore your body. Students have the option to focus their training and choose the amount of hours spent practicing acrobatics and/or therapeutics.</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2015-12-13 07:01:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(378,NULL,1,'tt_program_main','tt_program_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Teachers</h2>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=33\'><span class=\'teacherIcon emily\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Emily Baxter<span></a> -  Super mama, loves party time</div></div>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=34\'><span class=\'teacherIcon niko\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Niko Douwes<span></a> - Sargent Acro</div></div>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=56\'><span class=\'teacherIcon martin\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Martin Kvist<span></a> -   Prancer Extraordinnaire</div></div>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=36\'><span class=\'teacherIcon mimi\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Mimi Nuñez<span></a> -  The teacher, when passion matters</div></div>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=76\'><span class=\'teacherIcon zsa\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Zsa Zsa Mak<span></a>Acro Goddess</div></div>\n<div class=\'teacherLI\'><a href=\'teacher.php?id=40\'><span class=\'teacherIcon rhiannon\'> </span><div><span class=\'teacherName \'>Rhiannon Cheroke Whyn<span></a>The soft side of PA</div></div>\n\n<h2>Sample Schedule</h2>\n\n<table cellpadding=\'1em\' border=\'1px solid gray\'>\n  <tr>\n    <th></th>\n    <th>Monday</th>\n    <th>Tuesday</th>\n    <th>Wednesday</th>\n    <th>Thursday</th>\n    <th>Friday</th>\n    <th>Saturday</th>\n    <th>Sunday</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>7-8</td>\n    <td colspan=\'6\' class=\'progOptional\'>Optional activities</td>\n    <td class=\'progOffTime\' rowspan=\'2\'>Day off</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>8-9</td>\n    <td colspan=\'6\' class=\'progWarmUp\'>Prehab</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>9-10</td>\n    <td colspan=\'7\' class=\'progFood\'>Breakfast</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>10:30-11:00</td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progHandstand\'>Handstands</td>\n    <td rowspan=\'2\' class=\'progTherapy\'>Therapeutic practice</td>\n    <td colspan=\'3\' class=\'progHandstand\'>Handstands</td>\n    <td rowspan=\'2\' class=\'progOffTime\'></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>11-1<br></td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progFoundations\'>Foundation - Acro training</td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progFoundations\'>Foundation - Acro training</td>\n    <td class=\'progTeaching\'>Teaching Practice</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>1-3</td>\n    <td colspan=\'7\' class=\'progFood\'>Lunch break<br></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>3:30-4:30</td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Mixed Grill</td>\n    <td class=\'progOffTime\' rowspan=\'2\'>Afternoon off<br></td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Mixed Grill</td>\n    <td class=\'progTeaching\'>Teaching Practice</td>\n    <td class=\'progOffTime\' rowspan=\'2\'></td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>4:30- 6</td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Mixed Grill or One Minute Practice</td>\n    <td colspan=\'2\' class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Mixed Grill or One Minute Practice</td>\n    <td class=\'progTeaching\'>Teaching Practice</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>6-8</td>\n    <td colspan=\'7\' class=\'progFood\'>Dinner break</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>8-9</td>\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Optional activities</td>\n    <td class=\'progLecture\'>Lecture</td>\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Optional activities</td>\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Optional activities</td>\n    <td class=\'progLecture\'>Lecture</td>\n    <td class=\'progOptional\'>Optional activities</td>\n    <td class=\'progOffTime\'></td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n<h3>Legend</h3>\n<div class=\'progLegend\'>\n  <p><span class=\'progHandstand\'>Handstand</span>: every day a decicated practice to make your Handstand amazing.</p>\n  <p><span class=\'progFoundations\'>Foundations</span>: the Acrobatic skills that everyone has to master.</p>\n  <p><span class=\'progMixedGrill\'>Mixed Grill</span>: 2 or 3 parallel workshops picking from: Standing Acrobatics, Washing Machines, Dutch Acro, Flying Therapeutics, Icarian etc. </p>\n  <p><span class=\'progTherapy\'>Therapeutic Practice</span>: A mix of thai massage, <a href=\'http://flyingtherapeutics.org/\' target=\'_blank\'>Flying Therapeutics</a>, <a href=\'http://one-minute-practice.com\' target=\'_blank\'>One Minute Practice</a> Enjoy resting and recovering.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progTeaching\'>Teaching</span>: Dedicated to grow your skills as a teacher.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progLecture\'>Lecture</span>: From sport science to marketing, perfecting your knowledge as a practitioner and teacher.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progOptional\'>Optional</span>: Dedicated to participants that want to share some special skills with the rest of the group or do your own practice.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progWarmUp\'>Prehab</span>: Injury prevention and conditioning the best practice to prepare your training day.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progFood\'>Food</span>: Mostly vegetarian meals.</p>\n<p><span class=\'progOffTime\'>Off Time</span>: Sometimes we can also rest :)</p>\n</div>\n<p>*More details on the <a href=\'/schedule-tt.php\'>Schedule</a> page.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<p>\nUpon successful completion of this training, students can receive a certificate in Partner Acrobatics declaring that they have completed over 150 hours of training and will be featured on the teachers page of PartnerAcrobatics.com.  While completing a certification program is useful in your path to becoming a teacher, it is potentially more important to build a strong and safe practice that you can confidently share with others. \n</p>','pages',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,'2016-10-07 19:21:32',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(679,678,1,'Swing to shoulderstand with h2h','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','	<iframe width=\'560\' height=\'315\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/C6CTntpj4QM?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\n	base 1: <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=34\'>Niko Douwes</a><br>\r\n	base 2: <a href=\'#\'>Michael Steimel</a><br>\r\n	flyer: <a href=\'#\'>Amy Rowland</a>\r\n\r\n','manual',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,'2016-03-18 09:49:06',NULL,NULL,'',''),(680,678,1,'Swing to shoulderstand with f2h','',NULL,NULL,NULL,'','	<iframe width=\'560\' height=\'315\' src=\'//www.youtube.com/embed/8tdXTm1kvEg?rel=0\' frameborder=\'0\' allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n	<br><br>\r\n	base 1: <a href=\'http://partneracrobatics.com/teacher.php?id=34\'>Niko Douwes</a><br>\r\n	base 2: <a href=\'#\'>Michael Steimel</a><br>\r\n	flyer: <a href=\'#\'>Amy Rowland</a>\r\n','manual',NULL,NULL,2,NULL,'2016-03-18 09:49:28',NULL,NULL,'',''),(379,NULL,1,'tt_fees_main','tt_fees_main',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<h2>Prices </h2>\n<p>Prices include the training, accommodation and three mostly vegetarian meals daily.</p>\n\n<p>\nThe price of the course <b>does not include</b> flights or transportation.</p>\n\n<p